03Lv 1:1 Then the LORD summoned Moses and spoke to him from the tent of meeting:
03Lv 1:2 "Speak to the Israelites and tell them: When any of you brings an offering to the LORD from the livestock, you may bring your offering from the herd or the flock.
03Lv 1:3 "If his gift is a burnt offering from the herd, he is to bring an unblemished male. He must bring it to the entrance to the tent of meeting so that he may be accepted by the LORD.
03Lv 1:4 He is to lay his hand on the head of the burnt offering so it can be accepted on his behalf to make atonement for him.
03Lv 1:5 He is to slaughter the bull before the LORD; Aaron's sons the priests are to present the blood and sprinkle it on all sides of the altar that is at the entrance to the tent of meeting.
03Lv 1:6 Then he must skin the burnt offering and cut it into pieces.
03Lv 1:7 The sons of Aaron the priest will prepare a fire on the altar and arrange wood on the fire.
03Lv 1:8 Aaron's sons the priests are to arrange the pieces, the head, and the suet on top of the burning wood on the altar.
03Lv 1:9 The offerer must wash its entrails and shanks with water. Then the priest will burn all of it on the altar as a burnt offering, a fire offering of a pleasing aroma to the LORD.
03Lv 1:10 "But if his gift for a burnt offering is from the flock, from sheep or goats, he is to present an unblemished male.
03Lv 1:11 He will slaughter it on the north side of the altar before the LORD. Aaron's sons the priests will sprinkle its blood against the altar on all sides.
03Lv 1:12 He will cut it into pieces with its head and its suet, and the priest will arrange them on top of the burning wood on the altar.
03Lv 1:13 But he is to wash the entrails and shanks with water. The priest will then present all of it and burn [it] on the altar; it is a burnt offering, a fire offering of a pleasing aroma to the LORD.
03Lv 1:14 "If his gift to the LORD is a burnt offering of birds, he is to present his offering from the turtledoves or young pigeons.
03Lv 1:15 Then the priest must bring it to the altar, and must twist off its head and burn [it] on the altar; its blood should be drained at the side of the altar.
03Lv 1:16 He will remove its digestive tract, cutting off the tail feathers, and throw it on the east side of the altar at the place for ashes.
03Lv 1:17 He will tear it open by its wings without dividing [the bird]. Then the priest is to burn it on the altar on top of the burning wood. It is a burnt offering, a fire offering of a pleasing aroma to the LORD.
03Lv 2:1 "When anyone presents a grain offering as a gift to the LORD, his gift must consist of fine flour. He is to pour olive oil on it, put frankincense on it,
03Lv 2:2 and bring it to Aaron's sons the priests. The priest will take a handful of fine flour and oil from it, along with all its frankincense, and will burn this memorial portion of it on the altar, a fire offering of a pleasing aroma to the LORD.
03Lv 2:3 But the rest of the grain offering will belong to Aaron and his sons, the holiest part of the fire offerings to the LORD.
03Lv 2:4 "When you present a grain offering baked in an oven, it must be [made] of fine flour, either unleavened cakes mixed with oil or unleavened wafers coated with oil.
03Lv 2:5 If your gift is a grain offering prepared on the griddle, it must be unleavened bread [made] of fine flour mixed with oil.
03Lv 2:6 Break it into pieces and pour oil on it; it is a grain offering.
03Lv 2:7 If your gift is a grain offering [prepared] in a pan, it must be made of fine flour with oil.
03Lv 2:8 When you bring to the LORD the grain offering made in any of these ways, it is to be presented to the priest, and he will take it to the altar.
03Lv 2:9 The priest will remove the memorial portion from the grain offering and burn it on the altar, a fire offering of a pleasing aroma to the LORD.
03Lv 2:10 But the rest of the grain offering will belong to Aaron and his sons, the holiest part of the fire offerings to the LORD.
03Lv 2:11 "No grain offering that you present to the LORD is to be made with yeast, for you are not to burn any yeast or honey as a fire offering to the LORD.
03Lv 2:12 You may present them to the LORD as an offering of firstfruits, but they are not to be offered on the altar as a pleasing aroma.
03Lv 2:13 You are to season each of your grain offerings with salt; you must not omit from your grain offering the salt of the covenant with your God. You are to present salt with each of your offerings.
03Lv 2:14 "If you present a grain offering of firstfruits to the LORD, you must present fresh heads of grain, crushed kernels, roasted on the fire, for your grain offering of firstfruits.
03Lv 2:15 You are to put oil and frankincense on it; it is a grain offering.
03Lv 2:16 The priest will then burn some of its crushed kernels and oil with all its frankincense as a fire offering to the LORD.
03Lv 3:1 "If his offering is a fellowship sacrifice, and he is presenting [an animal] from the herd, whether male or female, he must present one without blemish before the LORD.
03Lv 3:2 He is to lay his hand on the head of his offering and slaughter it at the entrance to the tent of meeting. Then Aaron's sons the priests will sprinkle the blood on all sides of the altar.
03Lv 3:3 He will present part of the fellowship sacrifice as a fire offering to the LORD: the fat surrounding the entrails, all the fat that is on the entrails,
03Lv 3:4 and the two kidneys with the fat on them at the loins; he will also remove the fatty lobe of the liver with the kidneys.
03Lv 3:5 Aaron's sons will burn it on the altar along with the burnt offering that is on the burning wood, a fire offering of a pleasing aroma to the LORD.
03Lv 3:6 "If his offering as a fellowship sacrifice to the LORD is from the flock, he must present a male or female without blemish.
03Lv 3:7 If he is presenting a lamb for his offering, he is to present it before the LORD.
03Lv 3:8 He must lay his hand on the head of his offering, then slaughter it before the tent of meeting. Aaron's sons will sprinkle its blood on all sides of the altar.
03Lv 3:9 He will then present part of the fellowship sacrifice as a fire offering to the LORD [consisting of] its fat and the entire fat tail, which he is to remove close to the backbone. He will also remove the fat surrounding the entrails, all the fat on the entrails,
03Lv 3:10 the two kidneys with the fat on them at the loins, and the fatty lobe of the liver above the kidneys.
03Lv 3:11 Then the priest will burn it on the altar as food, a fire offering to the LORD.
03Lv 3:12 "If his offering is a goat, he is to present it before the LORD.
03Lv 3:13 He must lay his hand on its head and slaughter it before the tent of meeting. Aaron's sons will sprinkle its blood on all sides of the altar.
03Lv 3:14 He will present part of his offering as a fire offering to the LORD: the fat surrounding the entrails, all the fat that is on the entrails,
03Lv 3:15 and the two kidneys with the fat on them at the loins; he will also remove the fatty lobe of the liver with the kidneys.
03Lv 3:16 Then the priest will burn them on the altar as food, a fire offering for a pleasing aroma. "All fat belongs to the LORD.
03Lv 3:17 This is a permanent statute throughout your generations, wherever you live: you must not eat any fat or any blood."
03Lv 4:1 Then the LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 4:2 "Tell the Israelites: When someone sins unintentionally against any of the LORD's commands and does anything prohibited by them--
03Lv 4:3 "If the anointed priest sins, bringing guilt on the people, he is to present to the LORD a young, unblemished bull as a sin offering for the sin he has committed.
03Lv 4:4 He must bring the bull to the entrance to the tent of meeting before the LORD, lay his hand on the bull's head, and slaughter it before the LORD.
03Lv 4:5 The anointed priest must then take some of the bull's blood and bring it into the tent of meeting.
03Lv 4:6 The priest is to dip his finger in the blood and sprinkle some of it seven times before the LORD in front of the veil of the sanctuary.
03Lv 4:7 The priest must apply some of the blood to the horns of the altar of fragrant incense that is before the LORD in the tent of meeting. He must pour out the rest of the bull's blood at the base of the altar of burnt offering that is at the entrance to the tent of meeting.
03Lv 4:8 He is to remove all the fat from the bull of the sin offering: the fat surrounding the entrails; all the fat that is on the entrails;
03Lv 4:9 and the two kidneys with the fat on them at the loins. He will also remove the fatty lobe of the liver with the kidneys,
03Lv 4:10 just as the fat is removed from the ox of the fellowship sacrifice. The priest is to burn them on the altar of burnt offering.
03Lv 4:11 But the hide of the bull and all its flesh, with its head and shanks, and its entrails and dung--
03Lv 4:12 all [the rest] of the bull-- he must bring to a ceremonially clean place outside the camp to the ash heap, and must burn it on a wood fire. It is to be burned at the ash heap.
03Lv 4:13 "Now if the whole community of Israel errs, and the matter escapes the notice of the assembly, so that they violate any of the LORD's commands and incur guilt by doing what is prohibited,
03Lv 4:14 then the assembly must present a young bull as a sin offering. When the sin they have committed in regard to the command becomes known, they are to bring it before the tent of meeting.
03Lv 4:15 The elders of the assembly are to lay their hands on the bull's head before the LORD and it is to be slaughtered before the LORD.
03Lv 4:16 The anointed priest will bring some of the bull's blood into the tent of meeting.
03Lv 4:17 The priest is to dip his finger in the blood and sprinkle [it] seven times before the LORD in front of the veil.
03Lv 4:18 He is to apply some of the blood to the horns of the altar that is before the LORD in the tent of meeting. He must pour out the rest of the blood at the base of the altar of burnt offering that is at the entrance to the tent of meeting.
03Lv 4:19 He is to remove all the fat from it and burn it on the altar.
03Lv 4:20 He is to offer this bull just as he did with the bull in the sin offering; he will offer it the same way. So the priest will make atonement on their behalf, and they will be forgiven.
03Lv 4:21 Then he will bring the bull outside the camp and burn it just as he burned the first bull. It is the sin offering for the assembly.
03Lv 4:22 "When a leader sins and unintentionally violates any of the commands of the LORD his God by doing what is prohibited, and incurs guilt,
03Lv 4:23 or someone informs him about the sin he has committed, he is to bring an unblemished male goat as his offering.
03Lv 4:24 He is to lay his hand on the head of the goat and slaughter it at the place where the burnt offering is slaughtered before the LORD. It is a sin offering.
03Lv 4:25 Then the priest must take some of the blood from the sin offering with his finger and apply it to the horns of the altar of burnt offering. The rest of its blood he must pour out at the base of the altar of burnt offering.
03Lv 4:26 He must burn all its fat on the altar, like the fat of the fellowship sacrifice. In this way the priest will make atonement on his behalf for that person's sin, and he will be forgiven.
03Lv 4:27 "Now if any of the common people sins unintentionally by violating one of the LORD's commands, does what is prohibited, and incurs guilt,
03Lv 4:28 or if someone informs him about the sin he has committed, then he is to bring an unblemished female goat as his offering for the sin that he has committed.
03Lv 4:29 He is to lay his hand on the head of the sin offering and slaughter it at the place of the burnt offering.
03Lv 4:30 Then the priest must take some of its blood with his finger and apply it to the horns of the altar of burnt offering. He must pour out the rest of its blood at the base of the altar.
03Lv 4:31 He is to remove all its fat just as the fat is removed from the fellowship sacrifice. The priest is to burn [it] on the altar as a pleasing aroma to the LORD. In this way the priest will make atonement on his behalf, and he will be forgiven.
03Lv 4:32 "Or if the offering that he brings as a sin offering is a lamb, he is to bring an unblemished female.
03Lv 4:33 He is to lay his hand on the head of the sin offering and slaughter it as a sin offering at the place where the burnt offering is slaughtered.
03Lv 4:34 Then the priest must take some of the blood of the sin offering with his finger and apply it to the horns of the altar of burnt offering. He must pour out the rest of its blood at the base of the altar.
03Lv 4:35 He is to remove all its fat just as the fat of the lamb is removed from the fellowship sacrifice. The priest will burn it on the altar along with the fire offerings to the LORD. In this way the priest will make atonement on his behalf for the sin he has committed, and he will be forgiven.
03Lv 5:1 "When someone sins [in any of these ways]: [If] he has seen, heard, or known about something he has witnessed, and did not respond to a public call to testify, he is guilty.
03Lv 5:2 Or [if] someone touches anything unclean-- a carcass of an unclean wild animal, or unclean livestock, or an unclean swarming creature-- without being aware of it, he is unclean and guilty.
03Lv 5:3 Or [if] he touches human uncleanness-- any uncleanness by which one can become defiled-- without being aware of it, but [later] recognizes [it], he is guilty.
03Lv 5:4 Or [if] someone swears rashly to do what is good or evil-- concerning anything a person may speak rashly in an oath-- without being aware of it, but [later] recognizes it, he incurs guilt in such an instance.
03Lv 5:5 If someone incurs guilt in one of these cases, he is to confess he has committed that sin.
03Lv 5:6 He must bring his restitution for the sin he has committed to the LORD: a female lamb or goat from the flock as a sin offering. In this way the priest will make atonement on his behalf for his sin.
03Lv 5:7 "But if he cannot afford an animal from the flock, then he may bring to the LORD two turtledoves or two young pigeons as restitution for his sin-- one as a sin offering and the other as a burnt offering.
03Lv 5:8 He is to bring them to the priest, who will first present the one for the sin offering. He must twist its head at the back of the neck without severing [it].
03Lv 5:9 Then he will sprinkle some of the blood of the sin offering on the side of the altar, while the rest of the blood is to be drained out at the base of the altar; it is a sin offering.
03Lv 5:10 He must prepare the second [bird] as a burnt offering according to the regulation. In this way the priest will make atonement on his behalf for the sin he has committed, and he will be forgiven.
03Lv 5:11 "But if he cannot afford two turtledoves or two young pigeons, he may bring two quarts of fine flour as an offering for his sin. He must not put olive oil or frankincense on it, for it is a sin offering.
03Lv 5:12 He is to bring it to the priest, who will take a handful from it as its memorial portion and burn [it] on the altar along with the fire offerings to the LORD; it is a sin offering.
03Lv 5:13 In this way the priest will make atonement on his behalf concerning the sin he has committed in any of these cases, and he will be forgiven. The rest will belong to the priest, like the grain offering."
03Lv 5:14 Then the LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 5:15 "If someone offends by sinning unintentionally in regard to any of the LORD's holy things, he must bring his restitution offering to the LORD: an unblemished ram from the flock by your valuation in silver shekels, according to the sanctuary shekel, as a restitution offering.
03Lv 5:16 He must make restitution for his sin regarding any holy thing, adding a fifth of its value to it, and give it to the priest. Then the priest will make atonement on his behalf with the ram of the restitution offering, and he will be forgiven.
03Lv 5:17 "If someone sins and without knowing [it] violates any of the LORD's commands concerning anything prohibited, he bears the consequences of his guilt.
03Lv 5:18 He must bring an unblemished ram from the flock according to your valuation as a restitution offering to the priest. Then the priest will make atonement on his behalf for the error he has committed unintentionally, and he will be forgiven.
03Lv 5:19 It is a restitution offering; he is indeed guilty before the LORD."
03Lv 6:1  The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 6:2 "When someone sins and offends the LORD by deceiving his neighbor in regard to a deposit, a security, or a robbery; or defrauds his neighbor;
03Lv 6:3 or finds something lost and lies about it; or swears falsely about any of the sinful things a person may do--
03Lv 6:4 once he has sinned and acknowledged [his] guilt-- he must return what he stole or defrauded, or the deposit entrusted to him, or the lost item he found,
03Lv 6:5 or anything else about which he swore falsely. He must make full restitution for it and add a fifth of its value to it. He is to pay it to its owner on the day he acknowledges [his] guilt.
03Lv 6:6 Then he must bring his restitution offering to the LORD: an unblemished ram from the flock, according to your valuation, as a restitution offering to the priest.
03Lv 6:7 In this way the priest will make atonement on his behalf before the LORD, and he will be forgiven for anything he may have done to incur guilt."
03Lv 6:8  The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 6:9 "Command Aaron and his sons: This is the law of the burnt offering; the burnt offering itself must remain on the altar's hearth all night until morning, while the fire of the altar is kept burning on it.
03Lv 6:10 The priest is to put on his linen robe and linen undergarments. He is to remove the ashes of the burnt offering the fire has consumed on the altar, and place them beside the altar.
03Lv 6:11 Then he must take off his garments, put on other clothes, and bring the ashes outside the camp to a ceremonially clean place.
03Lv 6:12 The fire on the altar is to be kept burning; it must not go out. Every morning the priest will burn wood on the fire. He is to arrange the burnt offering on the fire and burn the fat portions from the fellowship offerings on it.
03Lv 6:13 Fire must be kept burning on the altar continually; it must not go out.
03Lv 6:14 "Now this is the law of the grain offering: Aaron's sons will present it before the LORD in front of the altar.
03Lv 6:15 The priest is to remove a handful of fine flour and olive oil from the grain offering, with all the frankincense that is on the offering, and burn its memorial portion on the altar as a pleasing aroma to the LORD.
03Lv 6:16 Aaron and his sons may eat the rest of it. It is to be eaten as unleavened bread in a holy place; they are to eat it in the courtyard of the tent of meeting.
03Lv 6:17 It must not be baked with yeast; I have assigned it as their portion from My fire offerings. It is especially holy, like the sin offering and the restitution offering.
03Lv 6:18 Any male among Aaron's descendants may eat it. It is a permanent portion throughout your generations from the fire offerings to the Lord. Anything that touches the offerings will become holy."
03Lv 6:19 The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 6:20 "This is the offering that Aaron and his sons must present to the LORD on the day that he is anointed: two quarts of fine flour as a regular grain offering, half of it in the morning and half in the evening.
03Lv 6:21 It is to be prepared with oil on a griddle; you are to bring it well-kneaded. You must present it as a grain offering of baked pieces, a pleasing aroma to the LORD.
03Lv 6:22 The priest, who is of Aaron's sons and will be anointed to take his place, is to prepare it. It must be completely burned as a permanent portion for the LORD.
03Lv 6:23 Every grain offering for a priest will be a whole burnt offering; it is not to be eaten."
03Lv 6:24 The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 6:25 "Tell Aaron and his sons: This is the law of the sin offering. The sin offering is most holy and must be slaughtered before the LORD at the place where the burnt offering is slaughtered.
03Lv 6:26 The priest who offers it as a sin offering is to eat it. It must be eaten in a holy place, in the courtyard of the tent of meeting.
03Lv 6:27 Anything that touches its flesh will become holy, and if any of its blood spatters on a garment, then you must wash that garment in a holy place.
03Lv 6:28 A clay pot in which the sin offering is boiled must be broken; if it is boiled in a bronze vessel, it must be scoured and rinsed with water.
03Lv 6:29 Any male among the priests may eat it; it is especially holy.
03Lv 6:30 But no sin offering may be eaten if its blood has been brought into the tent of meeting to make atonement in the holy place; it must be burned up.
03Lv 7:1 "Now this is the law of the restitution offering; it is especially holy.
03Lv 7:2 The restitution offering must be slaughtered at the place where the burnt offering is slaughtered, and the priest is to sprinkle its blood on all sides of the altar.
03Lv 7:3 The offerer must present all the fat from it: the fat tail, the fat surrounding the entrails,
03Lv 7:4 and the two kidneys with the fat on them at the loins; he will also remove the fatty lobe of the liver with the kidneys.
03Lv 7:5 The priest will burn them on the altar as a fire offering to the LORD; it is a restitution offering.
03Lv 7:6 Any male among the priests may eat it. It is to be eaten in a holy place; it is especially holy.
03Lv 7:7 "The restitution offering is like the sin offering; the law is the same for both. It belongs to the priest who makes atonement with it.
03Lv 7:8 As for the priest who presents someone's burnt offering, the hide of the burnt offering he has presented belongs to him; it is the priest's.
03Lv 7:9 Any grain offering that is baked in an oven, or prepared in a pan or on a griddle, belongs to the priest who presents it; it is his.
03Lv 7:10 But any grain offering, whether dry or mixed with oil, belongs equally to all of Aaron's sons.
03Lv 7:11 "Now this is the law of the fellowship sacrifice that someone may present to the LORD:
03Lv 7:12 If he presents it for thanksgiving, in addition to the thanksgiving sacrifice, he is to present unleavened cakes mixed with olive oil, unleavened wafers coated with oil, and well-kneaded cakes of fine flour mixed with oil.
03Lv 7:13 He is to present as his offering cakes of leavened bread, with his thanksgiving sacrifice of fellowship.
03Lv 7:14 From the cakes he must present one [portion] of each offering as a contribution to the LORD. It will belong to the priest who sprinkles the blood of the fellowship offering; it is his.
03Lv 7:15 The meat of his thanksgiving sacrifice of fellowship must be eaten on the day he offers it; he may not leave any of it until morning.
03Lv 7:16 "If the sacrifice he offers is a vow or a freewill offering, it is to be eaten on the day he presents his sacrifice, and what is left over may be eaten on the next day.
03Lv 7:17 But what remains of the sacrificial meat by the third day must be burned up.
03Lv 7:18 If any of the meat of his fellowship sacrifice is eaten on the third day, it will not be accepted. It will not be credited to the one who presents it; it is repulsive. The person who eats any of it will be guilty.
03Lv 7:19 "Meat that touches anything unclean must not be eaten; it is to be burned up. Everyone who is clean may eat any [other] meat.
03Lv 7:20 But the one who eats meat from the LORD's fellowship sacrifice while he is unclean, that person must be cut off from his people.
03Lv 7:21 If someone touches anything unclean, whether human uncleanness, an unclean animal, or any unclean, detestable creature, and eats meat from the LORD's fellowship sacrifice, that person must be cut off from his people."
03Lv 7:22 The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 7:23 "Tell the Israelites: You are not to eat any fat of an ox, a sheep, or a goat.
03Lv 7:24 The fat of an animal that dies naturally or is mauled by wild beasts may be used for any purpose, but you must not eat it.
03Lv 7:25 If anyone eats animal fat from a fire offering presented to the LORD, the person who eats [it] must be cut off from his people.
03Lv 7:26 Wherever you live, you must not eat the blood of any bird or animal.
03Lv 7:27 Whoever eats any blood, that person must be cut off from his people."
03Lv 7:28 The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 7:29 "Tell the Israelites: The one who presents a fellowship sacrifice to the LORD must bring an offering to the LORD from his sacrifice.
03Lv 7:30 His own hands will bring the fire offerings to the LORD. He will bring the fat together with the breast. The breast is to be waved as a presentation offering before the LORD.
03Lv 7:31 The priest is to burn the fat on the altar, but the breast belongs to Aaron and his sons.
03Lv 7:32 You are to give the right thigh to the priest as a contribution from your fellowship sacrifices.
03Lv 7:33 The son of Aaron who presents the blood of the fellowship offering and the fat will have the right thigh as a portion.
03Lv 7:34 I have taken from the Israelites the breast of the presentation offering and the thigh of the contribution from their fellowship sacrifices, and have assigned them to Aaron the priest and his sons as a permanent portion from the Israelites."
03Lv 7:35 This is the portion from the fire offerings to the LORD for Aaron and his sons since the day they were presented to serve the LORD as priests.
03Lv 7:36 The LORD commanded this to be given to them by the Israelites on the day He anointed them. It is a permanent portion throughout their generations.
03Lv 7:37 This is the law for the burnt offering, the grain offering, the sin offering, the restitution offering, the ordination offering, and the fellowship sacrifice,
03Lv 7:38 which the LORD commanded Moses on Mount Sinai on the day He commanded the Israelites to present their offerings to the LORD in the Wilderness of Sinai.
03Lv 8:1 The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 8:2 "Take Aaron, his sons with him, the garments, the anointing oil, the bull of the sin offering, the two rams, and the basket of unleavened bread,
03Lv 8:3 and assemble the whole community at the entrance to the tent of meeting."
03Lv 8:4 So Moses did as the LORD commanded him, and the community assembled at the entrance to the tent of meeting.
03Lv 8:5 Moses said to them, "This is what the LORD has commanded to be done."
03Lv 8:6 Then Moses presented Aaron and his sons and washed them with water.
03Lv 8:7 He put the tunic on Aaron, wrapped the sash around him, clothed him with the robe, and put the ephod on him. He put the woven band of the ephod around him and fastened it to him.
03Lv 8:8 Then he put the breastpiece on him and placed the Urim and Thummim into the breastpiece.
03Lv 8:9 He also put the turban on his head and placed the plate of gold, the holy diadem, on the front of the turban, as the LORD had commanded Moses.
03Lv 8:10 Then Moses took the anointing oil and anointed the tabernacle and everything in it to consecrate them.
03Lv 8:11 He sprinkled some of the oil on the altar seven times, anointing the altar with all its utensils, and the basin with its stand, to consecrate them.
03Lv 8:12 He poured some of the anointing oil on Aaron's head and anointed and consecrated him.
03Lv 8:13 Then Moses presented Aaron's sons, clothed them with tunics, wrapped sashes around them, and fastened headbands on them, as the LORD had commanded Moses.
03Lv 8:14 Then he brought the bull near for the sin offering, and Aaron and his sons laid their hands on the head of the bull for the sin offering.
03Lv 8:15 Then Moses slaughtered [it], took the blood, and applied it with his finger to the horns of the altar on all sides, purifying the altar. He poured out the blood at the base of the altar and consecrated it by making atonement for it.
03Lv 8:16 Moses took all the fat that was on the entrails, the fatty lobe of the liver, and the two kidneys with their fat, and he burned them on the altar.
03Lv 8:17 He burned up the bull with its hide, flesh, and dung outside the camp, as the LORD had commanded Moses.
03Lv 8:18 Then he presented the ram for the burnt offering, and Aaron and his sons laid their hands on the head of the ram.
03Lv 8:19 Moses slaughtered it and sprinkled the blood on all sides of the altar.
03Lv 8:20 Moses cut the ram into pieces and burned the head, the pieces, and the suet,
03Lv 8:21 but he washed the entrails and shanks with water. He then burned the entire ram on the altar. It was a burnt offering for a pleasing aroma, a fire offering to the LORD as He had commanded Moses.
03Lv 8:22 Next he presented the second ram, the ram of ordination, and Aaron and his sons laid their hands on the head of the ram.
03Lv 8:23 Moses slaughtered [it], took some of its blood, and put [it] on Aaron's right earlobe, on the thumb of his right hand, and on the big toe of his right foot.
03Lv 8:24 Moses also presented Aaron's sons and put some of the blood on their right earlobes, on the thumbs of their right hands, and on the big toes of their right feet. Then Moses sprinkled the blood on all sides of the altar.
03Lv 8:25 He took the fat-- the fat tail, all the fat that was on the entrails, the fatty lobe of the liver, and the two kidneys with their fat-- as well as the right thigh.
03Lv 8:26 From the basket of unleavened bread that was before the LORD he took one cake of unleavened bread, one cake of bread [made] with oil, and one wafer, and placed [them] on the fat portions and the right thigh.
03Lv 8:27 He put all [these] in the hands of Aaron and his sons and waved them before the LORD as a presentation offering.
03Lv 8:28 Then Moses took them from their hands and burned [them] on the altar with the burnt offering. This was an ordination offering for a pleasing aroma, a fire offering to the LORD.
03Lv 8:29 He also took the breast and waved it before the LORD as a presentation offering; it was Moses' portion of the ordination ram as the LORD had commanded him.
03Lv 8:30 Then Moses took some of the anointing oil and some of the blood that was on the altar and sprinkled [them] on Aaron and his garments, as well as on his sons and their garments. In this way he consecrated Aaron and his garments, as well as his sons and their garments.
03Lv 8:31 Moses said to Aaron and his sons, "Boil the meat at the entrance to the tent of meeting and eat it there with the bread that is in the basket for the ordination offering as I commanded: Aaron and his sons are to eat it.
03Lv 8:32 You must burn up what remains of the meat and bread.
03Lv 8:33 You must not go outside the entrance to the tent of meeting for seven days, until the time your days of ordination are completed, because it will take seven days to ordain you.
03Lv 8:34 The LORD commanded what has been done today in order to make atonement for you.
03Lv 8:35 You must remain at the entrance to the tent of meeting day and night for seven days and keep the LORD's charge so that you will not die, for this is what I was commanded."
03Lv 8:36 So Aaron and his sons did everything the LORD had commanded through Moses.
03Lv 9:1 On the eighth day Moses summoned Aaron, his sons, and the elders of Israel.
03Lv 9:2 He said to Aaron, "Take a young bull for a sin offering and a ram for a burnt offering, both without blemish, and present [them] before the LORD.
03Lv 9:3 And tell the Israelites: 'Take a male goat for a sin offering; a calf and a lamb, male yearlings without blemish, for a burnt offering;
03Lv 9:4 an ox and a ram for a fellowship offering to sacrifice before the LORD; and a grain offering mixed with oil. For today the LORD is going to appear to you.'"
03Lv 9:5 They brought what Moses had commanded to the front of the tent of meeting, and the whole community came forward and stood before the LORD.
03Lv 9:6 Moses said, "This is what the LORD commanded you to do, that the glory of the LORD may appear to you."
03Lv 9:7 Then Moses said to Aaron, "Approach the altar and sacrifice your sin offering and your burnt offering; make atonement for yourself and the people. Sacrifice the people's offering and make atonement for them, as the LORD commanded."
03Lv 9:8 So Aaron approached the altar and slaughtered the calf as a sin offering for himself.
03Lv 9:9 Aaron's sons brought the blood to him, and he dipped his finger in the blood and applied it to the horns of the altar. He poured out the blood at the base of the altar.
03Lv 9:10 He burned the fat, the kidneys, and the fatty lobe of the liver from the sin offering on the altar, as the LORD had commanded Moses.
03Lv 9:11 He burned up the flesh and the hide outside the camp.
03Lv 9:12 Then he slaughtered the burnt offering. Aaron's sons brought him the blood, and he sprinkled it on all sides of the altar.
03Lv 9:13 They brought him the burnt offering piece by piece, along with the head, and he burned [them] on the altar.
03Lv 9:14 He washed the entrails and the shanks and burned them with the burnt offering on the altar.
03Lv 9:15 Aaron presented the people's offering. He took the male goat for the people's sin offering, slaughtered it, and made a sin offering with it as he did before.
03Lv 9:16 He presented the burnt offering and sacrificed it according to the regulation.
03Lv 9:17 Next he presented the grain offering, took a handful of it, and burned it on the altar in addition to the morning burnt offering.
03Lv 9:18 Finally, he slaughtered the ox and the ram as the people's fellowship sacrifice. Aaron's sons brought him the blood, and he sprinkled it on all sides of the altar.
03Lv 9:19 They also brought the fat portions from the ox and the ram-- the fat tail, the [fat] surrounding [the entrails], the kidneys, and the fatty lobe of the liver--
03Lv 9:20 and placed these on the breasts. Aaron burned the fat portions on the altar,
03Lv 9:21 but he waved the breasts and the right thigh as a presentation offering before the LORD, as Moses had commanded.
03Lv 9:22 Aaron lifted up his hands toward the people and blessed them. He came down after sacrificing the sin offering, the burnt offering, and the fellowship offering.
03Lv 9:23 Moses and Aaron then entered the tent of meeting. When they came out, they blessed the people, and the glory of the LORD appeared to all the people.
03Lv 9:24 Fire came out from the LORD and consumed the burnt offering and the fat portions on the altar. And when all the people saw it, they shouted and fell facedown [on the ground].
03Lv 10:1 Aaron's sons Nadab and Abihu each took his own firepan, put fire in it, placed incense on it, and presented unauthorized fire before the LORD, which He had not commanded them [to do].
03Lv 10:2 Then flames leaped from the LORD's presence and burned them to death before the LORD.
03Lv 10:3 So Moses said to Aaron, "This is what the LORD meant when He said: I will show My holiness to those who are near Me, and I will reveal My glory before all the people." But Aaron remained silent.
03Lv 10:4 Moses summoned Mishael and Elzaphan, sons of Aaron's uncle Uzziel, and said to them, "Come here and carry your relatives away from the front of the sanctuary to [a place] outside the camp."
03Lv 10:5 So they came forward and carried them in their tunics outside the camp, as Moses had said.
03Lv 10:6 Then Moses said to Aaron and his sons Eleazar and Ithamar, "Do not let your hair hang loose and do not tear your garments, or else you will die, and the LORD will become angry with the whole community. However, your brothers, the whole house of Israel, may mourn over that tragedy when the LORD sent the fire.
03Lv 10:7 You must not go outside the entrance to the tent of meeting or you will die, for the LORD's anointing oil is on you." So they did as Moses said.
03Lv 10:8 The LORD spoke to Aaron:
03Lv 10:9 "You and your sons are not to drink wine or beer when you enter the tent of meeting, or else you will die; this is a permanent statute throughout your generations.
03Lv 10:10 You must distinguish between the holy and the common, and the clean and the unclean,
03Lv 10:11 and teach the Israelites all the statutes that the LORD has given to them through Moses."
03Lv 10:12 Moses spoke to Aaron and his remaining sons, Eleazar and Ithamar: "Take the grain offering that is left over from the fire offerings to the LORD, and eat it prepared without yeast beside the altar, because it is especially holy.
03Lv 10:13 You must eat it in a holy place because it is your portion and your sons' from the fire offerings to the LORD, for this is what I was commanded.
03Lv 10:14 But you and your sons and your daughters may eat the breast of the presentation offering and the thigh of the contribution in any ceremonially clean place, because these portions have been assigned to you and your children from the Israelites' fellowship sacrifices.
03Lv 10:15 They are to bring the thigh of the contribution and the breast of the presentation offering, together with the offerings of fat portions made by fire, to wave as a presentation offering before the LORD. It will belong permanently to you and your children, as the LORD commanded."
03Lv 10:16 Later, Moses inquired about the male goat of the sin offering, but it had already been burned up. He was angry with Eleazar and Ithamar, Aaron's surviving sons, and asked,
03Lv 10:17 "Why didn't you eat the sin offering in the sanctuary area? For it is especially holy, and He has assigned it to you to take away the guilt of the community and make atonement for them before the LORD.
03Lv 10:18 Since its blood was not brought inside the sanctuary, you should have eaten it in the sanctuary [area], as I commanded."
03Lv 10:19 But Aaron replied to Moses, "See, today they presented their sin offering and their burnt offering before the LORD. Since these things have happened to me, if I had eaten the sin offering today, would it have been acceptable in the LORD's sight?"
03Lv 10:20 When Moses heard this, it was acceptable to him.
03Lv 11:1 The LORD spoke to Moses and Aaron:
03Lv 11:2 "Tell the Israelites: You may eat all these [kinds] of land animals.
03Lv 11:3 You may eat any animal with divided hooves and that chews the cud.
03Lv 11:4 But among the ones that chew the cud or have hooves you are not to eat [these]: the camel, though it chews the cud, does not have hooves-- it is unclean for you;
03Lv 11:5 the hyrax, though it chews the cud, does not have hooves-- it is unclean for you;
03Lv 11:6 the hare, though it chews the cud, does not have hooves-- it is unclean for you;
03Lv 11:7 the pig, though it has divided hooves, does not chew the cud-- it is unclean for you.
03Lv 11:8 Do not eat any of their meat or touch their carcasses-- they are unclean for you.
03Lv 11:9 "This [is what] you may eat from all that is in the water: You may eat everything in the water that has fins and scales, whether in the seas or streams.
03Lv 11:10 But these are to be detestable to you: everything that does not have fins and scales in the seas or streams, among all the swarming things and [other] living creatures in the water.
03Lv 11:11 They are to remain detestable to you; you must not eat any of their meat, and you must detest their carcasses.
03Lv 11:12 Everything in the water that does not have fins and scales will be detestable to you.
03Lv 11:13 "You are to detest these birds. They must not be eaten because they are detestable: the eagle, the bearded vulture, the black vulture,
03Lv 11:14 the kite, the various kinds of falcon,
03Lv 11:15 every kind of raven,
03Lv 11:16 the ostrich, the short-eared owl, the gull, the various kinds of hawk,
03Lv 11:17 the little owl, the cormorant, the long-eared owl,
03Lv 11:18 the white owl, the desert owl, the osprey,
03Lv 11:19 the stork, the various kinds of heron, the hoopoe, and the bat.
03Lv 11:20 "All winged insects that walk on all fours are to be detestable to you.
03Lv 11:21 But you may eat these kinds of all the winged insects that walk on all fours: those that have jointed legs above their feet for hopping on the ground.
03Lv 11:22 You may eat these: the various kinds of locust, the various kinds of katydid, the various kinds of cricket, and the various kinds of grasshopper.
03Lv 11:23 All [other] winged insects that have four feet are to be detestable to you.
03Lv 11:24 "These will make you unclean. Whoever touches their carcasses will be unclean until evening,
03Lv 11:25 and whoever carries any of their carcasses must wash his clothes and will be unclean until evening.
03Lv 11:26 All animals that have hooves but do not have a divided hoof and do not chew the cud are unclean for you. Whoever touches them becomes unclean.
03Lv 11:27 All the four-footed animals that walk on their paws are unclean for you. Whoever touches their carcasses will be unclean until evening,
03Lv 11:28 and anyone who carries their carcasses must wash his clothes and will be unclean until evening. They are unclean for you.
03Lv 11:29 "These creatures that swarm on the ground are unclean for you: the weasel, the mouse, the various kinds of large lizard,
03Lv 11:30 the gecko, the monitor lizard, the common lizard, the skink, and the chameleon.
03Lv 11:31 These are unclean for you among all the swarming creatures. Whoever touches them when they are dead will be unclean until evening.
03Lv 11:32 When any one of them dies and falls on anything it becomes unclean-- any item of wood, clothing, leather, sackcloth, or any implement used for work. It is to be rinsed with water and will remain unclean until evening; then it will be clean.
03Lv 11:33 If any of them falls into any clay pot, everything in it will become unclean; you must break it.
03Lv 11:34 Any edible food coming into contact with [that unclean] water will become unclean, and any drinkable liquid in any container will become unclean.
03Lv 11:35 Anything one of their carcasses falls on will become unclean. If it is an oven or stove, it must be smashed; it is unclean and will remain unclean for you.
03Lv 11:36 A spring or cistern containing water will remain clean, but someone who touches a carcass [in it] will become unclean.
03Lv 11:37 If one of their carcasses falls on any seed that is to be sown, it is clean;
03Lv 11:38 but if water has been put on the seed and one of their carcasses falls on it, it is unclean for you.
03Lv 11:39 "If one of the animals that you use for food dies, anyone who touches its carcass will be unclean until evening.
03Lv 11:40 Anyone who eats some of its carcass must wash his clothes and will be unclean until evening. Anyone who carries its carcass must wash his clothes and will be unclean until evening.
03Lv 11:41 "All the creatures that swarm on the earth are detestable; they must not be eaten.
03Lv 11:42 Do not eat any of the creatures that swarm on the earth, anything that moves on its belly or walks on all fours or on many feet, for they are detestable.
03Lv 11:43 Do not become contaminated by any creature that swarms; do not become unclean or defiled by them.
03Lv 11:44 For I am the LORD your God, so you must consecrate yourselves and be holy because I am holy. You must not defile yourselves by any swarming creature that crawls on the ground.
03Lv 11:45 For I am the Lord, who brought you up from the land of Egypt to be your God, so you must be holy because I am holy.
03Lv 11:46 "This is the law concerning animals, birds, all living creatures that move in the water, and all creatures that swarm on the ground,
03Lv 11:47 in order to distinguish between the unclean and the clean, between the animals that may be eaten and those that may not be eaten."
03Lv 12:1 The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 12:2 "Tell the Israelites: When a woman becomes pregnant and gives birth to a male child, she will be unclean seven days, as she is during the days of her menstrual impurity.
03Lv 12:3 The flesh of his foreskin must be circumcised on the eighth day.
03Lv 12:4 She will continue in purification from her bleeding for 33 days. She must not touch any holy thing or go into the sanctuary until completing her days of purification.
03Lv 12:5 But if she gives birth to a female child, she will be unclean for two weeks as [she is] during her [menstrual] impurity. She will continue in purification from her bleeding for 66 days.
03Lv 12:6 "When her days of purification are complete, whether for a son or daughter, she is to bring to the priest at the entrance to the tent of meeting a year-old male lamb for a burnt offering, and a young pigeon or a turtledove for a sin offering.
03Lv 12:7 He will present them before the LORD and make atonement on her behalf; she will be clean from her discharge of blood. This is the law for a woman giving birth, whether to a male or female.
03Lv 12:8 But if she doesn't have sufficient means for a sheep, she may take two turtledoves or two young pigeons, one for a burnt offering and the other for a sin offering. Then the priest will make atonement on her behalf, and she will be clean."
03Lv 13:1 The LORD spoke to Moses and Aaron:
03Lv 13:2 "When a person has a swelling, scab, or spot on the skin of his body, and it becomes a disease on the skin of his body, he is to be brought to Aaron the priest or to one of his sons, the priests.
03Lv 13:3 The priest will examine the infection on the skin of his body. If the hair in the infection has turned white and the infection appears to be deeper than the skin of his body, it is a skin disease. After the priest examines him, he must pronounce him unclean.
03Lv 13:4 But if the spot on the skin of his body is white and does not appear to be deeper than the skin, and the hair in it has not turned white, the priest must quarantine the infected person for seven days.
03Lv 13:5 The priest will then reexamine him on the seventh day. If the infection remains unchanged in his sight and has not spread on the skin, the priest must quarantine him for another seven days.
03Lv 13:6 The priest will examine him again on the seventh day. If the infection has faded and has not spread on the skin, the priest is to pronounce him clean; it is a scab. The person is to wash his clothes and will become clean.
03Lv 13:7 But if the scab spreads further on his skin after he has presented himself to the priest for his cleansing, he must present himself again to the priest.
03Lv 13:8 The priest will examine him, and if the scab has spread on the skin, then the priest must pronounce him unclean; he has a skin disease.
03Lv 13:9 "When a skin disease develops on a person, he is to be brought to the priest.
03Lv 13:10 The priest will examine him. If there is a white swelling on the skin that has turned the hair white, and there is a patch of raw flesh in the swelling,
03Lv 13:11 it is a chronic disease on the skin of his body, and the priest must pronounce him unclean. He need not quarantine him, for he is unclean.
03Lv 13:12 But if the skin disease breaks out completely over the skin so that it covers all the skin of the infected person from his head to his feet so far as the priest can see,
03Lv 13:13 the priest will look, and if the skin disease has covered his entire body, he is to pronounce the infected person clean. Since he has turned totally white, he is clean.
03Lv 13:14 But whenever raw flesh appears on him, he will be unclean.
03Lv 13:15 When the priest examines the raw flesh, he must pronounce him unclean. Raw flesh is unclean; it is a skin disease.
03Lv 13:16 But if the raw flesh changes and turns white, he must go to the priest.
03Lv 13:17 The priest will examine him, and if the infection has turned white, the priest must pronounce the infected person clean; he is clean.
03Lv 13:18 "When a boil appears on the skin of one's body and it heals,
03Lv 13:19 and a white swelling or a reddish-white spot develops where the boil was, the person must present himself to the priest.
03Lv 13:20 The priest will make an examination, and if the spot seems to be beneath the skin and the hair in it has turned white, the priest must pronounce him unclean; it is a skin disease that has broken out in the boil.
03Lv 13:21 But when the priest examines it, if there is no white hair in it, and it is not beneath the skin but is faded, the priest must quarantine him seven days.
03Lv 13:22 If it spreads further on the skin, the priest must pronounce him unclean; it is an infection.
03Lv 13:23 But if the spot remains where it is and does not spread, it is [only] the scar from the boil. The priest is to pronounce him clean.
03Lv 13:24 "When there is a burn on the skin of one's body produced by fire, and the patch made raw by the burn becomes a reddish-white or white spot,
03Lv 13:25 the priest is to examine it. If the hair in the spot has turned white and the spot appears to be deeper than the skin, it is a skin disease that has broken out in the burn. The priest must pronounce him unclean; it is a skin disease.
03Lv 13:26 But when the priest examines it, if there is no white hair in the spot and it is not beneath the skin but is faded, the priest must quarantine him seven days.
03Lv 13:27 The priest will reexamine him on the seventh day. If it has spread further on the skin, the priest must pronounce him unclean; it is a skin disease.
03Lv 13:28 But if the spot has remained where it was and has not spread on the skin but is faded, it is the swelling from the burn. The priest is to pronounce him clean, for it is [only] the scar from the burn.
03Lv 13:29 "When a man or woman has an infection on the head or chin,
03Lv 13:30 the priest must examine the infection. If it appears to be deeper than the skin, and the hair in it is yellow and sparse, the priest must pronounce the person unclean. It is a scaly outbreak, a skin disease of the head or chin.
03Lv 13:31 When the priest examines the scaly infection, if it does not appear to be deeper than the skin, and there is no black hair in it, the priest must quarantine the person with the scaly infection for seven days.
03Lv 13:32 The priest will reexamine the infection on the seventh day. If the scaly outbreak has not spread and there is no yellow hair in it and it does not appear to be deeper than the skin,
03Lv 13:33 the person must shave himself but not shave the scaly area. Then the priest must quarantine the person who has the scaly outbreak for another seven days.
03Lv 13:34 The priest will examine the scaly outbreak on the seventh day, and if it has not spread on the skin and does not appear to be deeper than the skin, the priest is to pronounce the person clean. He is to wash his clothes, and he will be clean.
03Lv 13:35 But if the scaly outbreak spreads further on the skin after his cleansing,
03Lv 13:36 the priest is to examine the person. If the scaly outbreak has spread on the skin, the priest does not need to look for yellow hair; the person is unclean.
03Lv 13:37 But if as far as he can see, the scaly outbreak remains unchanged and black hair has grown in it, then it has healed; he is clean. The priest is to pronounce the person clean.
03Lv 13:38 "When a man or a woman has white spots on the skin of the body,
03Lv 13:39 the priest is to make an examination. If the spots on the skin of the body are dull white, it is [only] a rash that has broken out on the skin; the person is clean.
03Lv 13:40 "If a man loses the hair of his head, he is bald, but he is clean.
03Lv 13:41 Or if he loses the hair at his hairline, he is bald on his forehead, but he is clean.
03Lv 13:42 But if there is a reddish-white infection on the bald head or forehead, it is a skin disease breaking out on his head or forehead.
03Lv 13:43 The priest is to examine him, and if the swelling of the infection on his bald head or forehead is reddish-white, like the appearance of a skin disease on his body,
03Lv 13:44 the man is afflicted with a skin disease; he is unclean. The priest must pronounce him unclean; the infection is on his head.
03Lv 13:45 "The person afflicted with an infectious skin disease is to have his clothes torn and his hair hanging loose, and he must cover his mouth and cry out, 'Unclean, unclean!'
03Lv 13:46 He will remain unclean as long as he has the infection; he is unclean. He must live alone in a place outside the camp.
03Lv 13:47 "If a fabric is contaminated with mildew-- in wool or linen fabric,
03Lv 13:48 in the warp or woof of linen or wool, or in leather or anything made of leather--
03Lv 13:49 and if the contamination is green or red in the fabric, the leather, the warp, the woof, or any leather article, it is a mildew contamination and is to be shown to the priest.
03Lv 13:50 The priest is to examine the contamination and quarantine the contaminated fabric for seven days.
03Lv 13:51 The priest is to reexamine the contamination on the seventh day. If it has spread in the fabric, the warp, the woof, or the leather, regardless of how it is used, the contamination is harmful mildew; it is unclean.
03Lv 13:52 He is to burn the fabric, the warp or woof in wool or linen, or any leather article, which is contaminated. Since it is harmful mildew it must be burned up.
03Lv 13:53 "When the priest examines [it], if the contamination has not spread in the fabric, the warp or woof, or any leather article,
03Lv 13:54 the priest is to order whatever is contaminated to be washed and quarantined for another seven days.
03Lv 13:55 After it has been washed, the priest is to reexamine the contamination. If the appearance of the contaminated article has not changed, it is unclean. Even though the contamination has not spread, you must burn up the fabric. It is a fungus on the front or back [of the fabric].
03Lv 13:56 "If the priest examines [it], and the contamination has faded after it has been washed, he must cut the contaminated section out of the fabric, the leather, or the warp or woof.
03Lv 13:57 But if it reappears in the fabric, the warp or woof, or any leather article, it has broken out again. You must burn up whatever is contaminated.
03Lv 13:58 But if the contamination disappears from the fabric, the warp or woof, or any leather article, which have been washed, it is to be washed again, and it will be clean.
03Lv 13:59 "This is the law concerning a mildew contamination in wool or linen fabric, warp or woof, or any leather article, in order to pronounce it clean or unclean."
03Lv 14:1 The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 14:2 "This is the law concerning the person afflicted with a skin disease on the day of his cleansing. He is to be brought to the priest,
03Lv 14:3 who will go outside the camp and examine [him]. If the skin disease has disappeared from the afflicted person,
03Lv 14:4 the priest will order that two live clean birds, cedar wood, scarlet yarn, and hyssop be brought for the one who is to be cleansed.
03Lv 14:5 Then the priest will order that one of the birds be slaughtered over fresh water in a clay pot.
03Lv 14:6 He is to take the live bird together with the cedar wood, scarlet yarn, and hyssop, and dip them all into the blood of the bird that was slaughtered over the fresh water.
03Lv 14:7 He will then sprinkle [the blood] seven times on the one who is to be cleansed from the skin disease. He is to pronounce him clean and release the live bird over the open countryside.
03Lv 14:8 The one who is to be cleansed must wash his clothes, shave off all his hair, and bathe with water; he is clean. Afterwards he may enter the camp, but he must remain outside his tent for seven days.
03Lv 14:9 He is to shave off all his hair [again] on the seventh day: his head, his beard, his eyebrows, and the rest of his hair. He is to wash his clothes and bathe himself with water; he is clean.
03Lv 14:10 "On the eighth day he must take two unblemished male lambs, an unblemished year-old ewe lamb, a grain offering of three quarts of fine flour mixed with olive oil, and one-third of a quart of olive oil.
03Lv 14:11 The priest who performs the cleansing will place the person who is to be cleansed, together with these offerings, before the LORD at the entrance to the tent of meeting.
03Lv 14:12 The priest is to take one male lamb and present it as a restitution offering, along with the one-third quart of olive oil, and he must wave them as a presentation offering before the LORD.
03Lv 14:13 He is to slaughter the male lamb at the place in the sanctuary area where the sin offering and burnt offering are slaughtered, for like the sin offering, the restitution offering belongs to the priest; it is especially holy.
03Lv 14:14 The priest is to take some of the blood from the restitution offering and put [it] on the lobe of the right ear of the one to be cleansed, on the thumb of his right hand, and on the big toe of his right foot.
03Lv 14:15 Then the priest will take some of the one-third of a quart of olive oil and pour it into his left palm.
03Lv 14:16 The priest will dip his right finger into the oil in his left palm and sprinkle some of the oil with his finger seven times before the LORD.
03Lv 14:17 From the oil remaining in his palm the priest will put some on the lobe of the right ear of the one to be cleansed, on the thumb of his right hand, and on the big toe of his right foot, on top of the blood of the restitution offering.
03Lv 14:18 What is left of the oil in the priest's palm he is to put on the head of the one to be cleansed. In this way the priest will make atonement for him before the LORD.
03Lv 14:19 The priest must sacrifice the sin offering and make atonement for the one to be purified from his uncleanness. Afterwards he will slaughter the burnt offering.
03Lv 14:20 The priest is to offer the burnt offering and the grain offering on the altar. The priest will make atonement for him, and he will be clean.
03Lv 14:21 "But if he is poor and cannot afford [these], he is to take one male lamb for a restitution offering to be waved in order to make atonement for him, along with two quarts of fine flour mixed with olive oil for a grain offering, one-third of a quart of olive oil,
03Lv 14:22 and two turtledoves or two young pigeons, whatever he can afford, one to be a sin offering and the other a burnt offering.
03Lv 14:23 On the eighth day he is to bring these things for his cleansing to the priest at the entrance to the tent of meeting before the LORD.
03Lv 14:24 The priest will take the male lamb for the restitution offering and the one-third of a quart of olive oil, and wave them as a presentation offering before the LORD.
03Lv 14:25 After he slaughters the male lamb for the restitution offering, the priest is to take some of the blood of the restitution offering and put [it] on the right earlobe of the one to be cleansed, on the thumb of his right hand, and on the big toe of his right foot.
03Lv 14:26 Then the priest will pour some of the oil into his left palm.
03Lv 14:27 With his right finger the priest will sprinkle some of the oil in his left palm seven times before the LORD.
03Lv 14:28 The priest will also put some of the oil in his palm on the right earlobe of the one to be cleansed, on the thumb of his right hand, and on the big toe of his right foot, on the [same] place as the blood of the restitution offering.
03Lv 14:29 What is left of the oil in the priest's palm he is to put on the head of the one to be cleansed to make atonement for him before the LORD.
03Lv 14:30 He must then sacrifice one type of what he can afford, either the turtledoves or young pigeons,
03Lv 14:31 one as a sin offering and the other as a burnt offering, [sacrificing] what he can afford together with the grain offering. In this way the priest will make atonement before the LORD for the one to be cleansed.
03Lv 14:32 This is the law for someone who has a skin disease and cannot afford the cost of his cleansing."
03Lv 14:33 The LORD spoke to Moses and Aaron:
03Lv 14:34 "When you enter the land of Canaan that I am giving you as a possession, and I place a mildew contamination in a house in the land you possess,
03Lv 14:35 the owner of the house is to come and tell the priest: Something like mildew contamination has appeared in my house.
03Lv 14:36 The priest must order them to clear the house before he enters to examine the contamination, so that nothing in the house becomes unclean. Afterwards the priest will come to examine the house.
03Lv 14:37 He will examine it, and if the contamination in the walls of the house consists of green or red indentations that appear to be beneath the surface of the wall,
03Lv 14:38 the priest is to go outside the house to its doorway and quarantine the house for seven days.
03Lv 14:39 The priest is to return on the seventh day and examine it. If the contamination has spread on the walls of the house,
03Lv 14:40 the priest must order that the stones with the contamination be pulled out and thrown into an unclean place outside the city.
03Lv 14:41 He is to have the inside of the house completely scraped, and the plaster that is scraped off must be dumped in an unclean place outside the city.
03Lv 14:42 Then they must take different stones to replace the [former] ones and take additional plaster to replaster the house.
03Lv 14:43 "If the contamination reappears in the house after the stones have been pulled out, and after the house has been scraped and replastered,
03Lv 14:44 the priest must come and examine it. If the contamination has spread in the house, it is harmful mildew; the house is unclean.
03Lv 14:45 It must be torn down with its stones, its beams, and all its plaster, and taken outside the city to an unclean place.
03Lv 14:46 Whoever enters the house during any of the days the priest quarantines it will be unclean until evening.
03Lv 14:47 Whoever lies down in the house is to wash his clothes, and whoever eats in it is to wash his clothes.
03Lv 14:48 "But when the priest comes and examines it, if the contamination has not spread in the house after it was replastered, he is to pronounce the house clean because the contamination has disappeared.
03Lv 14:49 He is to take two birds, cedar wood, scarlet yarn, and hyssop to purify the house,
03Lv 14:50 and he is to slaughter one of the birds over a clay pot containing fresh water.
03Lv 14:51 He will take the cedar wood, the hyssop, the scarlet yarn, and the live bird, dip them in the blood of the slaughtered bird and the fresh water, and sprinkle the house seven times.
03Lv 14:52 He will purify the house with the blood of the bird, the fresh water, the live bird, the cedar wood, the hyssop, and the scarlet yarn.
03Lv 14:53 Then he is to release the live bird into the open countryside outside the city. In this way he will make atonement for the house, and it will be clean.
03Lv 14:54 "This is the law for any skin disease or mildew, for a scaly outbreak,
03Lv 14:55 for mildew in clothing or on a house,
03Lv 14:56 and for a swelling, scab, or spot,
03Lv 14:57 to determine when something is unclean or clean. This is the law regarding skin disease and mildew."
03Lv 15:1 The LORD spoke to Moses and Aaron:
03Lv 15:2 "Speak to the Israelites and tell them: When any man has a discharge from his body, he is unclean.
03Lv 15:3 This is uncleanness of his discharge: Whether his body secretes the discharge or retains it, he is unclean. All the days that his body secretes or retains anything because of his discharge, he is unclean.
03Lv 15:4 Any bed the man with the discharge lies on will be unclean, and any furniture he sits on will be unclean.
03Lv 15:5 Anyone who touches his bed is to wash his clothes and bathe with water, and he will remain unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:6 Whoever sits on furniture that the man with the discharge was sitting on is to wash his clothes and bathe with water, and he will remain unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:7 Whoever touches the body of the man with a discharge is to wash his clothes and bathe with water, and he will remain unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:8 If the man with the discharge spits on anyone who is clean, he is to wash his clothes and bathe with water, and he will remain unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:9 Any saddle the man with the discharge rides on will be unclean.
03Lv 15:10 Whoever touches anything that was under him will be unclean until evening, and whoever carries such things is to wash his clothes and bathe with water, and he will remain unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:11 If the man with the discharge touches anyone without [first] rinsing his hands in water, the person who was touched is to wash his clothes and bathe with water, and he will remain unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:12 Any clay pot that the man with the discharge touches must be broken, while any wooden utensil must be rinsed with water.
03Lv 15:13 "When the man with the discharge has been cured of it, he is to count seven days for his cleansing, wash his clothes, and bathe his body in fresh water; he will be clean.
03Lv 15:14 He must take two turtledoves or two young pigeons on the eighth day, come before the LORD at the entrance to the tent of meeting, and give them to the priest.
03Lv 15:15 The priest is to sacrifice them, one as a sin offering and the other as a burnt offering. In this way the priest will make atonement for him before the LORD because of his discharge.
03Lv 15:16 "When a man has an emission of semen, he is to bathe himself completely with water, and he will remain unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:17 Any clothing or leather on which there is an emission of semen must be washed with water, and it will remain unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:18 If a man sleeps with a woman and has an emission of semen, both of them are to bathe with water, and they will remain unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:19 "When a woman has a discharge, and it consists of blood from her body, she will be unclean because of her menstruation for seven days. Everyone who touches her will be unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:20 Anything she lies on during her menstruation will become unclean, and anything she sits on will become unclean.
03Lv 15:21 Everyone who touches her bed is to wash his clothes and bathe with water, and he will remain unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:22 Everyone who touches any furniture she was sitting on is to wash his clothes and bathe with water, and he will remain unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:23 If discharge is on the bed or the furniture she was sitting on, when he touches it he will be unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:24 If a man sleeps with her, and [blood from] her menstruation gets on him, he will be unclean for seven days, and every bed he lies on will become unclean.
03Lv 15:25 "When a woman has a discharge of her blood for many days, though it is not the time of her menstruation, or if she has a discharge beyond her period, she will be unclean all the days of her unclean discharge, as [she is] during the days of her menstruation.
03Lv 15:26 Any bed she lies on during the days of her discharge will be like her bed during menstrual impurity; any furniture she sits on will be unclean as in her menstrual period.
03Lv 15:27 Everyone who touches them will be unclean; he must wash his clothes and bathe with water, and he will remain unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:28 When she is cured of her discharge, she is to count seven days, and after that she will be clean.
03Lv 15:29 On the eighth day she must take two turtledoves or two young pigeons and bring them to the priest at the entrance to the tent of meeting.
03Lv 15:30 The priest is to sacrifice one as a sin offering and the other as a burnt offering. In this way the priest will make atonement for her before the LORD because of her unclean discharge.
03Lv 15:31 "You must keep the Israelites from their uncleanness, so that they do not die by defiling My tabernacle that is among them.
03Lv 15:32 This is the law for someone with a discharge: a man who has an emission of semen, becoming unclean by it;
03Lv 15:33 a woman who is in her menstrual period; anyone who has a discharge, whether male or female; and a man who sleeps with an unclean woman."
03Lv 16:1 The LORD spoke to Moses after the death of two of Aaron's sons when they approached the presence of the LORD and died.
03Lv 16:2 The LORD said to Moses: "Tell your brother Aaron that he may not come whenever he wants into the holy place behind the veil in front of the mercy seat on the ark or else he will die, because I appear in the cloud above the mercy seat.
03Lv 16:3 "Aaron is to enter the [most] holy place in this way: with a young bull for a sin offering and a ram for a burnt offering.
03Lv 16:4 He is to wear a holy linen tunic, and linen undergarments are to be on his body. He must tie a linen sash [around him] and wrap his head with a linen turban. These are holy garments; he must bathe his body with water before he wears them.
03Lv 16:5 He is to take from the Israelite community two male goats for a sin offering and one ram for a burnt offering.
03Lv 16:6 "Aaron will present the bull for his sin offering and make atonement for himself and his household.
03Lv 16:7 Next he will take the two goats and place them before the LORD at the entrance to the tent of meeting.
03Lv 16:8 After Aaron casts lots for the two goats, one lot for the LORD and the other for Azazel,
03Lv 16:9 he is to present the goat chosen by lot for the LORD and sacrifice it as a sin offering.
03Lv 16:10 But the goat chosen by lot for Azazel is to be presented alive before the LORD to make purification with it by sending it into the wilderness for Azazel.
03Lv 16:11 "When Aaron presents the bull for his sin offering and makes atonement for himself and his household, he will slaughter the bull for his sin offering.
03Lv 16:12 Then he must take a firepan full of fiery coals from the altar before the LORD and two handfuls of finely ground fragrant incense, and bring [them] inside the veil.
03Lv 16:13 He is to put the incense on the fire before the LORD, so that the cloud of incense covers the mercy seat that is over the testimony, or else he will die.
03Lv 16:14 He is to take some of the bull's blood and sprinkle [it] with his finger against the east side of the mercy seat; then he will sprinkle some of the blood with his finger before the mercy seat seven times.
03Lv 16:15 "When he slaughters the male goat for the people's sin offering and brings its blood inside the veil, he must do the same with its blood as he did with the bull's blood: he is to sprinkle it against the mercy seat and in front of it.
03Lv 16:16 He will purify the [most] holy place in this way for all their sins because of the Israelites' impurities and rebellious acts. He will do the same for the tent of meeting that remains among them, because it is surrounded by their impurities.
03Lv 16:17 No one may be in the tent of meeting from the time he enters to make atonement in the [most] holy place until he leaves after he has made atonement for himself, his household, and the whole assembly of Israel.
03Lv 16:18 Then he will go out to the altar that is before the LORD and make atonement for it. He is to take some of the bull's blood and some of the goat's blood and put [it] on the horns on all sides of the altar.
03Lv 16:19 He is to sprinkle some of the blood on it with his finger seven times to cleanse and set it apart from the Israelites' impurities.
03Lv 16:20 "When he has finished purifying the [most] holy place, the tent of meeting, and the altar, he is to present the live male goat.
03Lv 16:21 Aaron will lay both his hands on the head of the live goat and confess over it all the Israelites' wrongdoings and rebellious acts-- all their sins. He is to put them on the goat's head and send [it] away into the wilderness by the man appointed for the task.
03Lv 16:22 The goat will carry on it all their wrongdoings into a desolate land, and he will release it there.
03Lv 16:23 "Then Aaron is to enter the tent of meeting, take off the linen garments he wore when he entered the [most] holy place, and leave them there.
03Lv 16:24 He will bathe his body with water in a holy place and put on his clothes. Then he must go out and sacrifice his burnt offering and the people's burnt offering; he will make atonement for himself and for the people.
03Lv 16:25 He is to burn the fat of the sin offering on the altar.
03Lv 16:26 The man who released the goat for Azazel is to wash his clothes and bathe his body with water; afterwards he may reenter the camp.
03Lv 16:27 The bull for the sin offering and the goat for the sin offering, whose blood was brought into the [most] holy place to make atonement, must be brought outside the camp and their hide, flesh, and dung burned up.
03Lv 16:28 The one who burns them is to wash his clothes and bathe himself with water; afterwards he may reenter the camp.
03Lv 16:29 "This is to be a permanent statute for you: In the seventh month, on the tenth [day] of the month you are to practice self-denial and do no work, both the native and the foreigner who resides among you.
03Lv 16:30 Atonement will be made for you on this day to cleanse you, and you will be clean from all your sins before the LORD.
03Lv 16:31 It is a Sabbath of complete rest for you, and you must practice self-denial; it is a permanent statute.
03Lv 16:32 The priest who is anointed and ordained to serve as [high] priest in place of his father will make atonement. He will put on the linen garments, the holy garments,
03Lv 16:33 and purify the most holy place. He will purify the tent of meeting and the altar and will make atonement for the priests and all the people of the assembly.
03Lv 16:34 This is to be a permanent statute for you, to make atonement for the Israelites once a year because of all their sins." And all this was done as the LORD commanded Moses.
03Lv 17:1 The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 17:2 "Speak to Aaron, his sons, and all the Israelites and tell them: This is what the LORD has commanded:
03Lv 17:3 Anyone from the house of Israel who slaughters an ox, sheep, or goat in the camp, or slaughters [it] outside the camp,
03Lv 17:4 instead of bringing it to the entrance to the tent of meeting to present [it] as an offering to the LORD before His tabernacle-- that person will be charged with murder. He has shed blood and must be cut off from his people.
03Lv 17:5 This is so the Israelites will bring to the LORD the sacrifices they have been offering in the open country. They are to bring them to the priest at the entrance to the tent of meeting and offer them as fellowship sacrifices to the LORD.
03Lv 17:6 The priest will then sprinkle the blood on the LORD's altar at the entrance to the tent of meeting and burn the fat as a pleasing aroma to the LORD.
03Lv 17:7 They must no longer offer their sacrifices to the goat-demons that they have prostituted themselves with. This will be a permanent statute for them throughout their generations.
03Lv 17:8 "Say to them: Anyone from the house of Israel or from the foreigners who live among them who offers a burnt offering or a sacrifice
03Lv 17:9 but does not bring it to the entrance to the tent of meeting to sacrifice it to the LORD, that person must be cut off from his people.
03Lv 17:10 "Anyone from the house of Israel or from the foreigners who live among them who eats any blood, I will turn against that person who eats blood and cut him off from his people.
03Lv 17:11 For the life of a creature is in the blood, and I have appointed it to you to make atonement on the altar for your lives, since it is the lifeblood that makes atonement.
03Lv 17:12 Therefore I say to the Israelites: None of you and no foreigner who lives among you may eat blood.
03Lv 17:13 "Any Israelite or foreigner living among them, who hunts down a wild animal or bird that may be eaten must drain its blood and cover it with dirt.
03Lv 17:14 Since the life of every creature is its blood, I have told the Israelites: You must not eat the blood of any creature, because the life of every creature is its blood; whoever eats it must be cut off.
03Lv 17:15 "Every person, whether the native or the foreigner, who eats an animal that died a natural death or was mauled by wild beasts is to wash his clothes and bathe with water, and he will remain unclean until evening; he will be clean.
03Lv 17:16 But if he does not wash [his clothes] and bathe himself, he will bear his punishment."
03Lv 18:1 The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 18:2 "Speak to the Israelites and tell them: I am the LORD your God.
03Lv 18:3 Do not follow the practices of the land of Egypt, where you used to live, or follow the practices of the land of Canaan, where I am bringing you. You must not follow their customs.
03Lv 18:4 You are to practice My ordinances and you are to keep My statutes by following them; I am the LORD your God.
03Lv 18:5 Keep My statutes and ordinances; a person will live if he does them. I am the LORD.
03Lv 18:6 "You are not to come near any close relative for sexual intercourse; I am the LORD.
03Lv 18:7 You are not to shame your father by having sex with your mother. She is your mother; you must not have sexual intercourse with her.
03Lv 18:8 You are not to have sex with your father's wife; it will shame your father.
03Lv 18:9 You are not to have sexual intercourse with your sister, either your father's daughter or your mother's, whether born at home or born elsewhere. You are not to have sex with her.
03Lv 18:10 You are not to have sexual intercourse with your son's daughter or your daughter's daughter, because it will shame your family.
03Lv 18:11 You are not to have sexual intercourse with your father's wife's daughter, who is adopted by your father; she is your sister.
03Lv 18:12 You are not to have sexual intercourse with your father's sister; she is your father's close relative.
03Lv 18:13 You are not to have sexual intercourse with your mother's sister, for she is your mother's close relative.
03Lv 18:14 You are not to shame your father's brother by coming near his wife to have sexual intercourse; she is your aunt.
03Lv 18:15 You are not to have sexual intercourse with your daughter-in-law. She is your son's wife; you are not to have sex with her.
03Lv 18:16 You are not to have sexual intercourse with your brother's wife; it will shame your brother.
03Lv 18:17 You are not to have sexual intercourse with a woman and her daughter. You are not to marry her son's daughter or her daughter's daughter and have sex with her. They are close relatives; it is depraved.
03Lv 18:18 You are not to marry a woman as a rival to her sister and have sexual intercourse with her during her [sister's] lifetime.
03Lv 18:19 "You are not to come near a woman during her menstrual impurity to have sexual intercourse with her.
03Lv 18:20 You are not to have sexual intercourse with your neighbor's wife, defiling yourself with her.
03Lv 18:21 "You are not to make any of your children pass through [the fire] to Molech. Do not profane the name of your God; I am the LORD.
03Lv 18:22 You are not to sleep with a man as with a woman; it is detestable.
03Lv 18:23 You are not to have sexual intercourse with any animal, defiling yourself with it; a woman is not to present herself to an animal to mate with it; it is a perversion.
03Lv 18:24 "Do not defile yourselves by any of these [practices], for the nations I am driving out before you have defiled themselves by all these things.
03Lv 18:25 The land has become defiled, so I am punishing it for its sin, and the land will vomit out its inhabitants.
03Lv 18:26 But you are to keep My statutes and ordinances. You must not commit any of these abominations-- not the native or the foreigner who lives among you.
03Lv 18:27 For the men who were in the land prior to you have committed all these abominations, and the land has become defiled.
03Lv 18:28 If you defile the land, it will vomit you out as it has vomited out the nations that were before you.
03Lv 18:29 Any person who does any of these abominations must be cut off from his people.
03Lv 18:30 You must keep My instruction to not do any of the detestable customs that were practiced before you, so that you do not defile yourselves by them; I am the LORD your God."
03Lv 19:1 The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 19:2 "Speak to the entire Israelite community and tell them: Be holy because I, the LORD your God, am holy.
03Lv 19:3 "Each of you is to respect his mother and father. You are to keep My Sabbaths; I am the LORD your God.
03Lv 19:4 Do not turn to idols or make cast images of gods for yourselves; I am the LORD your God.
03Lv 19:5 "When you offer a fellowship sacrifice to the LORD, sacrifice it that you may be accepted.
03Lv 19:6 It is to be eaten on the day you sacrifice [it] or on the next day, but what remains on the third day must be burned up.
03Lv 19:7 If any is eaten on the third day, it is a repulsive thing; it will not be accepted.
03Lv 19:8 Anyone who eats it will bear his punishment, for he has profaned what is holy to the LORD. That person must be cut off from his people.
03Lv 19:9 "When you reap the harvest of your land, you are not to reap to the very edge of your field or gather the gleanings of your harvest.
03Lv 19:10 You must not strip your vineyard bare or gather its fallen grapes. Leave them for the poor and the foreign resident; I am the LORD your God.
03Lv 19:11 "You must not steal. You must not act deceptively or lie to one another.
03Lv 19:12 You must not swear falsely by My name, profaning the name of your God; I am the LORD.
03Lv 19:13 "You must not oppress your neighbor or rob [him]. The wages due a hired hand must not remain with you until morning.
03Lv 19:14 You must not curse the deaf or put a stumbling block in front of the blind, but you are to fear your God; I am the LORD.
03Lv 19:15 "You must not act unjustly when rendering judgment. Do not be partial to the poor or give preference to the rich; judge your neighbor fairly.
03Lv 19:16 You must not go about spreading slander among your people; you must not jeopardize your neighbor's life; I am the LORD.
03Lv 19:17 "You must not hate your brother in your heart. Rebuke your neighbor directly, and you will not incur guilt because of him.
03Lv 19:18 Do not take revenge or bear a grudge against members of your community, but love your neighbor as yourself; I am the LORD.
03Lv 19:19 "You are to keep My statutes. You must not crossbreed two different kinds of your livestock, sow your fields with two kinds of seed, or put on a garment made of two kinds of material.
03Lv 19:20 "If a man has sexual intercourse with a woman who is a slave designated for [another] man, but she has not been redeemed or given her freedom, there must be punishment. They are not to be put to death, because she had not been freed.
03Lv 19:21 However, he must bring his ram as a restitution offering to the LORD at the entrance to the tent of meeting.
03Lv 19:22 The priest will make atonement on his behalf before the LORD with the ram of the restitution offering for the sin he has committed, and he will be forgiven for the sin he committed.
03Lv 19:23 "When you come into the land and plant any kind of tree for food, you are to consider the fruit forbidden. It will be forbidden to you for three years; it is not to be eaten.
03Lv 19:24 In the fourth year all its fruit must be consecrated as a praise offering to the LORD.
03Lv 19:25 But in the fifth year you may eat its fruit. In this way its yield will increase for you; I am the LORD your God.
03Lv 19:26 "You are not to eat [anything] with blood [in it]. You are not to practice divination or sorcery.
03Lv 19:27 You are not to cut off the hair at the sides of your head or mar the edge of your beard.
03Lv 19:28 You are not to make gashes on your bodies for the dead or put tattoo marks on yourselves; I am the LORD.
03Lv 19:29 "Do not debase your daughter by making her a prostitute, or the land will be prostituted and filled with depravity.
03Lv 19:30 You must keep My Sabbaths and revere My sanctuary; I am the LORD.
03Lv 19:31 "Do not turn to mediums or consult spiritists, or you will be defiled by them; I am the LORD your God.
03Lv 19:32 "You are to rise in the presence of the elderly and honor the old. Fear your God; I am the LORD.
03Lv 19:33 "When a foreigner lives with you in your land, you must not oppress him.
03Lv 19:34 You must regard the foreigner who lives with you as the native-born among you. You are to love him as yourself, for you were foreigners in the land of Egypt; I am the LORD your God.
03Lv 19:35 "You must not act unfairly in measurements of length, weight, or volume.
03Lv 19:36 You are to have honest balances, honest weights, an honest dry measure, and an honest liquid measure; I am the LORD your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt.
03Lv 19:37 You must keep all My statutes and all My ordinances and do them; I am the LORD."
03Lv 20:1 The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 20:2 "Say to the Israelites: Any Israelite or foreigner living in Israel who gives any of his children to Molech must be put to death; the people of the country are to stone him.
03Lv 20:3 I will turn against that man and cut him off from his people, because he gave his offspring to Molech, defiling My sanctuary and profaning My holy name.
03Lv 20:4 But if the people of the country look the other way when that man gives any of his children to Molech, and do not put him to death,
03Lv 20:5 then I will turn against that man and his family, and cut off from their people both him and all who follow him, prostituting themselves with Molech.
03Lv 20:6 "Whoever turns to mediums or spiritists and prostitutes himself with them, I will turn against that person and cut him off from his people.
03Lv 20:7 Consecrate yourselves and be holy, for I am the LORD your God.
03Lv 20:8 Keep My statutes and do them; I am the LORD who sets you apart.
03Lv 20:9 "If anyone curses his father or mother, he must be put to death. He has cursed his father or mother; his blood is on his own hands.
03Lv 20:10 If a man commits adultery with a married woman-- if he commits adultery with his neighbor's wife-- both the adulterer and the adulteress must be put to death.
03Lv 20:11 If a man sleeps with his father's wife, he has shamed his father. Both of them must be put to death; their blood is on their own hands.
03Lv 20:12 If a man sleeps with his daughter-in-law, both of them must be put to death. They have acted perversely; their blood is on their own hands.
03Lv 20:13 If a man sleeps with a man as with a woman, they have both committed an abomination. They must be put to death; their blood is on their own hands.
03Lv 20:14 If a man marries a woman and her mother, it is depraved. Both he and they must be burned with fire, so that there will be no depravity among you.
03Lv 20:15 If a man has sexual intercourse with an animal, he must be put to death; you are also to kill the animal.
03Lv 20:16 If a woman comes near any animal and mates with it, you are to kill the woman and the animal. They must be put to death; their [own] blood is on them.
03Lv 20:17 If a man marries his sister, whether his father's daughter or his mother's daughter, and they have sexual relations, it is a disgrace. They must be cut off publicly from their people. He has had sexual intercourse with his sister; he will bear his punishment.
03Lv 20:18 If a man sleeps with a menstruating woman and has sexual intercourse with her, he has exposed the source of her [flow], and she has uncovered the source of her blood. Both of them must be cut off from their people.
03Lv 20:19 You must not have sexual intercourse with your mother's sister or your father's sister, for it is exposing one's own blood relative; both people will bear their punishment.
03Lv 20:20 If a man sleeps with his aunt, he has shamed his uncle; they will bear their guilt and die childless.
03Lv 20:21 If a man marries his brother's wife, it is impurity. He has shamed his brother; they will be childless.
03Lv 20:22 "You are to keep all My statutes and all My ordinances, and do them, so that the land where I am bringing you to live will not vomit you out.
03Lv 20:23 You must not follow the statutes of the nations I am driving out before you, for they did all these things, and I abhorred them.
03Lv 20:24 And I promised you: You will inherit their land, since I will give it to you to possess, a land flowing with milk and honey. I am the LORD your God who set you apart from the peoples.
03Lv 20:25 Therefore you must distinguish the clean animal from the unclean one, and the unclean bird from the clean one. You are not to make yourselves detestable by any land animal, bird, or whatever crawls on the ground; I have set these apart as unclean for you.
03Lv 20:26 You are to be holy to Me because I, the LORD, am holy, and I have set you apart from the nations to be Mine.
03Lv 20:27 A man or a woman who is a medium or a spiritist must be put to death. They are to be stoned; their blood is on their own hands."
03Lv 21:1 The LORD said to Moses: "Speak to Aaron's sons, the priests, and tell them: A priest is not to make himself ceremonially unclean for a [dead] person among his relatives,
03Lv 21:2 except for his immediate family: his mother, father, son, daughter, or brother.
03Lv 21:3 He may make himself unclean for his young unmarried sister in his immediate family.
03Lv 21:4 He is not to make himself unclean for those related to him by marriage and so defile himself.
03Lv 21:5 "Priests may not make bald spots on their heads, shave the edge of their beards, or make gashes on their bodies.
03Lv 21:6 They are to be holy to their God and not profane the name of their God, because they present the fire offerings to the LORD, the food of their God. They must be holy.
03Lv 21:7 They are not to marry a woman defiled by prostitution or divorced by her husband, for the priest is holy to his God.
03Lv 21:8 You are to consider him holy since he presents the food of your God. He will be holy to you because I, the LORD who sets you apart, am holy.
03Lv 21:9 If a priest's daughter defiles herself by promiscuity, she defiles her father; she must be burned up.
03Lv 21:10 "The priest who is highest among his brothers, who has had the anointing oil poured on his head and has been ordained to wear the garments, must not dishevel his hair or tear his garments.
03Lv 21:11 He must not go near any dead person or make himself unclean [even] for his father or mother.
03Lv 21:12 He must not leave the sanctuary or he will desecrate the sanctuary of his God, for the consecration of the anointing oil of his God is on him; I am the LORD.
03Lv 21:13 "He is to marry a woman who is a virgin.
03Lv 21:14 He is not to marry a widow, a divorced woman, or one defiled by prostitution. He is to marry a virgin from his own people,
03Lv 21:15 so that he does not corrupt his bloodline among his people, for I am the LORD who sets him apart."
03Lv 21:16 The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 21:17 "Tell Aaron: None of your descendants throughout your generations who has a physical defect is to come near to present the food of his God.
03Lv 21:18 No man who has any defect is to come near: no man who is blind, lame, facially disfigured, or deformed;
03Lv 21:19 no man who has a broken foot or hand,
03Lv 21:20 or who is a hunchback or a dwarf, or who has an eye defect, a festering rash, scabs, or a crushed testicle.
03Lv 21:21 No descendant of Aaron the priest who has a defect is to come near to present the fire offerings to the LORD. He has a defect and is not to come near to present the food of his God.
03Lv 21:22 He may eat the food of his God from what is especially holy as well as from what is holy.
03Lv 21:23 But because he has a defect, he must not go near the curtain or approach the altar. He is not to desecrate My sanctuaries, for I am the LORD who sets them apart."
03Lv 21:24 Moses said [this] to Aaron and his sons and to all the Israelites.
03Lv 22:1 The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 22:2 "Tell Aaron and his sons to deal respectfully with the holy offerings of the Israelites that they have consecrated to Me, so they do not profane My holy name; I am the LORD.
03Lv 22:3 Say to them: If any man from any of your descendants throughout your generations is in a state of uncleanness yet approaches the holy offerings that the Israelites consecrate to the LORD, that person will be cut off from My presence; I am the LORD.
03Lv 22:4 No man of Aaron's descendants who has a skin disease or a discharge is to eat from the holy offerings until he is clean. Whoever touches anything made unclean by a dead person or by a man who has an emission of semen,
03Lv 22:5 or whoever touches any swarming creature that makes him unclean or any person who makes him unclean-- whatever his uncleanness--
03Lv 22:6 the man who touches any of these will remain unclean until evening and is not to eat from the holy offerings unless he has bathed his body with water.
03Lv 22:7 When the sun has set, he will become clean, and then he may eat from the holy offerings, for that is his food.
03Lv 22:8 He must not eat an animal that died naturally or was mauled by wild beasts, making himself unclean by it; I am the LORD.
03Lv 22:9 They must keep My instruction, or they will be guilty and die because they profane it; I am the LORD who sets them apart.
03Lv 22:10 "No one outside a priest's family is to eat the holy offering. A foreigner staying with a priest or a hired hand is not to eat the holy offering.
03Lv 22:11 But if a priest purchases someone with his money, that person may eat it, and those born in his house may eat his food.
03Lv 22:12 If the priest's daughter is married to a man outside a priest's family, she is not to eat from the holy contributions.
03Lv 22:13 But if the priest's daughter becomes widowed or divorced, has no children, and returns to her father's house as in her youth, she may share her father's food. But no outsider may share it.
03Lv 22:14 If anyone eats a holy offering in error, he must add a fifth to its value and give the holy offering to the priest.
03Lv 22:15 The priests must not profane the holy offerings the Israelites give to the LORD
03Lv 22:16 and have them bear the penalty of restitution if the people eat their holy offerings. For I am the LORD who sets them apart."
03Lv 22:17 The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 22:18 "Speak to Aaron, his sons, and all the Israelites and tell them: Any man of the house of Israel or of the foreign residents in Israel who presents his offering-- whether they present freewill gifts or payment of vows to the LORD as burnt offerings--
03Lv 22:19 must offer an unblemished male from the cattle, sheep, or goats in order for you to be accepted.
03Lv 22:20 You are not to present anything that has a defect, because it will not be accepted on your behalf.
03Lv 22:21 "When a man presents a fellowship sacrifice to the LORD to fulfill a vow or as a freewill offering from the herd or flock, it has to be unblemished to be acceptable; there must be no defect in it.
03Lv 22:22 You are not to present any [animal] to the LORD that is blind, injured, maimed, or has a running sore, festering rash, or scabs; you may not put any of them on the altar as a fire offering to the LORD.
03Lv 22:23 You may sacrifice as a freewill offering any animal from the herd or flock that has an elongated or stunted limb, but it is not acceptable as a vow offering.
03Lv 22:24 You are not to present to the LORD anything that has bruised, crushed, torn, or severed [testicles]; you must not sacrifice [them] in your land.
03Lv 22:25 Neither you nor a foreigner are to present food to your God from any of these animals. They will not be accepted for you because they are deformed and have a defect."
03Lv 22:26 The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 22:27 "When an ox, sheep, or goat is born, it must remain with its mother for seven days; from the eighth day on, it will be acceptable as a gift, a fire offering to the LORD.
03Lv 22:28 But you are not to slaughter an animal from the herd or flock on the same day as its young.
03Lv 22:29 When you sacrifice a thank offering to the LORD, sacrifice it so that you may be accepted.
03Lv 22:30 It is to be eaten on the same day. Do not let any of it remain until morning; I am the LORD.
03Lv 22:31 "You are to keep My commands and do them; I am the LORD.
03Lv 22:32 You must not profane My holy name; I must be treated as holy among the Israelites. I am the LORD who sets you apart,
03Lv 22:33 the One who brought you out of the land of Egypt to be your God; I am the LORD."
03Lv 23:1 The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 23:2 "Speak to the Israelites and tell them: These are My appointed times, the times of the LORD that you will proclaim as sacred assemblies.
03Lv 23:3 "For six days work may be done, but on the seventh day there must be a Sabbath of complete rest, a sacred assembly. You are not to do any work; it is a Sabbath to the LORD wherever you live.
03Lv 23:4 "These are the LORD's appointed times, the sacred assemblies you are to proclaim at their appointed times.
03Lv 23:5 The Passover to the LORD comes in the first month, at twilight on the fourteenth day of the month.
03Lv 23:6 The Festival of Unleavened Bread to the LORD is on the fifteenth day of the same month. For seven days you must eat unleavened bread.
03Lv 23:7 On the first day you are to hold a sacred assembly; you are not to do any daily work.
03Lv 23:8 You are to present a fire offering to the LORD for seven days. On the seventh day there will be a sacred assembly; you must not do any daily work."
03Lv 23:9 The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 23:10 "Speak to the Israelites and tell them: When you enter the land I am giving you and reap its harvest, you are to bring the first sheaf of your harvest to the priest.
03Lv 23:11 He will wave the sheaf before the LORD so that you may be accepted; the priest is to wave it on the day after the Sabbath.
03Lv 23:12 On the day you wave the sheaf, you are to offer a year-old male lamb without blemish as a burnt offering to the LORD.
03Lv 23:13 Its grain offering is to be four quarts of fine flour mixed with oil as a fire offering to the LORD, a pleasing aroma, and its drink offering will be one quart of wine.
03Lv 23:14 You must not eat bread, roasted grain, or [any] new grain until this very day, and you have brought the offering of your God. This is to be a permanent statute throughout your generations wherever you live.
03Lv 23:15 "You are to count seven complete weeks starting from the day after the Sabbath, the day you brought the sheaf of the presentation offering.
03Lv 23:16 You are to count 50 days until the day after the seventh Sabbath and then present an offering of new grain to the LORD.
03Lv 23:17 Bring two loaves of bread from your settlements as a presentation offering, each of them made from four quarts of fine flour, baked with yeast, as firstfruits to the LORD.
03Lv 23:18 You are to present with the bread seven unblemished male lambs a year old, one young bull, and two rams. They will be a burnt offering to the Lord, with their grain offerings and drink offerings, a fire offering of a pleasing aroma to the LORD.
03Lv 23:19 You are also to prepare one male goat as a sin offering, and two male lambs a year old as a fellowship sacrifice.
03Lv 23:20 The priest will wave the lambs with the bread of firstfruits as a presentation offering before the LORD; the bread and the two lambs will be holy to the LORD for the priest.
03Lv 23:21 On that same day you are to make a proclamation and hold a sacred assembly. You are not to do any daily work. This is to be a permanent statute wherever you live throughout your generations.
03Lv 23:22 When you reap the harvest of your land, you are not to reap all the way to the edge of your field or gather the gleanings of your harvest. Leave them for the poor and the foreign resident; I am the LORD your God."
03Lv 23:23 The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 23:24 "Tell the Israelites: In the seventh month, on the first [day] of the month, you are to have a day of complete rest, commemoration and jubilation-- a sacred assembly.
03Lv 23:25 You must not do any daily work, but you must present a fire offering to the LORD."
03Lv 23:26 The LORD again spoke to Moses:
03Lv 23:27 "The tenth [day] of this seventh month is the Day of Atonement. You are to hold a sacred assembly and practice self-denial; you are to present a fire offering to the LORD.
03Lv 23:28 On this particular day you are not to do any work, for it is a Day of Atonement to make atonement for yourselves before the LORD your God.
03Lv 23:29 If any person does not practice self-denial on this particular day, he must be cut off from his people.
03Lv 23:30 I will destroy among his people anyone who does any work on this same day.
03Lv 23:31 You are not to do any work. This is a permanent statute throughout your generations wherever you live.
03Lv 23:32 It will be a Sabbath of complete rest for you, and you must practice self-denial. You are to observe your Sabbath from the evening of the ninth [day] of the month until the [following] evening."
03Lv 23:33 The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 23:34 "Tell the Israelites: The Festival of Booths to the LORD begins on the fifteenth day of this seventh month and continues for seven days.
03Lv 23:35 There is to be a sacred assembly on the first day; you are not to do any daily work.
03Lv 23:36 You are to present a fire offering to the LORD for seven days. On the eighth day you are to hold a sacred assembly and present a fire offering to the LORD. It is a solemn gathering; you are not to do any daily work.
03Lv 23:37 "These are the LORD's appointed times that you are to proclaim as sacred assemblies for presenting fire offerings to the LORD, burnt offerings and grain offerings, sacrifices and drink offerings, each on its [designated] day.
03Lv 23:38 These are in addition to the offerings for the LORD's Sabbaths, your gifts, all your vow offerings, and all your freewill offerings that you give to the LORD.
03Lv 23:39 "You are to celebrate the LORD's festival on the fifteenth day of the seventh month for seven days after you have gathered the produce of the land. There will be complete rest on the first day and complete rest on the eighth day.
03Lv 23:40 On the first day you are to take the product of majestic trees-- palm fronds, boughs of leafy trees, and willows of the brook-- and rejoice before the LORD your God for seven days.
03Lv 23:41 You are to celebrate it as a festival to the LORD seven days each year. This is a permanent statute for you throughout your generations; you must celebrate it in the seventh month.
03Lv 23:42 You are to live in booths for seven days. All the native-born of Israel must live in booths,
03Lv 23:43 so that your generations may know that I made the Israelites live in booths when I brought them out of the land of Egypt; I am the LORD your God."
03Lv 23:44 So Moses declared the LORD's appointed times to the Israelites.
03Lv 24:1 The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 24:2 "Command the Israelites to bring you pure oil of beaten olives for the light, so that the lamp will burn regularly.
03Lv 24:3 Aaron is to tend it regularly from evening until morning before the LORD outside the veil of the testimony in the tent of meeting. This is a permanent statute throughout your generations.
03Lv 24:4 He must regularly tend the lamps on the pure [gold] lampstand in the LORD's presence.
03Lv 24:5 "Take fine flour and bake it into 12 loaves; each loaf is to be made with four quarts.
03Lv 24:6 Arrange them in two rows, six to a row, on the pure [gold] table before the LORD.
03Lv 24:7 Place pure frankincense near each row, so that it may serve as a memorial portion for the bread and a fire offering to the LORD.
03Lv 24:8 The bread is to be set out before the LORD every Sabbath day as a perpetual covenant obligation on the part of the Israelites.
03Lv 24:9 It belongs to Aaron and his sons, who are to eat it in a holy place, for it is the holiest portion for him from the fire offerings to the Lord; this is a permanent rule."
03Lv 24:10 Now the son of an Israelite mother and an Egyptian father was among the Israelites. A fight broke out in the camp between the Israelite woman's son and an Israelite man.
03Lv 24:11 Her son cursed and blasphemed the Name, and they brought him to Moses. (His mother's name was Shelomith, a daughter of Dibri of the tribe of Dan.)
03Lv 24:12 They put him in custody until the LORD's decision could be made clear to them.
03Lv 24:13 Then the LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 24:14 "Bring the one who has cursed to the outside of the camp and have all who heard [him] lay their hands on his head; then have the whole community stone him.
03Lv 24:15 And tell the Israelites: If anyone curses his God, he will bear the consequences of his sin.
03Lv 24:16 Whoever blasphemes the name of the LORD is to be put to death; the whole community must stone him. If he blasphemes the Name, he is to be put to death, whether the foreign resident or the native.
03Lv 24:17 "If a man kills anyone, he must be put to death.
03Lv 24:18 Whoever kills an animal is to make restitution for it, life for life.
03Lv 24:19 If any man inflicts a permanent injury on his neighbor, whatever he has done is to be done to him:
03Lv 24:20 fracture for fracture, eye for eye, tooth for tooth. Whatever injury he inflicted on the person, the same is to be inflicted on him.
03Lv 24:21 Whoever kills an animal is to make restitution for it, but whoever kills a person is to be put to death.
03Lv 24:22 You are to have the same law for the foreign resident and the native, because I am the LORD your God."
03Lv 24:23 After Moses spoke to the Israelites, they brought the one who had cursed to the outside of the camp and stoned him. So the Israelites did as the LORD had commanded Moses.
03Lv 25:1 The LORD spoke to Moses on Mount Sinai:
03Lv 25:2 "Speak to the Israelites and tell them: When you enter the land I am giving you, the land will observe a Sabbath to the LORD.
03Lv 25:3 You may sow your field for six years, and you may prune your vineyard and gather its produce for six years.
03Lv 25:4 But there will be a Sabbath of complete rest for the land in the seventh year, a Sabbath to the LORD: you are not to sow your field or prune your vineyard.
03Lv 25:5 You are not to reap what grows by itself from your crop, or harvest the grapes of your untended vines. It must be a year of complete rest for the land.
03Lv 25:6 [Whatever] the land [produces during] the Sabbath year can be food for you; for yourself, your male or female slave, and the hired hand or foreigner who stays with you.
03Lv 25:7 All of its growth may serve as food for your livestock and the wild animals in your land.
03Lv 25:8 "You are to count seven sabbatic years, seven times seven years, so that the time period of the seven sabbatic years amounts to 49.
03Lv 25:9 Then you are to sound a trumpet loudly in the seventh month, on the tenth [day] of the month; you will sound it throughout your land on the Day of Atonement.
03Lv 25:10 You are to consecrate the fiftieth year and proclaim freedom in the land for all its inhabitants. It will be your Jubilee, when each of you are to return to his property and each of you to his clan.
03Lv 25:11 The fiftieth year will be your Jubilee; you are not to sow, reap what grows by itself, or harvest its untended vines.
03Lv 25:12 It is to be holy to you because it is the Jubilee; you may [only] eat its produce [directly] from the field.
03Lv 25:13 "In this Year of Jubilee, each of you will return to his property.
03Lv 25:14 If you make a sale to your neighbor or a purchase from him, do not cheat one another.
03Lv 25:15 You are to make the purchase from your neighbor based on the number of years since the last Jubilee. He is to sell to you based on the number of [remaining] harvest years.
03Lv 25:16 You are to increase its price in proportion to a greater amount of years, and decrease its price in proportion to a lesser amount of years, because what he is selling to you is a number of harvests.
03Lv 25:17 You are not to cheat one another, but fear your God, for I am the LORD your God.
03Lv 25:18 "You are to observe My statutes and ordinances and carefully observe them, so that you may live securely in the land.
03Lv 25:19 Then the land will yield its fruit, so that you can eat, be satisfied, and live securely in the land.
03Lv 25:20 If you wonder: 'What will we eat in the seventh year if we don't sow or gather our produce?'
03Lv 25:21 I will appoint My blessing for you in the sixth year, so that it will produce a crop sufficient for three years.
03Lv 25:22 When you sow in the eighth year, you will be eating from the previous harvest. You will be eating this until the ninth year when its harvest comes in.
03Lv 25:23 "The land is not to be permanently sold because it is Mine, and you are only foreigners and temporary residents on My land.
03Lv 25:24 You are to allow the redemption of any land you occupy.
03Lv 25:25 If your brother becomes destitute and sells part of his property, his nearest relative may come and redeem what his brother has sold.
03Lv 25:26 If a man has no family redeemer, but he prospers and obtains enough to redeem his land,
03Lv 25:27 he may calculate the years since its sale, repay the balance to the man he sold it to, and return to his property.
03Lv 25:28 But if he cannot obtain enough to repay him, what he sold will remain in the possession of its purchaser until the Year of Jubilee. It is to be released at the Jubilee, so that he may return to his property.
03Lv 25:29 "If a man sells a residence in a walled city, his right of redemption will last until a year has passed after its sale; his right of redemption will last a year.
03Lv 25:30 If it is not redeemed by the end of a full year, then the house in the walled city is permanently transferred to its purchaser throughout his generations. It is not to be released on the Jubilee.
03Lv 25:31 But houses in villages that have no walls around them are to be classified as open fields. The right to redeem [such] houses stays in effect, and they are to be released at the Jubilee.
03Lv 25:32 "Concerning the Levitical cities, the Levites always have the right to redeem houses in the cities they possess.
03Lv 25:33 Whatever [property] one of the Levites can redeem-- a house sold in a city they possess-- must be released at the Jubilee, because the houses in the Levitical cities are their possession among the Israelites.
03Lv 25:34 The open pastureland around their cities may not be sold, for it is their permanent possession.
03Lv 25:35 "If your brother becomes destitute and cannot sustain himself among you, you are to support him as a foreigner or temporary resident, so that he can continue to live among you.
03Lv 25:36 Do not profit or take interest from him, but fear your God and let your brother live among you.
03Lv 25:37 You are not to lend him your silver with interest or sell [him] your food for profit.
03Lv 25:38 I am the LORD your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt to give you the land of Canaan and to be your God.
03Lv 25:39 "If your brother among you becomes destitute and sells himself to you, you must not force him to do slave labor.
03Lv 25:40 Let him stay with you as a hired hand or temporary resident; he may work for you until the Year of Jubilee.
03Lv 25:41 Then he and his children are to be released from you, and he may return to his clan and his ancestral property.
03Lv 25:42 They are not to be sold as slaves, because they are My slaves I brought out of the land of Egypt.
03Lv 25:43 You are not to rule over them harshly but fear your God.
03Lv 25:44 Your male and female slaves are to be from the nations around you; you may purchase male and female slaves.
03Lv 25:45 You may also purchase them from the foreigners staying with you, or from their families living among you-- those born in your land. These may become your property.
03Lv 25:46 You may leave them to your sons after you to inherit as property; you can make them slaves for life. But concerning your brothers, the Israelites, you must not rule over one another harshly.
03Lv 25:47 "If a foreigner or temporary resident [living] among you prospers, but your brother [living] near him becomes destitute and sells himself to the foreigner living among you, or to a member of the foreigner's clan,
03Lv 25:48 he has the right of redemption after he has been sold. One of his brothers may redeem him.
03Lv 25:49 His uncle or cousin may redeem him, or any of his close relatives from his clan may redeem him. If he prospers, he may redeem himself.
03Lv 25:50 The one who purchased him is to calculate [the time] from the year he sold himself to him until the Year of Jubilee. The price of his sale will be [determined] by the number of years. It will be [set] for him like the daily wages of a hired hand.
03Lv 25:51 If many years are still left, he must pay his redemption price in proportion to them based on his purchase price.
03Lv 25:52 If only a few years remain until the Year of Jubilee, he will calculate and pay the price of his redemption in proportion to his [remaining] years.
03Lv 25:53 He will stay with him like a man hired year by year. A foreign owner is not to rule over him harshly in your sight.
03Lv 25:54 If he is not redeemed in any of these [ways], he and his children are to be released at the Year of Jubilee.
03Lv 25:55 For the Israelites are My slaves. They are My slaves I brought out of the land of Egypt; I am the LORD your God.
03Lv 26:1 "Do not make idols for yourselves, set up a carved image or sacred pillar for yourselves, or place a sculpted stone in your land to bow down to it, for I am the LORD your God.
03Lv 26:2 You must keep My Sabbaths and honor My sanctuary; I am the LORD.
03Lv 26:3 "If you follow My statutes and faithfully observe My commands,
03Lv 26:4 I will give you rain at the right time, and the land will yield its produce, and the trees of the field will bear their fruit.
03Lv 26:5 Your threshing will continue until grape harvest, and the grape harvest will continue until sowing time; you will have plenty of food to eat and live securely in your land.
03Lv 26:6 I will give peace to the land, and you will lie down with nothing to frighten [you]. I will remove dangerous animals from the land, and no sword will pass through your land.
03Lv 26:7 You will pursue your enemies, and they will fall before you by the sword.
03Lv 26:8 Five of you will pursue 100, and 100 of you will pursue 10,000; your enemies will fall before you by the sword.
03Lv 26:9 "I will turn to you, make you fruitful and multiply you, and confirm My covenant with you.
03Lv 26:10 You will eat the old grain of the previous year and will clear out the old to make room for the new.
03Lv 26:11 I will place My residence among you, and I will not reject you.
03Lv 26:12 I will walk among you and be your God, and you will be My people.
03Lv 26:13 I am the LORD your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, so that you would no longer be their slaves. I broke the bars of your yoke and enabled you to live in freedom.
03Lv 26:14 "But if you do not obey Me and observe all these commands--
03Lv 26:15 if you reject My statutes and despise My ordinances, and do not observe all My commands-- and break My covenant,
03Lv 26:16 then I will do this to you: I will bring terror on you-- wasting disease and fever that will cause your eyes to fail and your life to ebb away. You will sow your seed in vain because your enemies will eat it.
03Lv 26:17 I will turn against you, so that you will be defeated by your enemies. Those who hate you will rule over you, and you will flee even though no one is pursuing you.
03Lv 26:18 "But if after these things you will not obey Me, I will proceed to discipline you seven times for your sins.
03Lv 26:19 I will break down your strong pride. I will make your sky like iron and your land like bronze,
03Lv 26:20 and your strength will be used up for nothing. Your land will not yield its produce, and the trees of the land will not bear their fruit.
03Lv 26:21 "If you act with hostility toward Me and are unwilling to obey Me, I will multiply your plagues seven times for your sins.
03Lv 26:22 I will send wild animals against you that will deprive you of your children, ravage your livestock, and reduce your numbers until your roads are deserted.
03Lv 26:23 "If in spite of these things you do not accept My discipline, but act with hostility toward Me,
03Lv 26:24 then I will act with hostility toward you; I also will strike you seven times for your sins.
03Lv 26:25 I will bring a sword against you to execute the vengeance of the covenant. Though you withdraw into your cities, I will send a pestilence among you, and you will be delivered into enemy hands.
03Lv 26:26 When I cut off your supply of bread, 10 women will bake your bread in a single oven and ration out your bread by weight, so that you will eat but not be satisfied.
03Lv 26:27 "And if in spite of this you do not obey Me but act with hostility toward Me,
03Lv 26:28 I will act with furious hostility toward you; I will also discipline you seven times for your sins.
03Lv 26:29 You will eat the flesh of your sons; you will eat the flesh of your daughters.
03Lv 26:30 I will destroy your high places, cut down your incense altars, and heap your dead bodies on the lifeless bodies of your idols; I will reject you.
03Lv 26:31 I will reduce your cities to ruins and devastate your sanctuaries. I will not smell the pleasing aroma of your [sacrifices].
03Lv 26:32 I also will devastate the land, so that your enemies who come to live there will be appalled by it.
03Lv 26:33 But I will scatter you among the nations, and I will draw a sword [to chase] after you. So your land will become desolate, and your cities will become ruins.
03Lv 26:34 "Then the land will make up for its Sabbath [years] during the time it lies desolate, while you are in the land of your enemies. At that time the land will rest and make up for its Sabbaths.
03Lv 26:35 As long as it lies desolate, it will have the rest it did not have during your Sabbaths when you lived there.
03Lv 26:36 "I will put anxiety in the hearts of those of you who survive in the lands of their enemies. The sound of a wind-driven leaf will put them to flight, and they will flee as one flees from a sword, and fall though no one is pursuing [them].
03Lv 26:37 They will stumble over one another as if [fleeing] from a sword though no one is pursuing [them]. You will not be able to stand against your enemies.
03Lv 26:38 You will perish among the nations; the land of your enemies will devour you.
03Lv 26:39 Those who survive in the lands of your enemies will waste away because of their sin; they will also waste away because of their fathers' sins along with theirs.
03Lv 26:40 "But if they will confess their sin and the sin of their fathers-- their unfaithfulness that they practiced against Me, and how they acted with hostility toward Me,
03Lv 26:41 and I acted with hostility toward them and brought them into the land of their enemies-- and if their uncircumcised hearts will be humbled, and if they will pay the penalty for their sin,
03Lv 26:42 then I will remember My covenant with Jacob. I will also remember My covenant with Isaac and My covenant with Abraham, and I will remember the land.
03Lv 26:43 For the land abandoned by them will make up for its Sabbaths by lying desolate without the people, while they pay the penalty for their sin, because they rejected My ordinances and abhorred My statutes.
03Lv 26:44 Yet in spite of this, while they are in the land of their enemies, I will not reject or abhor them so as to destroy them and break My covenant with them, since I am the LORD their God.
03Lv 26:45 For their sake I will remember the covenant with their fathers, whom I brought out of the land of Egypt in the sight of the nations to be their God; I am the LORD."
03Lv 26:46 These are the statutes, ordinances, and laws the LORD established between Himself and the Israelites through Moses on Mount Sinai.
03Lv 27:1 The LORD spoke to Moses:
03Lv 27:2 "Speak to the Israelites and tell them: When someone makes a special vow to the LORD that involves the valuation of people,
03Lv 27:3 if the valuation concerns a male from 20 to 60 years old, your valuation is 50 silver shekels [measured] by the standard sanctuary shekel.
03Lv 27:4 If the person is a female, your valuation is 30 shekels.
03Lv 27:5 If the person is from five to 20 years old, your valuation for a male is 20 shekels and for a female 10 shekels.
03Lv 27:6 If the person is from one month to five years old, your valuation for a male is five silver shekels, and for a female your valuation is three shekels of silver.
03Lv 27:7 If the person is 60 years or more, your valuation is 15 shekels for a male and 10 shekels for a female.
03Lv 27:8 But if one is too poor to pay the valuation, he must present the person before the priest and the priest will set a value for him. The priest will set a value for him according to what the one making the vow can afford.
03Lv 27:9 "If the vow involves one of the animals that may be brought as an offering to the LORD, any of these he gives to the LORD will be holy.
03Lv 27:10 He may not replace it or make a substitution for it, either good for bad, or bad for good. But if he does substitute one animal for another, both that animal and its substitute will be holy.
03Lv 27:11 "If the vow involves any of the unclean animals that may not be brought as an offering to the LORD, the animal must be presented before the priest.
03Lv 27:12 The priest will set its value, whether high or low; the price will be set as the priest makes the valuation for you.
03Lv 27:13 If the one who brought it decides to redeem it, he must add a fifth to the valuation.
03Lv 27:14 "When a man consecrates his house as holy to the LORD, the priest will assess its value, whether high or low. The price will stand just as the priest assesses it.
03Lv 27:15 But if the one who consecrated his house redeems [it], he must add a fifth to the valuation price, and it will be his.
03Lv 27:16 "If a man consecrates to the LORD any part of a field that he possesses, your valuation will be proportional to the seed needed to sow it, at the rate of 50 silver shekels for [every] five bushels of barley seed.
03Lv 27:17 If he consecrates his field during the Year of Jubilee, the price will stand according to your valuation.
03Lv 27:18 But if he consecrates his field after the Jubilee, the priest will calculate the price for him in proportion to the years left until the [next] Year of Jubilee, so that your valuation will be reduced.
03Lv 27:19 If the one who consecrated the field decides to redeem it, he must add a fifth to the valuation price, and the field will transfer back to him.
03Lv 27:20 But if he does not redeem the field or if he has sold it to another man, it is no longer redeemable.
03Lv 27:21 When the field is released in the Jubilee, it will be holy to the LORD like a field permanently set apart; it becomes the priest's property.
03Lv 27:22 "If a person consecrates to the LORD a field he has purchased that is not part of his inherited landholding,
03Lv 27:23 then the priest will calculate for him the amount of the valuation up to the Year of Jubilee, and the person will pay the valuation on that day as a holy offering to the LORD.
03Lv 27:24 In the Year of Jubilee the field will return to the one he bought it from, the original owner.
03Lv 27:25 All your valuations will be [measured] by the standard sanctuary shekel, 20 gerahs to the shekel.
03Lv 27:26 "But no one can consecrate a firstborn of the livestock, whether an animal from the herd or flock, to the LORD, because a firstborn [already] belongs to the LORD.
03Lv 27:27 If it is one of the unclean livestock, it must be ransomed according to your valuation by adding a fifth of its value to it. If it is not redeemed, it can be sold according to your valuation.
03Lv 27:28 "Nothing that a man permanently sets apart to the LORD from all he owns, whether a person, an animal, or his inherited landholding, can be sold or redeemed; everything set apart is especially holy to the LORD.
03Lv 27:29 No person who has been set apart [for destruction] is to be ransomed; he must be put to death.
03Lv 27:30 "Every tenth of the land's produce, grain from the soil or fruit from the trees, belongs to the LORD; it is holy to the LORD.
03Lv 27:31 If a man decides to redeem any part of this tenth, he must add one-fifth to its value.
03Lv 27:32 Every tenth animal from the herd or flock, which passes under the [shepherd's] rod, will be holy to the LORD.
03Lv 27:33 He is not to inspect whether it is good or bad, and he is not to make a substitution for it. But if he does make a substitution, both the animal and its substitute will be holy; they cannot be redeemed."
03Lv 27:34 These are the commands the LORD gave Moses for the Israelites on Mount Sinai.
