04Nm 7:73 His offering was one silver dish weighing three and a quarter pounds and one silver basin weighing one and three-quarter pounds, [measured] by the standard sanctuary shekel, both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil for a grain offering;
04Nm 7:74 one gold bowl weighing four ounces, full of incense;
04Nm 7:75 one young bull, one ram, and one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering;
04Nm 7:76 one male goat for a sin offering;
04Nm 7:77 and two bulls, five rams, five male breeding goats, and five male lambs a year old, for the fellowship sacrifice. This was the offering of Pagiel son of Ochran.
04Nm 7:78 On the twelfth day Ahira son of Enan, leader of the Naphtalites, [presented an offering].
04Nm 7:79 His offering was one silver dish weighing three and a quarter pounds and one silver basin weighing one and three-quarter pounds, [measured] by the standard sanctuary shekel, both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil for a grain offering;
04Nm 7:80 one gold bowl weighing four ounces, full of incense;
04Nm 7:81 one young bull, one ram, and one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering;
04Nm 7:82 one male goat for a sin offering;
04Nm 7:83 and two bulls, five rams, five male breeding goats, and five male lambs a year old, for the fellowship sacrifice. This was the offering of Ahira son of Enan.
04Nm 7:84 This was the dedication gift from the leaders of Israel for the altar when it was anointed: 12 silver dishes, 12 silver basins, and 12 gold bowls.
04Nm 7:85 Each silver dish [weighed] three and a quarter pounds, and each basin one and three-quarter pounds. The total [weight] of the silver articles was 60 pounds [measured] by the standard sanctuary shekel.
04Nm 7:86 The 12 gold bowls full of incense each [weighed] four ounces [measured] by the standard sanctuary shekel. The total [weight] of the gold bowls was three pounds.
04Nm 7:87 All the livestock for the burnt offering totaled 12 bulls, 12 rams, and 12 male lambs a year old, with their grain offerings, and 12 male goats for the sin offering.
04Nm 7:88 All the livestock for the fellowship sacrifice totaled 24 bulls, 60 rams, 60 male breeding goats, and 60 male lambs a year old. This was the dedication gift for the altar after it was anointed.
04Nm 7:89 When Moses entered the tent of meeting to speak with the LORD, he heard the voice speaking to him from above the mercy seat that was on the ark of the testimony, from between the two cherubim. He spoke to him [that way].
04Nm 8:1 The LORD spoke to Moses:
04Nm 8:2 "Speak to Aaron and tell him: When you set up the lamps, the seven lamps are to give light in front of the lampstand."
04Nm 8:3 So Aaron did this; he set up its lamps [to give light] in front of the lampstand just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
04Nm 8:4 This is the way the lampstand was made: it was a hammered work of gold, hammered from its base to its flower petals. The lampstand was made according to the pattern the LORD had shown Moses.
04Nm 8:5 The LORD spoke to Moses:
04Nm 8:6 "Take the Levites from among the Israelites and ceremonially cleanse them.
04Nm 8:7 This is what you must do to them for their purification: Sprinkle them with the purification water. Have them shave their entire bodies and wash their clothes, and so purify themselves.
04Nm 8:8 "They are to take a young bull and its grain offering of fine flour mixed with oil, and you are to take a second young bull for a sin offering.
04Nm 8:9 Bring the Levites before the tent of meeting and assemble the entire Israelite community.
04Nm 8:10 Then present the Levites before the LORD, and have the Israelites lay their hands on them.
04Nm 8:11 Aaron is to present the Levites before the LORD as a presentation offering from the Israelites, so that they may perform the LORD's work.
04Nm 8:12 Next the Levites are to lay their hands on the heads of the bulls. Sacrifice one as a sin offering and the other as a burnt offering to the Lord, to make atonement for the Levites.
04Nm 8:13 "You are to have the Levites stand before Aaron and his sons, and you are to present them before the LORD as a presentation offering.
04Nm 8:14 In this way you are to separate the Levites from the rest of the Israelites so that the Levites will belong to Me.
04Nm 8:15 After that the Levites may come to serve [at] the tent of meeting, once you have ceremonially cleansed them and presented them as a presentation offering.
04Nm 8:16 For they have been exclusively assigned to Me from the Israelites. I have taken them for Myself in place of all who come first from the womb, every Israelite firstborn.
04Nm 8:17 For every firstborn among the Israelites is Mine, both man and animal. I consecrated them to Myself on the day I struck down every firstborn in the land of Egypt.
04Nm 8:18 But I have taken the Levites in place of every firstborn among the Israelites.
04Nm 8:19 From the Israelites, I have given the Levites exclusively to Aaron and his sons to perform the work for the Israelites at the tent of meeting and to make atonement on their behalf, so that no plague will come against the Israelites when they approach the sanctuary."
04Nm 8:20 Moses, Aaron, and the entire Israelite community did [this] to the Levites. The Israelites did everything to them the LORD commanded Moses regarding the Levites.
04Nm 8:21 The Levites purified themselves and washed their clothes; then Aaron presented them before the LORD as a presentation offering. Aaron also made atonement for them to ceremonially cleanse them.
04Nm 8:22 After that, the Levites came to do their work at the tent of meeting in the presence of Aaron and his sons. So they did to them as the LORD had commanded Moses concerning the Levites.
04Nm 8:23 The LORD spoke to Moses:
04Nm 8:24 "In regard to the Levites: From 25 years old or more, a man enters the service in the work at the tent of meeting.
04Nm 8:25 But at 50 years old he is to retire from his service in the work and no longer serve.
04Nm 8:26 He may assist his brothers to fulfill responsibilities at the tent of meeting, but he must not do the work. This is how you are to deal with the Levites regarding their duties."
04Nm 9:1 In the first month of the second year after their departure from the land of Egypt, the LORD told Moses in the Wilderness of Sinai:
04Nm 9:2 "The Israelites are to observe the Passover at its appointed time.
04Nm 9:3 You must observe it at its appointed time on the fourteenth day of this month at twilight; you are to observe it according to all its statutes and ordinances."
04Nm 9:4 So Moses told the Israelites to observe the Passover,
04Nm 9:5 and they observed it in the first month on the fourteenth day at twilight in the Wilderness of Sinai. The Israelites did everything as the LORD had commanded Moses.
04Nm 9:6 But there were [some] men who were unclean because of a human corpse, so they could not observe the Passover on that day. These men came before Moses and Aaron the same day
04Nm 9:7 and said to him, "We are unclean because of a human corpse. Why should we be excluded from presenting the LORD's offering at its appointed time with the [other] Israelites?"
04Nm 9:8 Moses replied to them, "Wait here until I hear what the LORD commands for you."
04Nm 9:9 Then the LORD spoke to Moses:
04Nm 9:10 "Tell the Israelites: When any one of you or your descendants is unclean because of a corpse or is on a distant journey, he may still observe the Passover to the LORD.
04Nm 9:11 Such people are to observe it in the second month, on the fourteenth day at twilight. They are to eat the animal with unleavened bread and bitter herbs;
04Nm 9:12 they may not leave any of it until morning or break any of its bones. They must observe the Passover according to all its statutes.
04Nm 9:13 "But the man who is ceremonially clean, is not on a journey, and yet fails to observe the Passover is to be cut off from his people, because he did not present the LORD's offering at its appointed time. That man will bear the consequences of his sin.
04Nm 9:14 "If a foreigner resides with you and wants to observe the Passover to the LORD, he is to do so according to the Passover statute and its ordinances. You are to apply the same statute to both the foreign resident and the native of the land."
04Nm 9:15 On the day the tabernacle was set up, the cloud covered the tabernacle, the tent of the testimony, and it appeared like fire above the tabernacle from evening until morning.
04Nm 9:16 It remained that way continuously: the cloud would cover it, appearing like fire at night.
04Nm 9:17 Whenever the cloud was lifted up above the tent, the Israelites would set out; at the place where the cloud stopped, there the Israelites camped.
04Nm 9:18 At the LORD's command the Israelites set out, and at the LORD's command they camped. As long as the cloud stayed over the tabernacle, they camped.
04Nm 9:19 Even when the cloud stayed over the tabernacle many days, the Israelites carried out the LORD's requirement and did not set out.
04Nm 9:20 Sometimes the cloud remained over the tabernacle for [only] a few days. They would camp at the LORD's command and set out at the LORD's command.
04Nm 9:21 Sometimes the cloud remained [only] from evening until morning; when the cloud lifted in the morning, they set out. Or if it remained a day and a night, they moved out when the cloud lifted.
04Nm 9:22 Whether it was two days, a month, or longer, the Israelites camped and did not set out as long as the cloud stayed over the tabernacle. But when it was lifted, they set out.
04Nm 9:23 They camped at the LORD's command, and they set out at the LORD's command. They carried out the LORD's requirement according to His command through Moses.
04Nm 10:1 The LORD spoke to Moses:
04Nm 10:2 "Make two trumpets of hammered silver to summon the community and have the camps set out.
04Nm 10:3 When both are sounded in long blasts, the entire community is to gather before you at the entrance to the tent of meeting.
04Nm 10:4 However, if one is sounded, only the leaders, the heads of Israel's clans, are to gather before you.
04Nm 10:5 "When you sound short blasts, the camps pitched on the east are to set out.
04Nm 10:6 When you sound short blasts a second time, the camps pitched on the south are to set out. Short blasts are to be sounded for them to set out.
04Nm 10:7 When calling the assembly together, you are to sound long blasts, not short ones.
04Nm 10:8 The sons of Aaron, the priests, are to sound the trumpets. Your use of these is a permanent statute throughout your generations.
04Nm 10:9 "When you enter into battle in your land against an adversary who is attacking you, sound short blasts on the trumpets, and you will be remembered before the LORD your God and be delivered from your enemies.
04Nm 10:10 You are to sound the trumpets over your burnt offerings and your fellowship sacrifices and on your joyous occasions, your appointed festivals, and the beginning of each of your months. They will serve as a reminder for you before your God: I am the LORD your God."
04Nm 10:11 During the second year, in the second month on the twentieth [day] of the month, the cloud was lifted up above the tabernacle of the testimony.
04Nm 10:12 The Israelites traveled on from the Wilderness of Sinai, moving from one place to the next until the cloud stopped in the Wilderness of Paran.
04Nm 10:13 They set out for the first time according to the LORD's command through Moses.
04Nm 10:14 The military divisions of the camp of Judah with their banner set out first, and Nahshon son of Amminadab was over Judah's divisions.
04Nm 10:15 Nethanel son of Zuar was over the division of the Issachar tribe,
04Nm 10:16 and Eliab son of Helon was over the division of the Zebulun tribe.
04Nm 10:17 The tabernacle was then taken down, and the Gershonites and the Merarites set out, transporting the tabernacle.
04Nm 10:18 The military divisions of the camp of Reuben with their banner set out, and Elizur son of Shedeur was over Reuben's division.
04Nm 10:19 Shelumiel son of Zurishaddai was over the division of Simeon's tribe,
04Nm 10:20 and Eliasaph son of Deuel was over the division of the tribe of Gad.
04Nm 10:21 The Kohathites then set out, transporting the holy objects; the tabernacle was to be set up before their arrival.
04Nm 10:22 Next the military divisions of the camp of Ephraim with their banner set out, and Elishama son of Ammihud was over Ephraim's division.
04Nm 10:23 Gamaliel son of Pedahzur was over the division of the tribe of Manasseh,
04Nm 10:24 and Abidan son of Gideoni was over the division of the tribe of Benjamin.
04Nm 10:25 The military divisions of the camp of Dan with their banner set out, serving as rearguard for all the camps, and Ahiezer son of Ammishaddai was over Dan's division.
04Nm 10:26 Pagiel son of Ochran was over the division of the tribe of Asher,
04Nm 10:27 and Ahira son of Enan was over the division of the tribe of Naphtali.
04Nm 10:28 This was the order of march for the Israelites by their military divisions as they set out.
04Nm 10:29 Moses said to Hobab, son of Moses' father-in-law Reuel the Midianite: "We're setting out for the place the LORD promised: 'I will give it to you.' Come with us, and we will treat you well, for the LORD has promised good things to Israel."
04Nm 10:30 But he replied to him, "I don't want to go. Instead, I will go to my own land and my relatives."
04Nm 10:31 "Please don't leave us," Moses said, "since you know where we should camp in the wilderness, and you can serve as our eyes.
04Nm 10:32 If you come with us, whatever good the LORD does for us we will do for you."
04Nm 10:33 They set out from the mountain of the LORD on a three-day journey to seek a resting place for them, with the ark of the LORD's covenant traveling ahead of them for the three days.
04Nm 10:34 Meanwhile, the cloud of the LORD was over them by day when they set out from the camp.
04Nm 10:35 Whenever the ark set out, Moses would say: Arise, LORD! Let Your enemies be scattered, and those who hate You flee from Your presence.
04Nm 10:36 When it came to rest, he would say: Return, LORD, to the countless thousands of Israel.
04Nm 11:1 Now the people began complaining openly before the LORD about hardship. When the LORD heard, His anger burned, and the fire from the LORD blazed among them and consumed the outskirts of the camp.
04Nm 11:2 Then the people cried out to Moses, and he prayed to the LORD, and the fire died down.
04Nm 11:3 So that place was named Taberah, because the LORD's fire had blazed among them.
04Nm 11:4 Contemptible people among them had a strong craving [for other food]. The Israelites cried again and said, "Who will feed us meat?
04Nm 11:5 We remember the free fish we ate in Egypt, along with the cucumbers, melons, leeks, onions, and garlic.
04Nm 11:6 But now our appetite is gone; there's nothing to look at but this manna!"
04Nm 11:7 The manna resembled coriander seed, and its appearance was like that of bdellium.
04Nm 11:8 The people walked around and gathered [it]. They ground [it] on a pair of grinding stones or crushed [it] in a mortar, then boiled [it] in a cooking pot and shaped it into cakes. It tasted like a pastry cooked with the finest oil.
04Nm 11:9 When the dew fell on the camp at night, the manna would fall with it.
04Nm 11:10 Moses heard the people, family after family, crying at the entrance of their tents. The LORD was very angry; Moses was also provoked.
04Nm 11:11 So Moses asked the LORD, "Why have You brought such trouble on Your servant? Why are You angry with me, and why do You burden me with all these people?
04Nm 11:12 Did I conceive all these people? Did I give them birth so You should tell me, 'Carry them at your breast, as a nursing woman carries a baby,' to the land that You swore to [give] their fathers?
04Nm 11:13 Where can I get meat to give all these people? For they are crying to me: 'Give us meat to eat!'
04Nm 11:14 "I can't carry all these people by myself. They are too much for me.
04Nm 11:15 If You are going to treat me like this, please kill me right now. If You are pleased with me, don't let me see my misery [any more]."
04Nm 11:16 The LORD answered Moses, "Bring Me 70 men from Israel known to you as elders and officers of the people. Take them to the tent of meeting and have them stand there with you.
04Nm 11:17 Then I will come down and speak with you there. I will take some of the Spirit who is on you and put [the Spirit] on them. They will help you bear the burden of the people, so that you do not have to bear it by yourself.
04Nm 11:18 "Tell the people: Purify yourselves [in readiness] for tomorrow, and you will eat meat because you cried before the LORD: 'Who will feed us meat? We really had it good in Egypt.' The LORD will give you meat and you will eat.
04Nm 11:19 You will eat, not for one day, or two days, or five days, or 10 days, or 20 days,
04Nm 11:20 but for a whole month-- until it comes out of your nostrils and becomes nauseating to you-- because you have rejected the LORD who is among you, and cried to Him: 'Why did we ever leave Egypt?'"
04Nm 11:21 But Moses replied, "I'm in the middle of a people with 600,000 foot soldiers, yet You say, 'I will give them meat, and they will eat for a month.'
04Nm 11:22 If flocks and herds were slaughtered for them, would they have enough? Or if all the fish in the sea were caught for them, would they have enough?"
04Nm 11:23 The LORD answered Moses, "Is the LORD's power limited? You will see whether or not what I have promised will happen to you."
04Nm 11:24 Moses went out and told the people the words of the LORD. He brought 70 men from the elders of the people and had them stand around the tent.
04Nm 11:25 Then the LORD descended in the cloud and spoke to him. He took some of the Spirit that was on Moses and placed [the Spirit] on the 70 elders. As the Spirit rested on them, they prophesied, but they never did it again.
04Nm 11:26 Two men had remained in the camp, one named Eldad and the other Medad; the Spirit rested on them-- they were among those listed, but had not gone out to the tent-- and they prophesied in the camp.
04Nm 11:27 A young man ran and reported to Moses, "Eldad and Medad are prophesying in the camp."
04Nm 11:28 Joshua son of Nun, assistant to Moses since his youth, responded, "Moses, my lord, stop them!"
04Nm 11:29 But Moses asked him, "Are you jealous on my account? If only all the LORD's people were prophets, and the LORD would place His Spirit on them."
04Nm 11:30 Then Moses returned to the camp along with the elders of Israel.
04Nm 11:31 A wind sent by the LORD came up and blew quail in from the sea; it dropped [them] at the camp all around, three feet off the ground, about a day's journey in every direction.
04Nm 11:32 The people were up all that day and night and all the next day gathering the quail-- the one who took the least gathered 33 bushels-- and they spread them out all around the camp.
04Nm 11:33 While the meat was still between their teeth, before it was chewed, the LORD's anger burned against the people, and the LORD struck them with a very severe plague.
04Nm 11:34 So they named that place Kibroth-hattaavah, because there they buried the people who had craved [the meat].
04Nm 11:35 From Kibroth-hattaavah the people moved on to Hazeroth and remained there.
04Nm 12:1 Miriam and Aaron criticized Moses because of the Cushite woman he married (for he had married a Cushite woman).
04Nm 12:2 They said, "Does the LORD speak only through Moses? Does He not also speak through us?" And the LORD heard [it].
04Nm 12:3 Moses was a very humble man, more so than any man on the face of the earth.
04Nm 12:4 Suddenly the LORD said to Moses, Aaron, and Miriam, "You three come out to the tent of meeting." So the three of them went out.
04Nm 12:5 Then the LORD descended in a pillar of cloud, stood at the entrance to the tent, and summoned Aaron and Miriam. When the two of them came forward,
04Nm 12:6 He said: "Listen to what I say: If there is a prophet among you from the LORD, I make Myself known to him in a vision; I speak with him in a dream.
04Nm 12:7 Not so with My servant Moses; he is faithful in all My household.
04Nm 12:8 I speak with him directly, openly, and not in riddles; he sees the form of the LORD. So why were you not afraid to speak against My servant Moses?"
04Nm 12:9 The Lord's anger burned against them, and He left.
04Nm 12:10 As the cloud moved away from the tent, Miriam's [skin] suddenly became diseased, as [white] as snow. When Aaron turned toward her, he saw that she was diseased
04Nm 12:11 and said to Moses, "My lord, please don't hold against us this sin we have so foolishly committed.
04Nm 12:12 Please don't let her be like a dead [baby] whose flesh is half eaten away when he comes out of his mother's womb."
04Nm 12:13 Then Moses cried out to the LORD, "God, please heal her!"
04Nm 12:14 The LORD answered Moses, "If her father had merely spit in her face, wouldn't she remain in disgrace for seven days? Let her be confined outside the camp for seven days; after that she may be brought back in."
04Nm 12:15 So Miriam was confined outside the camp for seven days, and the people did not move on until Miriam was brought back in.
04Nm 12:16 After that, the people set out from Hazeroth and camped in the Wilderness of Paran.
04Nm 13:1 The LORD spoke to Moses:
04Nm 13:2 "Send men to scout out the land of Canaan I am giving to the Israelites. Send one man who is a leader among them from each of their ancestral tribes."
04Nm 13:3 Moses sent them from the Wilderness of Paran at the LORD's command. All the men were leaders in Israel.
04Nm 13:4 These were their names: Shammua son of Zaccur from the tribe of Reuben;
04Nm 13:5 Shaphat son of Hori from the tribe of Simeon;
04Nm 13:6 Caleb son of Jephunneh from the tribe of Judah;
04Nm 13:7 Igal son of Joseph from the tribe of Issachar;
04Nm 13:8 Hoshea son of Nun from the tribe of Ephraim;
04Nm 13:9 Palti son of Raphu from the tribe of Benjamin;
04Nm 13:10 Gaddiel son of Sodi from the tribe of Zebulun;
04Nm 13:11 Gaddi son of Susi from the tribe of Manasseh (from the tribe of Joseph);
04Nm 13:12 Ammiel son of Gemalli from the tribe of Dan;
04Nm 13:13 Sethur son of Michael from the tribe of Asher;
04Nm 13:14 Nahbi son of Vophsi from the tribe of Naphtali;
04Nm 13:15 Geuel son of Machi from the tribe of Gad.
04Nm 13:16 These were the names of the men Moses sent to scout out the land, and Moses renamed Hoshea son of Nun, Joshua.
04Nm 13:17 When Moses sent them to scout out the land of Canaan, he told them, "Go up this way to the Negev, then go up into the hill country.
04Nm 13:18 See what the land is like, and whether the people who live there are strong or weak, few or many.
04Nm 13:19 Is the land they live in good or bad? Are the cities they live in encampments or fortifications?
04Nm 13:20 Is the land fertile or unproductive? Are there trees in it or not? Be courageous. Bring back some fruit from the land." It was the season for the first ripe grapes.
04Nm 13:21 So they went up and scouted out the land from the Wilderness of Zin as far as Rehob near the entrance to Hamath.
04Nm 13:22 They went up through the Negev and came to Hebron, where Ahiman, Sheshai, and Talmai, the descendants of Anak, were living. Hebron was built seven years before Zoan in Egypt.
04Nm 13:23 When they came to the Valley of Eshcol, they cut down a branch with a single cluster of grapes, which was carried on a pole by two men. [They] also [took] some pomegranates and figs.
04Nm 13:24 That place was called the Valley of Eshcol because of the cluster [of grapes] the Israelites cut there.
04Nm 13:25 At the end of 40 days they returned from scouting out the land.
04Nm 13:26 The men went back to Moses, Aaron, and the entire Israelite community in the Wilderness of Paran at Kadesh. They brought back a report for them and the whole community, and they showed them the fruit of the land.
04Nm 13:27 They reported to Moses: "We went into the land where you sent us. Indeed it is flowing with milk and honey, and here is some of its fruit.
04Nm 13:28 However, the people living in the land are strong, and the cities are large and fortified. We also saw the descendants of Anak there.
04Nm 13:29 The Amalekites are living in the land of the Negev; the Hittites, Jebusites, and Amorites live in the hill country; and the Canaanites live by the sea and along the Jordan."
04Nm 13:30 Then Caleb quieted the people in the presence of Moses and said, "We must go up and take possession of the land because we can certainly conquer it!"
04Nm 13:31 But the men who had gone up with him responded, "We can't go up against the people because they are stronger than we are!"
04Nm 13:32 So they gave a negative report to the Israelites about the land they had scouted: "The land we passed through to explore is one that devours its inhabitants, and all the people we saw in it are men of great size.
04Nm 13:33 We even saw the Nephilim there." (The offspring of Anak were descended from the Nephilim.) "To ourselves we seemed like grasshoppers, and we must have seemed the same to them."
04Nm 14:1 Then the whole community broke into loud cries, and the people wept that night.
04Nm 14:2 All the Israelites complained about Moses and Aaron, and the whole community told them, "If only we had died in the land of Egypt, or if only we had died in this wilderness!
04Nm 14:3 Why is the LORD bringing us into this land to die by the sword? Our wives and little children will become plunder. Wouldn't it be better for us to go back to Egypt?"
04Nm 14:4 So they said to one another, "Let's appoint a leader and go back to Egypt."
04Nm 14:5 Then Moses and Aaron fell down with their faces [to the ground] in front of the whole assembly of the Israelite community.
04Nm 14:6 Joshua son of Nun and Caleb son of Jephunneh, who were among those who scouted out the land, tore their clothes
04Nm 14:7 and said to the entire Israelite community: "The land we passed through and explored is an extremely good land.
04Nm 14:8 If the LORD is pleased with us, He will bring us into this land, a land flowing with milk and honey, and give it to us.
04Nm 14:9 Only don't rebel against the LORD, and don't be afraid of the people of the land, for we will devour them. Their protection has been removed from them, and the LORD is with us. Don't be afraid of them!"
04Nm 14:10 While the whole community threatened to stone them, the glory of the LORD appeared to all the Israelites at the tent of meeting.
04Nm 14:11 The LORD said to Moses, "How long will these people despise Me? How long will they not trust in Me despite all the signs I have performed among them?
04Nm 14:12 I will strike them with a plague and destroy them. Then I will make you into a greater and mightier nation than they are."
04Nm 14:13 But Moses replied to the LORD, "The Egyptians will hear about it, for by Your strength You brought up this people from them.
04Nm 14:14 They will tell [it to] the inhabitants of this land. They have heard that You, LORD, are among these people, how You, Lord, are seen face to face, how Your cloud stands over them, and how You go before them in a pillar of cloud by day and in a pillar of fire by night.
04Nm 14:15 If You kill this people with a single blow, the nations that have heard of Your fame will declare,
04Nm 14:16 'Since the LORD wasn't able to bring this people into the land He swore to [give] them, He has slaughtered them in the wilderness.'
04Nm 14:17 "So now, may My Lord's power be magnified just as You have spoken:
04Nm 14:18 The LORD is slow to anger and rich in faithful love, forgiving wrongdoing and rebellion. But He will not leave [the guilty] unpunished, bringing the consequences of the fathers' wrongdoing on the children to the third and fourth generation.
04Nm 14:19 Please pardon the wrongdoing of this people in keeping with the greatness of Your faithful love, just as You have forgiven them from Egypt until now."
04Nm 14:20 The LORD responded, "I have pardoned [them] as you requested.
04Nm 14:21 Yet as surely as I live and as the whole earth is filled with the LORD's glory,
04Nm 14:22 none of the men who have seen My glory and the signs I performed in Egypt and in the wilderness, and have tested Me these 10 times and did not obey Me,
04Nm 14:23 will ever see the land I swore to [give] their fathers. None of those who have despised Me will see it.
04Nm 14:24 But since My servant Caleb has a different spirit and has followed Me completely, I will bring him into the land where he has gone, and his descendants will inherit it.
04Nm 14:25 Since the Amalekites and Canaanites are living in the lowlands, turn back tomorrow and head for the wilderness in the direction of the Red Sea."
04Nm 14:26 Then the LORD spoke to Moses and Aaron:
04Nm 14:27 "How long [must I endure] this evil community that keeps complaining about Me? I have heard the Israelites' complaints that they make against Me.
04Nm 14:28 Tell them: As surely as I live, declares the LORD, I will do to you exactly as I heard you say.
04Nm 14:29 Your corpses will fall in this wilderness-- all of you who were registered [in the census], the entire number of you 20 years old or more-- because you have complained about Me.
04Nm 14:30 I swear that none of you will enter the land I promised to settle you in, except Caleb son of Jephunneh and Joshua son of Nun.
04Nm 14:31 I will bring your children whom you said would become plunder into the land you rejected, and they will enjoy it.
04Nm 14:32 But as for you, your corpses will fall in this wilderness.
04Nm 14:33 Your children will be shepherds in the wilderness for 40 years and bear the penalty for your acts of unfaithfulness until all your corpses lie [scattered] in the wilderness.
04Nm 14:34 You will bear the consequences of your sins 40 years based on the number of the 40 days that you scouted the land, a year for each day. You will know My displeasure.
04Nm 14:35 I, the LORD, have spoken. I swear that I will do this to the entire evil community that has conspired against Me. They will come to an end in the wilderness, and there they will die."
04Nm 14:36 So the men Moses sent to scout out the land, and who returned and incited the entire community to complain about him by spreading a bad report about the land--
04Nm 14:37 those men who spread the report about the land were struck down by the LORD.
04Nm 14:38 Only Joshua son of Nun and Caleb son of Jephunneh remained alive of those men who went to scout out the land.
04Nm 14:39 When Moses reported these words to all the Israelites, the people were overcome with grief.
04Nm 14:40 They got up early the next morning and went up the ridge of the hill country, saying, "Let's go to the place the LORD promised, for we were wrong."
04Nm 14:41 But Moses responded, "Why are you going against the LORD's command? It won't succeed.
04Nm 14:42 Don't go, because the LORD is not among you and you will be defeated by your enemies.
04Nm 14:43 The Amalekites and Canaanites are right in front of you, and you will fall by the sword. The LORD won't be with you, since you have turned from following Him."
04Nm 14:44 But they dared to go up the ridge of the hill country, even though the ark of the LORD's covenant and Moses did not leave the camp.
04Nm 14:45 Then the Amalekites and Canaanites who lived in that [part of the] hill country came down, attacked them, and routed them as far as Hormah.
04Nm 15:1 The LORD instructed Moses:
04Nm 15:2 "Speak to the Israelites and tell them: When you enter the land I am giving you to settle in,
04Nm 15:3 and you make a fire offering to the LORD from the herd or flock-- either a burnt offering or a sacrifice, to fulfill a vow, or as a freewill offering, or at your appointed festivals-- to produce a pleasing aroma for the LORD,
04Nm 15:4 the one presenting his offering to the LORD must also present a grain offering of two quarts of fine flour mixed with a quart of oil.
04Nm 15:5 Prepare a quart of wine as a drink offering with the burnt offering or sacrifice of each lamb.
04Nm 15:6 "If you prepare a grain offering with a ram, it must be four quarts of fine flour mixed with a third of a gallon of oil.
04Nm 15:7 Also present a third of a gallon of wine for a drink offering as a pleasing aroma to the LORD.
04Nm 15:8 "If you prepare a young bull as a burnt offering or as a sacrifice, to fulfill a vow, or as a fellowship offering to the LORD,
04Nm 15:9 a grain offering of six quarts of fine flour mixed with two quarts of oil must be presented with the bull.
04Nm 15:10 Also present two quarts of wine as a drink offering. It is a fire offering of pleasing aroma to the LORD.
04Nm 15:11 This is to be done for each ox, ram, lamb, or goat.
04Nm 15:12 This is how you must prepare each of them, no matter how many.
04Nm 15:13 "Every Israelite is to prepare these things in this way when he presents a fire offering as a pleasing aroma to the LORD.
04Nm 15:14 When a foreigner resides with you or someone else is among you and wants to prepare a fire offering as a pleasing aroma to the LORD, he is to do exactly as you do throughout your generations.
04Nm 15:15 The assembly is to have the same statute for both you and the foreign resident as a permanent statute throughout your generations. You and the foreigner will be alike before the LORD.
04Nm 15:16 The same law and the same ordinance will apply to both you and the foreigner who resides with you."
04Nm 15:17 The LORD instructed Moses:
04Nm 15:18 "Speak to the Israelites and tell them: After you enter the land where I am bringing you,
04Nm 15:19 you are to offer a contribution to the LORD when you eat from the food of the land.
04Nm 15:20 You are to offer a loaf from your first batch of dough as a contribution; offer it just like a contribution from the threshing floor.
04Nm 15:21 Throughout your generations, you are to give the LORD a contribution from the first batch of your dough.
04Nm 15:22 "When you sin unintentionally and do not obey all these commands that the LORD spoke to Moses--
04Nm 15:23 all that the LORD has commanded you through Moses, from the day the LORD issued the commands and onward throughout your generations--
04Nm 15:24 and if it was done unintentionally without the community's awareness, the entire community is to prepare one young bull for a burnt offering as a pleasing aroma to the Lord, with its grain offering and drink offering according to the regulation, and one male goat as a sin offering.
04Nm 15:25 The priest must then make atonement for the entire Israelite community so that they may be forgiven, for the sin was unintentional. They are to bring their offering, one made by fire to the LORD, and their sin offering before the LORD for their unintentional sin.
04Nm 15:26 The entire Israelite community and the foreigner who resides among them will be forgiven, since it happened to all the people unintentionally.
04Nm 15:27 "If one person sins unintentionally, he is to present a year-old female goat as a sin offering.
04Nm 15:28 The priest must then make atonement before the LORD on behalf of the person who acts in error sinning unintentionally, and when he makes atonement for him, he will be forgiven.
04Nm 15:29 You are to have the same law for the person who acts in error, whether he is an Israelite or a foreigner who lives among you.
04Nm 15:30 "But the person who acts defiantly, whether native or foreign resident, blasphemes the LORD. That person is to be cut off from his people.
04Nm 15:31 He will certainly be cut off, because he has despised the LORD's word and broken His command; his guilt remains on him."
04Nm 15:32 While the Israelites were in the wilderness, they found a man gathering wood on the Sabbath day.
04Nm 15:33 Those who found him gathering wood brought him to Moses, Aaron, and the entire community.
04Nm 15:34 They placed him in custody, because it had not been decided what should be done to him.
04Nm 15:35 Then the LORD told Moses, "The man is to be put to death. The entire community is to stone him outside the camp."
04Nm 15:36 So the entire community brought him outside the camp and stoned him to death, as the LORD had commanded Moses.
04Nm 15:37 The LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 15:38 "Speak to the Israelites and tell them that throughout their generations they are to make tassels for the corners of their garments, and put a blue cord on the tassel at [each] corner.
04Nm 15:39 These will serve as tassels for you to look at, so that you may remember all the LORD's commands and obey them and not become unfaithful by following your own heart and your own eyes.
04Nm 15:40 This way you will remember and obey all My commands and be holy to your God.
04Nm 15:41 I am the LORD your God who brought you out of the land of Egypt to be your God; I am the LORD your God."
04Nm 16:1 Now Korah son of Izhar, son of Kohath, son of Levi, with Dathan and Abiram, sons of Eliab, and On son of Peleth, sons of Reuben, took
04Nm 16:2 250 prominent Israelite men who were leaders of the community and representatives in the assembly, and they rebelled against Moses.
04Nm 16:3 They came together against Moses and Aaron and told them, "You have gone too far! Everyone in the entire community is holy, and the LORD is among them. Why then do you exalt yourselves above the LORD's assembly?"
04Nm 16:4 When Moses heard [this], he fell facedown.
04Nm 16:5 Then he said to Korah and all his followers, "Tomorrow morning the LORD will reveal who belongs to Him, who is set apart, and [the one] He will let come near Him. He will let the one He chooses come near Him.
04Nm 16:6 Korah, you and all your followers are to do this: take firepans, and tomorrow
04Nm 16:7 place fire in them and put incense on them before the LORD. Then the man the LORD chooses will be the one who is set apart. It is you Levites who have gone too far!"
04Nm 16:8 Moses also told Korah, "Now listen, Levites!
04Nm 16:9 Isn't it enough for you that the God of Israel has separated you from the Israelite community to bring you near to Himself, to perform the work at the LORD's tabernacle, and to stand before the community to minister to them?
04Nm 16:10 He has brought you near, and all your fellow Levites who are with you, but you are seeking the priesthood as well.
04Nm 16:11 Therefore, it is you and all your followers who have conspired against the LORD! As for Aaron, who is he that you should complain about him?"
04Nm 16:12 Moses sent for Dathan and Abiram, the sons of Eliab, but they said, "We will not come!
04Nm 16:13 Is it not enough that you brought us up from a land flowing with milk and honey to kill us in the wilderness? Do you also have to appoint yourself as ruler over us?
04Nm 16:14 Furthermore, you didn't bring us to a land flowing with milk and honey or give us an inheritance of fields and vineyards. Will you gouge out the eyes of these men? We will not come!"
04Nm 16:15 Then Moses became angry and said to the LORD, "Don't respect their offering. I have not taken one donkey from them or mistreated a single one of them."
04Nm 16:16 So Moses told Korah, "You and all your followers are to appear before the LORD tomorrow-- you, they, and Aaron.
04Nm 16:17 Each of you is to take his firepan, place incense on it, and present his firepan before the LORD-- 250 firepans. You and Aaron [are] each [to present] your firepan also."
04Nm 16:18 Each man took his firepan, placed fire in it, put incense on it, and stood at the entrance to the tent of meeting along with Moses and Aaron.
04Nm 16:19 After Korah assembled the whole community against them at the entrance to the tent of meeting, the glory of the LORD appeared to the whole community.
04Nm 16:20 The LORD spoke to Moses and Aaron,
04Nm 16:21 "Separate yourselves from this community so I may consume them instantly."
04Nm 16:22 But Moses and Aaron fell facedown and said, "God, God of the spirits of all flesh, when one man sins, will you vent Your wrath on the whole community?"
04Nm 16:23 The LORD replied to Moses,
04Nm 16:24 "Tell the community: Get away from the dwellings of Korah, Dathan, and Abiram."
04Nm 16:25 Moses got up and went to Dathan and Abiram, and the elders of Israel followed him.
04Nm 16:26 He warned the community, "Get away now from the tents of these wicked men. Don't touch anything that belongs to them, or you will be swept away because of all their sins."
04Nm 16:27 So they got away from the dwellings of Korah, Dathan, and Abiram. Meanwhile, Dathan and Abiram came out and stood at the entrance of their tents with their wives, children, and infants.
04Nm 16:28 Then Moses said, "This is how you will know that the LORD sent me to do all these things and that it was not of my own will:
04Nm 16:29 If these men die [naturally] as all people would, and suffer the fate of all, then the LORD has not sent me.
04Nm 16:30 But if the LORD brings about something unprecedented, and the ground opens its mouth and swallows them along with all that belongs to them so that they go down alive into Sheol, then you will know that these men have despised the LORD."
04Nm 16:31 Just as he finished speaking all these words, the ground beneath them split open.
04Nm 16:32 The earth opened its mouth and swallowed them and their households, all Korah's people, and all [their] possessions.
04Nm 16:33 They went down alive into Sheol with all that belonged to them. The earth closed over them, and they vanished from the assembly.
04Nm 16:34 At their cries, all [the people of Israel] who were around them fled because they thought, "The earth may swallow us too!"
04Nm 16:35 Fire also came out from the LORD and consumed the 250 men who were presenting the incense.
04Nm 16:36  Then the LORD spoke to Moses:
04Nm 16:37 "Tell Eleazar son of Aaron the priest to remove the firepans from the burning debris, because they are holy, and scatter the fire far away.
04Nm 16:38 As for the firepans of those who sinned at the cost of their own lives, make them into hammered sheets as plating for the altar, for they presented them before the LORD, and the firepans are holy. They will be a sign to the Israelites."
04Nm 16:39 So Eleazar the priest took the bronze firepans that those who were burned had presented, and they were hammered into plating for the altar,
04Nm 16:40 just as the LORD commanded him through Moses. It was to be a reminder for the Israelites that no unauthorized person outside the lineage of Aaron should approach to offer incense before the LORD and become like Korah and his followers.
04Nm 16:41 The next day the entire Israelite community complained about Moses and Aaron, saying, "You have killed the LORD's people!"
04Nm 16:42 When the community assembled against them, Moses and Aaron turned toward the tent of meeting, and suddenly the cloud covered it, and the LORD's glory appeared.
04Nm 16:43 Moses and Aaron went to the front of the tent of meeting,
04Nm 16:44 and the LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 16:45 "Get away from this community so that I may consume them instantly." But they fell facedown.
04Nm 16:46 Then Moses told Aaron, "Take your firepan, place fire from the altar in it, and add incense. Go quickly to the community and make atonement for them, because wrath has come from the LORD; the plague has begun."
04Nm 16:47 So Aaron took his firepan as Moses had ordered, ran into the middle of the assembly, and saw that the plague had begun among the people. After he added incense, he made atonement for the people.
04Nm 16:48 He stood between the dead and the living, and the plague was halted.
04Nm 16:49 But those who died from the plague numbered 14,700, in addition to those who died because of the Korah incident.
04Nm 16:50 Aaron then returned to Moses at the entrance to the tent of meeting, since the plague had been halted.
04Nm 17:1  The LORD instructed Moses:
04Nm 17:2 "Speak to the Israelites and take one staff from them for each ancestral house, 12 staffs from all the leaders of their ancestral houses. Write each man's name on his staff.
04Nm 17:3 Write Aaron's name on Levi's staff, because there must be one staff for the head of each ancestral house.
04Nm 17:4 Then place them in the tent of meeting in front of the testimony where I meet with you.
04Nm 17:5 The staff of the man I choose will sprout, and I will rid Myself of the Israelites' complaints that they have been making about you."
04Nm 17:6 So Moses spoke to the Israelites, and each of their leaders gave him a staff, one for each of the leaders of their ancestral houses, 12 staffs [in all]. Aaron's staff was among them.
04Nm 17:7 Moses placed the staffs before the LORD in the tent of the testimony.
04Nm 17:8 The next day Moses entered the tent of the testimony and saw that Aaron's staff, representing the house of Levi, had sprouted, formed buds, blossomed, and produced almonds!
04Nm 17:9 Moses then brought out all the staffs from the LORD's presence to all the Israelites. They saw [them], and each man took his own staff.
04Nm 17:10 The LORD told Moses, "Put Aaron's rod back in front of the testimony to be kept as a sign for the rebels, so that you may put an end to their complaints before Me, or else they will die."
04Nm 17:11 So Moses did as the LORD commanded him.
04Nm 17:12 Then the Israelites declared to Moses, "Look, we're perishing! We're lost; we're all lost!
04Nm 17:13 Anyone who comes near the LORD's tabernacle will die. Will we all perish?"
04Nm 18:1 The LORD said to Aaron, "You, your sons, and your ancestral house will be responsible for sin against the sanctuary. You and your sons will be responsible for sin involving your priesthood.
04Nm 18:2 But also bring your brothers with you from the tribe of Levi, your ancestral tribe, so they may join you and serve with you and your sons in front of the tent of the testimony.
04Nm 18:3 They are to perform duties for you and for the whole tent. They must not come near the sanctuary equipment or the altar; otherwise, both they and you will die.
04Nm 18:4 They are to join you and guard the tent of meeting, doing all the work at the tent, but no unauthorized person may come near you.
04Nm 18:5 "You are to guard the sanctuary and the altar so that wrath may not fall on the Israelites again.
04Nm 18:6 Look, I have selected your fellow Levites from the Israelites as a gift for you, assigned by the LORD to work at the tent of meeting.
04Nm 18:7 But you and your sons will carry out your priestly responsibilities for everything concerning the altar and for what is inside the veil, and you will do that work. I am giving you the work of the priesthood as a gift, but an unauthorized person who comes near [the sanctuary] will be put to death."
04Nm 18:8 Then the LORD spoke to Aaron, "Look, I have put you in charge of the contributions brought to Me. As for all the holy offerings of the Israelites, I have given them to you and your sons as a portion and a perpetual statute.
04Nm 18:9 A portion of the holiest offerings [kept] from the fire will be yours; every one of their offerings that they give Me, whether the grain offering, sin offering, or restitution offering will be most holy for you and your sons.
04Nm 18:10 You are to eat it as a most holy offering. Every male may eat it; it is to be holy to you.
04Nm 18:11 "The contribution of their gifts also belongs to you. I have given all the Israelites' presentation offerings to you and to your sons and daughters as a perpetual statute. Every ceremonially clean person in your house may eat it.
04Nm 18:12 I am giving you all the best of the fresh olive oil, new wine, and grain, which the Israelites give to the LORD as their firstfruits.
04Nm 18:13 The firstfruits of all that is in their land, which they bring to the LORD, belong to you. Every clean person in your house may eat them.
04Nm 18:14 "Everything in Israel that is permanently dedicated [to the LORD] belongs to you.
04Nm 18:15 The firstborn of every living thing, man or animal, presented to the LORD belongs to you. But you must certainly redeem the firstborn of man, and redeem the firstborn of an unclean animal.
04Nm 18:16 You will pay the redemption price for a month-old male according to your valuation: five shekels of silver by the standard sanctuary shekel, which is 20 gerahs.
04Nm 18:17 "However, you must not redeem the firstborn of an ox, a sheep, or a goat; they are holy. You are to sprinkle their blood on the altar and burn their fat as a fire offering for a pleasing aroma to the LORD.
04Nm 18:18 But their meat belongs to you. It belongs to you like the breast of the presentation offering and the right thigh.
04Nm 18:19 "I give to you and to your sons and daughters all the holy contributions that the Israelites present to the LORD as a perpetual statute. It is a perpetual covenant of salt before the LORD for you as well as your offspring."
04Nm 18:20 The LORD told Aaron, "You will not have an inheritance in their land; there will be no portion among them for you. I am your portion and your inheritance among the Israelites.
04Nm 18:21 "Look, I have given the Levites every tenth in Israel as an inheritance in return for the work they do, the work of the tent of meeting.
04Nm 18:22 The Israelites must never again come near the tent of meeting, or they will incur guilt and die.
04Nm 18:23 The Levites will do the work of the tent of meeting, and they will bear the [consequences] of their sin. The Levites will not receive an inheritance among the Israelites; this is a perpetual statute throughout your generations.
04Nm 18:24 For I have given them the tenth that the Israelites present to the LORD as a contribution for [their] inheritance. That is why I told them that they would not receive an inheritance among the Israelites."
04Nm 18:25 The LORD instructed Moses,
04Nm 18:26 "Speak to the Levites and tell them: When you receive from the Israelites the tenth that I have given you as your inheritance, you must present part of it as an offering to the LORD-- a tenth of the tenth.
04Nm 18:27 Your offering will be credited to you as if [it were your] grain from the threshing floor or the full harvest from the winepress.
04Nm 18:28 You are to present an offering to the LORD from every tenth you receive from the Israelites. Give some of it to Aaron the priest as an offering to the LORD.
04Nm 18:29 You must present the entire offering due the LORD from all your gifts. The best part of the tenth is to be consecrated.
04Nm 18:30 "Tell them further: Once you have presented the best part of the tenth, and it is credited to you Levites as the produce of the threshing floor or the winepress,
04Nm 18:31 then you and your household may eat it anywhere. It is your wage in return for your work at the tent of meeting.
04Nm 18:32 You will not incur guilt because of it once you have presented the best part of it, but you must not defile the Israelites' holy offerings, so that you will not die."
04Nm 19:1 The LORD spoke to Moses and Aaron,
04Nm 19:2 "This is the legal statute that the LORD has commanded: Instruct the Israelites to bring you an unblemished red cow that has no defect and has never been yoked.
04Nm 19:3 Give it to Eleazar the priest, and he will have it brought outside the camp and slaughtered in his presence.
04Nm 19:4 Eleazar the priest is to take some of its blood with his finger and sprinkle it seven times toward the front of the tent of meeting.
04Nm 19:5 The cow must be burned in his sight. Its hide, flesh, and blood, are to be burned along with its dung.
04Nm 19:6 The priest is to take cedar wood, hyssop, and crimson yarn, and throw [them] onto the fire where the cow is burning.
04Nm 19:7 Then the priest must wash his clothes and bathe his body in water; after that he may enter the camp, but he will remain ceremonially unclean until evening.
04Nm 19:8 The one who burned the cow must also wash his clothes and bathe his body in water, and he will remain unclean until evening.
04Nm 19:9 "A man who is clean is to gather up the cow's ashes and deposit them outside the camp in a ceremonially clean place. The ashes must be kept by the Israelite community for [preparing] the water [to remove] impurity; it is a sin offering.
04Nm 19:10 Then the one who gathers up the cow's ashes must wash his clothes, and he will remain unclean until evening. This is a perpetual statute for the Israelites and for the foreigner who resides among them.
04Nm 19:11 "The person who touches any human corpse will be unclean for seven days.
04Nm 19:12 He is to purify himself with the water on the third day and the seventh day; then he will be clean. But if he does not purify himself on the third and seventh days, he will not be clean.
04Nm 19:13 Anyone who touches a body of a person who has died, and does not purify himself, defiles the tabernacle of the LORD. That person will be cut off from Israel. He remains unclean because the water for impurity has not been sprinkled on him, and his uncleanness is still on him.
04Nm 19:14 "This is the law when a person dies in a tent: everyone who enters the tent and everyone who is [already] in the tent will be unclean for seven days,
04Nm 19:15 and any open container without a lid tied on it is unclean.
04Nm 19:16 Anyone in the open field who touches a person who has been killed by the sword or has died, or a human bone, or a grave, will be unclean for seven days.
04Nm 19:17 For [the purification of] the unclean person, they are to take some of the ashes of the burnt sin offering, [put them] in a jar, and add fresh water to them.
04Nm 19:18 A person who is clean is to take hyssop, dip [it] in the water, and sprinkle the tent, all the furnishings, and the people who were there. He is also to sprinkle the one who touched a bone, a grave, a corpse, or a person who had been killed.
04Nm 19:19 "The one who is clean is to sprinkle the unclean person on the third day and the seventh day. After he purifies the unclean person on the seventh day, the one being purified must wash his clothes and bathe in water, and he will be clean by evening.
04Nm 19:20 But a person who is unclean and does not purify himself, that person will be cut off from the assembly because he has defiled the sanctuary of the LORD. The water for impurity has not been sprinkled on him; he is unclean.
04Nm 19:21 This is a perpetual statute for them. The person who sprinkles the water for impurity is to wash his clothes, and whoever touches the water for impurity will be unclean until evening.
04Nm 19:22 Anything the unclean person touches will become unclean, and anyone who touches [it] will be unclean until evening."
04Nm 20:1 The entire Israelite community entered the Wilderness of Zin in the first month, and they settled in Kadesh. Miriam died and was buried there.
04Nm 20:2 There was no water for the community, so they assembled against Moses and Aaron.
04Nm 20:3 The people quarreled with Moses and said, "If only we had perished when our brothers perished before the LORD.
04Nm 20:4 Why have you brought the LORD's assembly into this wilderness for us and our livestock to die here?
04Nm 20:5 Why have you led us up from Egypt to bring us to this evil place? It's not a place of grain, figs, vines, and pomegranates, and there is no water to drink!"
04Nm 20:6 Then Moses and Aaron went from the presence of the assembly to the doorway of the tent of meeting. They fell down with their faces [to the ground], and the glory of the LORD appeared to them.
04Nm 20:7 The LORD spoke to Moses,
04Nm 20:8 "Take the staff and assemble the community. You and your brother Aaron are to speak to the rock while they watch, and it will yield its water. You will bring out water for them from the rock and provide drink for the community and their livestock."
04Nm 20:9 So Moses took the staff from the LORD's presence just as He had commanded him.
04Nm 20:10 Moses and Aaron summoned the assembly in front of the rock, and Moses said to them, "Listen, you rebels! Must we bring water out of this rock for you?"
04Nm 20:11 Then Moses raised his hand and struck the rock twice with his staff, so that a great amount of water gushed out, and the community and their livestock drank.
04Nm 20:12 But the LORD said to Moses and Aaron, "Because you did not trust Me to show My holiness in the sight of the Israelites, you will not bring this assembly into the land I have given them."
04Nm 20:13 These are the waters of Meribah, where the Israelites quarreled with the LORD, and He showed His holiness to them.
04Nm 20:14 Moses sent messengers from Kadesh to the king of Edom, "This is what your brother Israel says, 'You know all the hardships that have overtaken us.
04Nm 20:15 Our fathers went down to Egypt, and we lived in Egypt many years, but the Egyptians treated us and our fathers badly.
04Nm 20:16 When we cried out to the LORD, He heard our voice, sent an Angel, and brought us out of Egypt. Now look, we are in Kadesh, a city on the border of your territory.
04Nm 20:17 Please let us travel through your land. We won't travel through [any] field or vineyard, or drink [any] well water. We will travel the King's Highway; we won't turn to the right or the left until we have traveled through your territory.'"
04Nm 20:18 But Edom answered him, "You must not travel through our land, or we will come out and confront you with the sword."
04Nm 20:19 "We will go on the main road," the Israelites replied to them, "and if we or our herds drink your water, we will pay its price. There will be no problem; only let us travel through on foot."
04Nm 20:20 Yet Edom insisted, "You must not travel through." And they came out to confront them with a large force of heavily-armed people.
04Nm 20:21 Edom refused to allow Israel to travel through their territory, and Israel turned away from them.
04Nm 20:22 After they set out from Kadesh, the entire Israelite community came to Mount Hor.
04Nm 20:23 The LORD said to Moses and Aaron at Mount Hor on the border of the land of Edom,
04Nm 20:24 "Aaron will be gathered to his people; he will not enter the land I have given the Israelites, because you both rebelled against My command at the waters of Meribah.
04Nm 20:25 Take Aaron and his son Eleazar and bring them up Mount Hor.
04Nm 20:26 Remove Aaron's garments and put them on his son Eleazar. Aaron will be gathered [to his people] and die there."
04Nm 20:27 So Moses did as the LORD commanded, and they climbed Mount Hor in the sight of the whole community.
04Nm 20:28 After Moses removed Aaron's garments and put them on his son Eleazar, Aaron died there on top of the mountain. Then Moses and Eleazar came down from the mountain.
04Nm 20:29 When the whole community saw that Aaron had passed away, the entire house of Israel mourned for him 30 days.
04Nm 21:1 When the Canaanite king of Arad, who lived in the Negev, heard that Israel was coming on the Atharim road, he fought against Israel and captured some prisoners.
04Nm 21:2 Then Israel made a vow to the LORD, "If You will deliver this people into our hands, we will completely destroy their cities."
04Nm 21:3 The LORD listened to Israel's request, the Canaanites were defeated, and Israel completely destroyed them and their cities. So they named the place Hormah.
04Nm 21:4 Then they set out from Mount Hor by way of the Red Sea to bypass the land of Edom, but the people became impatient because of the journey.
04Nm 21:5 The people spoke against God and Moses: "Why have you led us up from Egypt to die in the wilderness? There is no bread or water, and we detest this wretched food!"
04Nm 21:6 Then the LORD sent poisonous snakes among the people, and they bit them so that many Israelites died.
04Nm 21:7 The people then came to Moses and said, "We have sinned by speaking against the LORD and against you. Intercede with the LORD so that He will take the snakes away from us." And Moses interceded for the people.
04Nm 21:8 Then the LORD said to Moses, "Make a snake [image] and mount it on a pole. When anyone who is bitten looks at it, he will recover.
04Nm 21:9 So Moses made a bronze snake and mounted it on a pole. Whenever someone was bitten, and he looked at the bronze snake, he recovered.
04Nm 21:10 The Israelites set out and camped at Oboth.
04Nm 21:11 They set out from Oboth and camped at Iye-abarim in the wilderness that borders Moab on the east.
04Nm 21:12 From there they went and camped at Zered Valley.
04Nm 21:13 They set out from there and camped on the other side of the Arnon [River], in the wilderness that extends from the Amorite border, because the Arnon was the Moabite border between Moab and the Amorites.
04Nm 21:14 Therefore it is stated in the Book of the LORD's Wars: Waheb in Suphah and the ravines of the Arnon,
04Nm 21:15 even the slopes of the ravines that extend to the site of Ar and lie along the border of Moab.
04Nm 21:16 From there [they went] to Beer, the well the LORD told Moses about, "Gather the people so I may give them water."
04Nm 21:17 Then Israel sang this song: Spring up, well-- sing to it!
04Nm 21:18 The princes dug the well; The nobles of the people hollowed it out with a scepter and with their staffs. [They went] from the wilderness to Mattanah,
04Nm 21:19 from Mattanah to Nahaliel, from Nahaliel to Bamoth,
04Nm 21:20 from Bamoth to the valley in the territory of Moab near the Pisgah highlands that overlook the wasteland.
04Nm 21:21 Israel sent messengers to say to Sihon king of the Amorites:
04Nm 21:22 "Let us travel through your land. We won't go into the fields or vineyards. We won't drink [any] well water. We will travel the King's Highway until we have traveled through your territory."
04Nm 21:23 But Sihon would not let Israel travel through his territory. Instead, he gathered his whole army and went out to confront Israel in the wilderness. When he came to Jahaz, he fought against Israel.
04Nm 21:24 Israel struck him with the sword and took possession of his land from the Arnon to the Jabbok, [but only up] to the Ammonite border, because it was fortified.
04Nm 21:25 Israel took all the cities and lived in all these Amorite cities, including Heshbon and all its villages.
04Nm 21:26 Heshbon was the city of Sihon king of the Amorites, who had fought against the former king of Moab and had taken control of all his land as far as the Arnon.
04Nm 21:27 Therefore the poets say: Come to Heshbon, let it be rebuilt; let the city of Sihon be restored.
04Nm 21:28 For fire came out of Heshbon, a flame from the city of Sihon. It consumed Ar of Moab, the lords of Arnon's heights.
04Nm 21:29 Woe to you, Moab! You have been destroyed, people of Chemosh! He gave up his sons as refugees, and his daughters into captivity to Sihon the Amorite king.
04Nm 21:30 We threw them down; Heshbon has been destroyed as far as Dibon. We caused desolation as far as Nophah, which reaches as far as Medeba.
04Nm 21:31 So Israel lived in the Amorites' land.
04Nm 21:32 After Moses sent spies to Jazer, Israel captured its villages and drove out the Amorites who were there.
04Nm 21:33 Then they turned and went up the road to Bashan, and Og king of Bashan came out against them with his whole army to do battle at Edrei.
04Nm 21:34 But the LORD said to Moses, "Do not fear him, for I have handed him over to you along with his whole army and his land. Do to him as you did to Sihon king of the Amorites, who lived in Heshbon."
04Nm 21:35 So they struck him, his sons, and his whole army until no one was left, and they took possession of his land.
04Nm 22:1 The Israelites traveled on and camped in the plains of Moab near the Jordan across from Jericho.
04Nm 22:2 Now Balak son of Zippor saw all that Israel had done to the Amorites.
04Nm 22:3 Moab was terrified of the people because they were numerous, and dreaded the Israelites.
04Nm 22:4 So the Moabites said to the elders of Midian, "This horde will devour everything around us like an ox eats up the green plants in the field." Since Balak son of Zippor was Moab's king at that time,
04Nm 22:5 he sent messengers to Balaam son of Beor at Pethor, which is by the Euphrates in the land of his people. Balak said to him: "Look, a people has come out of Egypt; they cover the surface of the land and are living right across from me.
04Nm 22:6 Please come and put a curse on these people for me because they are more powerful than I am. I may be able to defeat them and drive them out of the land, for I know that those you bless are blessed and those you curse are cursed."
04Nm 22:7 The elders of Moab and Midian departed with fees for divination in hand. They came to Balaam and reported Balak's words to him.
04Nm 22:8 He said to them, "Spend the night here, and I will give you the answer the LORD tells me." So the officials of Moab stayed with Balaam.
04Nm 22:9 Then God came to Balaam and asked, "Who are these men with you?"
04Nm 22:10 Balaam replied to God, "Balak son of Zippor, king of Moab, sent [this message] to me:
04Nm 22:11 'Look, a people has come out of Egypt, and they cover the surface of the land. Now come and put a curse on them for me. I may be able to fight against them and drive them away.'"
04Nm 22:12 Then God said to Balaam, "You are not to go with them. You are not to curse this people, for they are blessed."
04Nm 22:13 So Balaam got up the next morning and said to Balak's officials, "Go back to your land, because the LORD has refused to let me go with you."
04Nm 22:14 The officials of Moab arose, returned to Balak, and reported, "Balaam refused to come with us."
04Nm 22:15 Balak sent officials again who were more numerous and higher in rank than the others.
04Nm 22:16 They came to Balaam and said to him, "This is what Balak son of Zippor says: 'Let nothing keep you from coming to me,
04Nm 22:17 for I will greatly honor you and do whatever you ask me. So please come and put a curse on these people for me!'"
04Nm 22:18 But Balaam responded to the servants of Balak, "If Balak were to give me his house full of silver and gold, I could not go against the command of the LORD my God to do [anything] small or great.
04Nm 22:19 Please stay here overnight as the others did, so that I may find out what else the LORD has to tell me."
04Nm 22:20 God came to Balaam at night and said to him, "Since these men have come to summon you, get up and go with them, but you must only do what I tell you."
04Nm 22:21 When he got up in the morning, Balaam saddled his donkey and went with the officials of Moab.
04Nm 22:22 But God was incensed that Balaam was going, and the Angel of the LORD took His stand on the path to oppose him. Balaam was riding his donkey, and his two servants were with him.
04Nm 22:23 When the donkey saw the Angel of the LORD standing on the path with a drawn sword in His hand, she turned off the path and went into the field. So Balaam hit her to return her to the path.
04Nm 22:24 Then the Angel of the LORD stood in a narrow passage between the vineyards, with a stone wall on either side.
04Nm 22:25 The donkey saw the Angel of the LORD and pressed herself against the wall, squeezing Balaam's foot against it. So he hit her once again.
04Nm 22:26 The Angel of the LORD went ahead and stood in a narrow place where there was no room to turn to the right or the left.
04Nm 22:27 When the donkey saw the Angel of the LORD, she crouched down under Balaam. So he became furious and beat the donkey with his stick.
04Nm 22:28 Then the LORD opened the donkey's mouth, and she asked Balaam, "What have I done to you that you have beaten me these three times?"
04Nm 22:29 Balaam answered the donkey, "You made me look like a fool. If I had a sword in my hand, I'd kill you now!"
04Nm 22:30 But the donkey said, "Am I not the donkey you've ridden all your life until today? Have I ever treated you this way before?" "No," he replied.
04Nm 22:31 Then the LORD opened Balaam's eyes, and he saw the Angel of the LORD standing in the path with a drawn sword in His hand. Balaam knelt and bowed with his face [to the ground].
04Nm 22:32 The Angel of the LORD asked him, "Why have you beaten your donkey these three times? Look, I came out to oppose you, because what you are doing is evil in My sight.
04Nm 22:33 The donkey saw Me and turned away from Me these three times. If she had not turned away from Me, I would have killed you by now and let her live."
04Nm 22:34 Balaam said to the Angel of the LORD, "I have sinned, for I did not know that You were standing in the path to confront me. And now, if it is evil in Your sight, I will go back."
04Nm 22:35 Then the Angel of the LORD said to Balaam, "Go with the men, but you are to say only what I tell you." So Balaam went with Balak's officials.
04Nm 22:36 When Balak heard that Balaam was coming, he went out to meet him at the Moabite city on the Arnon border at the edge of his territory.
04Nm 22:37 Balak asked Balaam, "Did I not send you an urgent summons? Why didn't you come to me? Am I really not able to reward you?"
04Nm 22:38 Balaam said to him, "Look, I have come to you, but can I say anything I want? I must speak only the message God puts in my mouth."
04Nm 22:39 So Balaam went with Balak, and they came to Kiriath-huzoth.
04Nm 22:40 Balak sacrificed cattle and sheep, and sent for Balaam and the officials who were with him.
04Nm 22:41 In the morning, Balak took Balaam and brought him to Bamoth-baal. From there he saw the outskirts of the people's camp.
04Nm 23:1 Then Balaam said to Balak, "Build me seven altars here and prepare seven bulls and seven rams for me."
04Nm 23:2 So Balak did as Balaam directed, and they offered a bull and a ram on each altar.
04Nm 23:3 Balaam said to Balak, "Stay here by your burnt offering while I am gone. Maybe the LORD will meet with me. I will tell you whatever He reveals to me." So he went to a barren hill.
04Nm 23:4 God met with him and Balaam said to Him, "I have arranged seven altars and offered a bull and a ram on each altar."
04Nm 23:5 Then the LORD put a message in Balaam's mouth and said, "Return to Balak and say what I tell you."
04Nm 23:6 So he returned to Balak, who was standing there by his burnt offering with all the officials of Moab.
04Nm 23:7 Balaam proclaimed his poem: Balak brought me from Aram; the king of Moab, from the eastern mountains: "Come, put a curse on Jacob for me; come, denounce Israel!"
04Nm 23:8 How can I curse someone God has not cursed? How can I denounce someone the LORD has not denounced?
04Nm 23:9 I see them from the top of rocky cliffs, and I watch them from the hills. There is a people living alone; it does not consider itself among the nations.
04Nm 23:10 Who has counted the dust of Jacob or numbered the dust clouds of Israel? Let me die the death of the upright; let the end of my [life] be like theirs.
04Nm 23:11 "What have you done to me?" Balak asked Balaam. "I brought you to curse my enemies, but look, you have only blessed [them]!"
04Nm 23:12 He answered, "Shouldn't I say exactly what the LORD puts in my mouth?"
04Nm 23:13 Then Balak said to him, "Please come with me to another place where you can see them. You will only see the outskirts of their camp; you won't see all of them. From there, put a curse on them for me."
04Nm 23:14 So Balak took him to Lookout Field on top of Pisgah, built seven altars, and offered a bull and a ram on each altar.
04Nm 23:15 Balaam said to Balak, "Stay here by your burnt offering while I seek [the LORD] over there."
04Nm 23:16 The LORD met with Balaam and put a message in his mouth. Then He said, "Return to Balak and say what I tell you."
04Nm 23:17 So he returned to Balak, who was standing there by his burnt offering with the officials of Moab. Balak asked him, "What did the LORD say?"
04Nm 23:18 Balaam proclaimed his poem: Balak, get up and listen; son of Zippor, pay attention to what I say!
04Nm 23:19 God is not a man who lies, or a son of man who changes His mind. Does He speak and not act, or promise and not fulfill?
04Nm 23:20 I have indeed received [a command] to bless; since He has blessed, I cannot change it.
04Nm 23:21 He considers no disaster for Jacob; He sees no trouble for Israel. The LORD their God is with them, and there is rejoicing over the King among them.
04Nm 23:22 God brought them out of Egypt; He is like the horns of a wild ox for them.
04Nm 23:23 There is no magic curse against Jacob and no divination against Israel. It will now be said about Jacob and Israel, "What [great things] God has done!"
04Nm 23:24 A people rise up like a lioness; They rouse themselves like a lion. They will not lie down until they devour the prey and drink the blood of the slain.
04Nm 23:25 Then Balak told Balaam, "Don't curse them and don't bless them!"
04Nm 23:26 But Balaam answered him, "Didn't I tell you: Whatever the LORD says, I must do?"
04Nm 23:27 Again Balak said to Balaam, "Please come. I will take you to another place. Maybe it will be agreeable to God that you can put a curse on them for me there."
04Nm 23:28 So Balak took Balaam to the top of Peor, which overlooks the wasteland.
04Nm 23:29 Balaam told Balak, "Build me seven altars here and prepare seven bulls and seven rams for me."
04Nm 23:30 So Balak did as Balaam said and offered a bull and a ram on each altar.
04Nm 24:1 Since Balaam saw that it pleased the LORD to bless Israel, he did not go to seek omens as on previous occasions, but turned toward the wilderness.
04Nm 24:2 When Balaam looked up and saw Israel encamped tribe by tribe, the Spirit of God descended on him,
04Nm 24:3 and he proclaimed his poem: The oracle of Balaam son of Beor, the oracle of the man whose eyes are opened,
04Nm 24:4 the oracle of one who hears the sayings of God, who sees a vision from the Almighty, who falls [into a trance] with [his] eyes uncovered:
04Nm 24:5 How beautiful are your tents, Jacob, your dwellings, Israel.
04Nm 24:6 they stretch out like river valleys, like gardens beside a stream, like aloes the LORD has planted, like cedars beside the water.
04Nm 24:7 Water will flow from his buckets, and his seed will be by abundant water. His king will be greater than Agag, and his kingdom will be exalted.
04Nm 24:8 God brought him out of Egypt; He is like the horns of a wild ox for them. He will feed on enemy nations and gnaw their bones; he will strike [them] with his arrows.
04Nm 24:9 He crouches, he lies down like a lion or a lioness-- who dares to rouse him? Those who bless you will be blessed, and those who curse you will be cursed.
04Nm 24:10 Then Balak became furious with Balaam, struck his hands together, and said to him, "I summoned you to put a curse on my enemies, but instead, you have blessed [them these three times].
04Nm 24:11 Now go to your home! I said I would reward you richly, but look, the LORD has denied you a reward."
04Nm 24:12 Balaam answered Balak, "Didn't I previously tell the messengers you sent me:
04Nm 24:13 If Balak were to give me his house full of silver and gold, I could not go against the LORD's command, to do [anything] good or bad of my own will? I will say whatever the LORD says.
04Nm 24:14 Now I am going back to my people, but first, let me warn you what these people will do to your people in the future."
04Nm 24:15 Then he proclaimed his poem: The oracle of Balaam son of Beor, the oracle of the man whose eyes are opened;
04Nm 24:16 the oracle of one who hears the sayings of God and has knowledge from the Most High, who sees a vision from the Almighty, who falls [into a trance] with [his] eyes uncovered:
04Nm 24:17 I see him, but not now; I perceive him, but not near. A star will come from Jacob, and a scepter will arise from Israel. He will smash the forehead of Moab and strike down all the Shethites.
04Nm 24:18 Edom will become a possession; Seir will become a possession of its enemies, but Israel will be triumphant.
04Nm 24:19 One who comes from Jacob will rule; he will destroy the city's survivors.
04Nm 24:20 Then Balaam saw Amalek and proclaimed his poem: Amalek was first among the nations, but his future is destruction.
04Nm 24:21 Next he saw the Kenites and proclaimed his poem: Your dwelling place is enduring; your nest is set in the cliffs.
04Nm 24:22 Kain will be destroyed when Asshur takes you captive.
04Nm 24:23 Once more he proclaimed his poem: Ah, who can live when God does this?
04Nm 24:24 Ships will come from the coast of Kittim; they will afflict Asshur and Eber, but they too will come to destruction.
04Nm 24:25 Balaam then arose and went back to his homeland, and Balak also went his way.
04Nm 25:1 While Israel was staying in Acacia Grove, the people began to have sexual relations with the women of Moab.
04Nm 25:2 The women invited them to the sacrifices for their gods, and the people ate and bowed in worship to their gods.
04Nm 25:3 So Israel aligned itself with Baal of Peor, and the LORD's anger burned against Israel.
04Nm 25:4 The LORD said to Moses, "Take all the leaders of the people and execute them in broad daylight before the LORD so that His burning anger may turn away from Israel."
04Nm 25:5 So Moses told Israel's judges, "Kill each of the men who aligned themselves with Baal of Peor."
04Nm 25:6 An Israelite man came bringing a Midianite woman to his relatives in the sight of Moses and the whole Israelite community while they were weeping at the entrance to the tent of meeting.
04Nm 25:7 When Phinehas son of Eleazar, son of Aaron the priest, saw [this], he got up from the assembly, took a spear in his hand,
04Nm 25:8 followed the Israelite man into the tent, and drove it through both the Israelite man and the woman-- through her belly. Then the plague on the Israelites was stopped,
04Nm 25:9 but those who died in the plague numbered 24,000.
04Nm 25:10 The LORD spoke to Moses,
04Nm 25:11 "Phinehas son of Eleazar, son of Aaron the priest, has turned back My wrath from the Israelites because he was zealous among them with My zeal, so that I did not destroy the Israelites in My zeal.
04Nm 25:12 Therefore declare: I grant him My covenant of peace.
04Nm 25:13 It will be a covenant of perpetual priesthood for him and his descendants, because he was zealous for his God and made atonement for the Israelites."
04Nm 25:14 The name of the slain Israelite man, who was struck dead with the Midianite woman, was Zimri son of Salu, the leader of a Simeonite ancestral house.
04Nm 25:15 The name of the slain Midianite woman was Cozbi, the daughter of Zur, a tribal head of an ancestral house in Midian.
04Nm 25:16 The LORD told Moses:
04Nm 25:17 "Attack the Midianites and strike them dead.
04Nm 25:18 For they attacked you with the treachery that they used against you in the Peor incident. They did the same in the case involving their sister Cozbi, daughter of the Midianite leader who was killed the day the plague came at Peor."
04Nm 26:1 After the plague, the LORD said to Moses and Eleazar son of Aaron the priest,
04Nm 26:2 "Take a census of the entire Israelite community by their ancestral houses of those 20 years old or more who can serve in Israel's army."
04Nm 26:3 So Moses and Eleazar the priest said to them in the plains of Moab by the Jordan [across from] Jericho,
04Nm 26:4 "[Take a census of] those 20 years old or more, as the LORD had commanded Moses and the Israelites who came out of the land of Egypt."
04Nm 26:5 Reuben was the firstborn of Israel. Reuben's descendants: the Hanochite clan [from] Hanoch; the Palluite clan from Pallu;
04Nm 26:6 the Hezronite clan from Hezron; the Carmite clan from Carmi.
04Nm 26:7 These were the Reubenite clans, and their registered men numbered 43,730.
04Nm 26:8 The son of Pallu was Eliab.
04Nm 26:9 The sons of Eliab were Nemuel, Dathan, and Abiram. (It was Dathan and Abiram, chosen by the community, who fought against Moses and Aaron; they and Korah's followers fought against the LORD.
04Nm 26:10 The earth opened its mouth and swallowed them with Korah, when his followers died and the fire consumed 250 men. They [serve as] a warning sign.
04Nm 26:11 The sons of Korah, however, did not die.)
04Nm 26:12 Simeon's descendants by their clans: the Nemuelite clan from Nemuel; the Jaminite clan from Jamin; the Jachinite clan from Jachin;
04Nm 26:13 the Zerahite clan from Zerah; the Shaulite clan from Shaul.
04Nm 26:14 These were the Simeonite clans, numbering 22,200 men.
04Nm 26:15 Gad's descendants by their clans: the Zephonite clan from Zephon; the Haggite clan from Haggi; the Shunite clan from Shuni;
04Nm 26:16 the Oznite clan from Ozni; the Erite clan from Eri;
04Nm 26:17 the Arodite clan from Arod; the Arelite clan from Areli.
04Nm 26:18 These were the Gadite clans [numbered] by their registered men: 40,500.
04Nm 26:19 Judah's sons included Er and Onan, but they died in the land of Canaan.
04Nm 26:20 Judah's descendants by their clans: the Shelanite clan from Shelah; the Perezite clan from Perez; the Zerahite clan from Zerah.
04Nm 26:21 The descendants of Perez: the Hezronite clan from Hezron; the Hamulite clan from Hamul.
04Nm 26:22 These were Judah's clans [numbered] by their registered men: 76,500.
04Nm 26:23 Issachar's descendants by their clans: the Tolaite clan from Tola; the Punite clan from Puvah;
04Nm 26:24 the Jashubite clan from Jashub; the Shimronite clan from Shimron.
04Nm 26:25 These were Issachar's clans [numbered] by their registered men: 64,300.
04Nm 26:26 Zebulun's descendants by their clans: the Seredite clan from Sered; the Elonite clan from Elon; the Jahleelite clan from Jahleel.
04Nm 26:27 These were the Zebulunite clans [numbered] by their registered men: 60,500.
04Nm 26:28 Joseph's descendants by their clans [from] Manasseh and Ephraim:
04Nm 26:29 Manasseh's descendants: the Machirite clan from Machir. Machir fathered Gilead; the Gileadite clan from Gilead.
04Nm 26:30 These were Gilead's descendants: the Iezerite clan [from] Iezer; the Helekite clan from Helek;
04Nm 26:31 The Asrielite clan [from] Asriel; the Shechemite clan [from] Shechem;
04Nm 26:32 the Shemidaite clan [from] Shemida; the Hepherite clan [from] Hepher;
04Nm 26:33 Zelophehad son of Hepher had no sons-- only daughters. The names of Zelophehad's daughters were Mahlah, Noah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Tirzah.
04Nm 26:34 These were Manasseh's clans, numbered by their registered men: 52,700.
04Nm 26:35 These were Ephraim's descendants by their clans: the Shuthelahite clan from Shuthelah; the Becherite clan from Becher; the Tahanite clan from Tahan.
04Nm 26:36 These were Shuthelah's descendants: the Eranite clan from Eran.
04Nm 26:37 These were the Ephraimite clans [numbered] by their registered men: 32,500. These were Joseph's descendants by their clans.
04Nm 26:38 Benjamin's descendants by their clans: the Belaite clan from Bela; the Ashbelite clan from Ashbel; the Ahiramite clan from Ahiram;
04Nm 26:39 the Shuphamite clan from Shupham; the Huphamite clan from Hupham.
04Nm 26:40 Bela's descendants [from] Ard and Naaman: the Ardite clan [from] Ard; the Naamite clan from Naaman.
04Nm 26:41 These were the Benjaminite clans numbered by their registered men: 45,600.
04Nm 26:42 These were Dan's descendants by their clans: the Shuhamite clan from Shuham. These were the clans of Dan by their clans.
04Nm 26:43 All the Shuhamite clans [numbered] by their registered men were 64,400.
04Nm 26:44 Asher's descendants by their clans: the Imnite clan from Imnah; the Ishvite clan from Ishvi; the Beriite clan from Beriah.
04Nm 26:45 From Beriah's descendants: the Heberite clan from Heber; the Malchielite clan from Malchiel.
04Nm 26:46 And the name of Asher's daughter was Serah.
04Nm 26:47 These were the Asherite clans [numbered] by their registered men: 53,400.
04Nm 26:48 Naphtali's descendants by their clans: the Jahzeelite clan from Jahzeel; the Gunite clan from Guni;
04Nm 26:49 the Jezerite clan from Jezer; the Shillemite clan from Shillem.
04Nm 26:50 These were the Naphtali clans numbered by their registered men: 45,400.
04Nm 26:51 These registered Israelite men numbered 601,730.
04Nm 26:52 The LORD spoke to Moses,
04Nm 26:53 "The land is to be divided among them as an inheritance based on the number of names.
04Nm 26:54 Increase the inheritance for a large [tribe], and decrease it for a small one. Each is to be given its inheritance according to those who were registered in it.
04Nm 26:55 The land must be divided by lot; they will receive an inheritance according to the names of their ancestral tribes.
04Nm 26:56 Each inheritance will be divided by lot among the larger and smaller [tribes]."
04Nm 26:57 These were the Levites registered by their clans: the Gershonite clan from Gershon; the Kohathite clan from Kohath; the Merarite clan from Merari.
04Nm 26:58 These were the Levite family groups: the Libnite clan, the Hebronite clan, the Mahlite clan, the Mushite clan, and the Korahite clan. Kohath was the ancestor of Amram.
04Nm 26:59 The name of Amram's wife was Jochebed, a descendant of Levi, born to Levi in Egypt. She bore to Amram: Aaron, Moses, and their sister Miriam.
04Nm 26:60 Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar were born to Aaron,
04Nm 26:61 but Nadab and Abihu died when they presented unauthorized fire before the LORD.
04Nm 26:62 Those registered were 23,000, every male one month old or more; they were not registered among the [other] Israelites, because no inheritance was given to them among the Israelites.
04Nm 26:63 These were the ones registered by Moses and Eleazar the priest when they registered the Israelites on the plains of Moab by the Jordan [across from] Jericho.
04Nm 26:64 But among them there was not one of those who had been registered by Moses and Aaron the priest when they registered the Israelites in the Wilderness of Sinai.
04Nm 26:65 For the LORD had said to them that they would all die in the wilderness. None of them was left except Caleb son of Jephunneh and Joshua son of Nun.
04Nm 27:1 The daughters of Zelophehad approached; [Zelophehad was the] son of Hepher, son of Gilead, son of Machir, son of Manasseh from the clans of Manasseh, the son of Joseph. These were the names of his daughters: Mahlah, Noah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Tirzah.
04Nm 27:2 They stood before Moses, Eleazar the priest, the leaders, and the entire community at the entrance to the tent of meeting and said,
04Nm 27:3 "Our father died in the wilderness, but he was not among Korah's followers, who gathered together against the LORD. Instead, he died because of his own sin, and he had no sons.
04Nm 27:4 Why should the name of our father be taken away from his clan? Since he had no son, give us property among our father's brothers."
04Nm 27:5 Moses brought their case before the LORD,
04Nm 27:6 and the LORD answered him,
04Nm 27:7 "What Zelophehad's daughters say is correct. You are to give them hereditary property among their father's brothers and transfer their father's inheritance to them.
04Nm 27:8 Tell the Israelites: When a man dies without having a son, transfer his inheritance to his daughter.
04Nm 27:9 If he has no daughter, give his inheritance to his brothers.
04Nm 27:10 If he has no brothers, give his inheritance to his father's brothers.
04Nm 27:11 If his father has no brothers, give his inheritance to the nearest relative of his clan, and he will take possession of it. This is to be a statutory ordinance for the Israelites as the LORD commanded Moses."
04Nm 27:12 Then the LORD said to Moses, "Go up this mountain of the Abarim [range] and see the land that I have given the Israelites.
04Nm 27:13 After you have seen it, you will also be gathered to your people, as Aaron your brother was.
04Nm 27:14 When the community quarreled in the Wilderness of Zin, both of you rebelled against My command to show My holiness in their sight at the waters." Those were the waters of Meribah of Kadesh in the Wilderness of Zin.
04Nm 27:15 So Moses appealed to the LORD,
04Nm 27:16 "May the LORD, the God of the spirits of all flesh, appoint a man over the community
04Nm 27:17 who will go out before them and come back in before them, and who will bring them out and bring them in, so that the LORD's community won't be like sheep without a shepherd."
04Nm 27:18 The LORD replied to Moses, "Take Joshua son of Nun, a man who has the Spirit in him, and lay your hands on him.
04Nm 27:19 Have him stand before Eleazar the priest and the whole community, and commission him in their sight.
04Nm 27:20 Confer some of your authority on him so that the entire Israelite community will obey [him].
04Nm 27:21 He will stand before Eleazar who will consult the LORD for him with the decision of the Urim. He and all the Israelites with him, even the entire community, will go out and come back in at his command."
04Nm 27:22 Moses did as the LORD commanded him. He took Joshua, had him stand before Eleazar the priest and the entire community,
04Nm 27:23 laid his hands on him, and commissioned him, as the LORD had spoken through Moses.
04Nm 28:1 The LORD spoke to Moses,
04Nm 28:2 "Command the Israelites and say to them: Be sure to present to Me at its appointed time My offering and My food as My fire offering, a pleasing aroma to Me.
04Nm 28:3 And say to them: This is the fire offering you are to present to the LORD: "Each day [present] two unblemished year-old male lambs as a regular burnt offering.
04Nm 28:4 Offer one lamb in the morning and the other lamb at twilight,
04Nm 28:5 along with two quarts of fine flour for a grain offering mixed with a quart of beaten olive oil.
04Nm 28:6 It is a regular burnt offering established at Mount Sinai for a pleasing aroma, a fire offering to the LORD.
04Nm 28:7 The drink offering is to be a quart with each lamb. Pour out the offering of beer to the LORD in the sanctuary area.
04Nm 28:8 Offer the second lamb at twilight, along with the same kind of grain offering and drink offering as in the morning. It is a fire offering, a pleasing aroma to the LORD.
04Nm 28:9 "On the Sabbath day [present] two unblemished year-old male lambs, four quarts of fine flour mixed with oil as a grain offering, and its drink offering.
04Nm 28:10 It is the burnt offering for every Sabbath, in addition to the regular burnt offering and its drink offering.
04Nm 28:11 "At the beginning of each of your months present a burnt offering to the LORD: two young bulls, one ram, seven male lambs a year old-- [all] unblemished--
04Nm 28:12 with six quarts of fine flour mixed with oil as a grain offering for each bull, four quarts of fine flour mixed with oil as a grain offering for the ram,
04Nm 28:13 and two quarts of fine flour mixed with oil as a grain offering for each lamb. It is a burnt offering, a pleasing aroma, a fire offering to the LORD.
04Nm 28:14 Their drink offerings are to be two quarts of wine with each bull, one and a third quarts with the ram, and one quart with each male lamb. This is the monthly burnt offering for all the months of the year.
04Nm 28:15 And one male goat is to be offered as a sin offering to the Lord, in addition to the regular burnt offering with its drink offering.
04Nm 28:16 "The Passover to the LORD comes in the first month, on the fourteenth day of the month.
04Nm 28:17 On the fifteenth day of this month there will be a festival; unleavened bread is to be eaten for seven days.
04Nm 28:18 On the first day there is to be a sacred assembly; you are not to do any daily work.
04Nm 28:19 Present a fire offering, a burnt offering to the LORD: two young bulls, one ram, and seven male lambs a year old. Your animals are to be unblemished.
04Nm 28:20 The grain offering with them is to be of fine flour mixed with oil; offer six quarts with each bull and four quarts with the ram.
04Nm 28:21 Offer two quarts with each of the seven lambs
04Nm 28:22 and one male goat for a sin offering to make atonement for yourselves.
04Nm 28:23 Offer these with the morning burnt offering that is part of the regular burnt offering.
04Nm 28:24 You are to offer the same food each day for seven days as a fire offering, a pleasing aroma to the LORD. It is to be offered with its drink offering and the regular burnt offering.
04Nm 28:25 On the seventh day you are to hold a sacred assembly; you are not to do any daily work.
04Nm 28:26 "On the day of firstfruits, you are to hold a sacred assembly when you present an offering of new grain to the LORD at your [Festival of] Weeks; you are not to do any daily work.
04Nm 28:27 Present a burnt offering for a pleasing aroma to the LORD: two young bulls, one ram, and seven male lambs a year old,
04Nm 28:28 with their grain offering of fine flour mixed with oil, six quarts with each bull, four quarts with the ram,
04Nm 28:29 and two quarts with each of the seven lambs
04Nm 28:30 and one male goat to make atonement for yourselves.
04Nm 28:31 Offer [them] with their drink offerings in addition to the regular burnt offering and its grain offering. Your animals are to be unblemished.
04Nm 29:1 "You are to hold a sacred assembly in the seventh month, on the first [day] of the month, and you are not to do any daily work. This will be a day of jubilation for you.
04Nm 29:2 Offer a burnt offering as a pleasing aroma to the LORD: one young bull, one ram, seven male lambs a year old-- [all] unblemished--
04Nm 29:3 with their grain offering of fine flour mixed with oil, six quarts with the bull, four quarts with the ram,
04Nm 29:4 and two quarts with each of the seven male lambs.
04Nm 29:5 Also [offer] one male goat as a sin offering to make atonement for yourselves.
04Nm 29:6 These are in addition to the monthly and regular burnt offerings with their grain offerings and drink offerings. They are a pleasing aroma, a fire offering to the LORD.
04Nm 29:7 "You are to hold a sacred assembly on the tenth [day] of this seventh month and practice self-denial; you must not do any work.
04Nm 29:8 Present a burnt offering to the LORD, a pleasing aroma: one young bull, one ram, and seven male lambs a year old. [All] your animals are to be unblemished.
04Nm 29:9 Their grain offering is to be of fine flour mixed with oil, six quarts with the bull, four quarts with the ram,
04Nm 29:10 and two quarts with each of the seven lambs.
04Nm 29:11 [Offer] one male goat for a sin offering. The regular burnt offering with its grain offering and drink offerings are in addition to the sin offering of atonement.
04Nm 29:12 "You are to hold a sacred assembly on the fifteenth day of the seventh month; you must not do any daily work. You are to celebrate a seven-day festival for the LORD.
04Nm 29:13 Present a burnt offering, a fire offering as a pleasing aroma to the LORD: 13 young bulls, two rams, and 14 male lambs a year old. They are to be unblemished.
04Nm 29:14 Their grain offering is to be of fine flour mixed with oil, six quarts with each of the 13 bulls, four quarts with each of the two rams,
04Nm 29:15 and two quarts with each of the 14 lambs.
04Nm 29:16 Also [offer] one male goat as a sin offering. These are in addition to the regular burnt offering with its grain and drink offerings.
04Nm 29:17 "On the second day [present] 12 young bulls, two rams, and 14 male lambs a year old-- [all] unblemished--
04Nm 29:18 with their grain and drink offerings for the bulls, rams, and lambs, in proportion to their number.
04Nm 29:19 Also [offer] one male goat as a sin offering. These are in addition to the regular burnt offering with its grain and drink offerings.
04Nm 29:20 "On the third day [present] 11 bulls, two rams, 14 male lambs a year old-- [all] unblemished--
04Nm 29:21 with their grain and drink offerings for the bulls, rams, and lambs, in proportion to their number.
04Nm 29:22 Also [offer] one male goat as a sin offering. These are in addition to the regular burnt offering with its grain and drink offerings.
04Nm 29:23 "On the fourth day [present] 10 bulls, two rams, 14 male lambs a year old-- [all] unblemished--
04Nm 29:24 with their grain and drink offerings for the bulls, rams, and lambs, in proportion to their number.
04Nm 29:25 Also [offer] one male goat as a sin offering. These are in addition to the regular burnt offering with its grain and drink offerings.
04Nm 29:26 "On the fifth day [present] nine bulls, two rams, 14 male lambs a year old-- [all] unblemished--
04Nm 29:27 with their grain and drink offerings for the bulls, rams, and lambs, in proportion to their number.
04Nm 29:28 Also [offer] one male goat as a sin offering. These are in addition to the regular burnt offering with its grain and drink offerings.
04Nm 29:29 "On the sixth day [present] eight bulls, two rams, 14 male lambs a year old-- [all] unblemished--
04Nm 29:30 with their grain and drink offerings for the bulls, rams, and lambs, in proportion to their number.
04Nm 29:31 Also [offer] one male goat as a sin offering. These are in addition to the regular burnt offering with its grain and drink offerings.
04Nm 29:32 "On the seventh day [present] seven bulls, two rams, and 14 male lambs a year old-- [all] unblemished--
04Nm 29:33 with their grain and drink offerings for the bulls, rams, and lambs, in proportion to their number.
04Nm 29:34 Also [offer] one male goat as a sin offering. These are in addition to the regular burnt offering with its grain and drink offerings.
04Nm 29:35 "On the eighth day you are to hold a solemn assembly; you are not to do any daily work.
04Nm 29:36 Present a burnt offering, a fire offering as a pleasing aroma to the LORD: one bull, one ram, seven male lambs a year old-- [all] unblemished--
04Nm 29:37 with their grain and drink offerings for the bulls, rams, and lambs, in proportion to their number.
04Nm 29:38 Also [offer] one male goat as a sin offering. These are in addition to the regular burnt offering with its grain and drink offerings.
04Nm 29:39 "You must offer these to the LORD at your appointed times in addition to your vow and freewill offerings, whether burnt, grain, drink, or fellowship offerings."
04Nm 29:40  So Moses told the Israelites everything the LORD had commanded him.
04Nm 30:1 Moses told the leaders of the Israelite tribes, "This is what the LORD has commanded:
04Nm 30:2 When a man makes a vow to the LORD or swears an oath to put himself under an obligation, he must not break his word; he must do whatever he has promised.
04Nm 30:3 "When a woman in her father's house during her youth makes a vow to the LORD or puts [herself] under an obligation,
04Nm 30:4 and her father hears about her vow or the obligation she put herself under, and he says nothing to her, all her vows and every obligation she put herself under are binding.
04Nm 30:5 But if her father prohibits her on the day he hears [about it], none of her vows and none of the obligations she put herself under are binding. The LORD will absolve her because her father has prohibited her.
04Nm 30:6 "If a woman marries while her vows or the rash commitment she herself made are binding,
04Nm 30:7 and her husband hears [about it] and says nothing to her when he finds out, her vows are binding, and the obligations she put herself under are binding.
04Nm 30:8 But if her husband prohibits her when he hears [about it], he will cancel her vow that is binding or the rash commitment she herself made, and the LORD will forgive her.
04Nm 30:9 "Any vow a widow or divorc? put herself under is binding on her.
04Nm 30:10 "If a woman in her husband's house has made a vow or put herself under an obligation with an oath,
04Nm 30:11 and her husband hears [about it], says nothing to her, and does not prohibit her, all her vows are binding, and every obligation she put herself under is binding.
04Nm 30:12 But if her husband cancels them on the day he hears [about it], nothing that came from her lips, whether her vows or her obligation, is binding. Her husband has canceled them, and the LORD will absolve her.
04Nm 30:13 Her husband may confirm or cancel any vow or any sworn obligation to deny herself.
04Nm 30:14 If her husband says nothing at all to her from day to day, he confirms all her vows and obligations, which are binding. He has confirmed them because he said nothing to her when he heard [about them].
04Nm 30:15 But if he cancels them after he hears [about them], he will be responsible for her commitment."
04Nm 30:16 These are the statutes that the LORD commanded Moses concerning [the relationship] between a man and his wife, or between a father and his daughter in his house during her youth.
04Nm 31:1 The LORD spoke to Moses,
04Nm 31:2 "Execute vengeance for the Israelites against the Midianites. After that, you will be gathered to your people."
04Nm 31:3 So Moses spoke to the people, "Equip some of your men for war. They will go against Midian to inflict the LORD's vengeance on them.
04Nm 31:4 Send 1,000 men to war from each Israelite tribe."
04Nm 31:5 So 1,000 were recruited from each Israelite tribe out of the thousands in Israel-- 12,000 equipped for war.
04Nm 31:6 Moses sent 1,000 from each tribe to war. They went with Phinehas son of Eleazar the priest, in whose care were the holy objects and signal trumpets.
04Nm 31:7 They waged war against Midian, as the LORD had commanded Moses, and killed every male.
04Nm 31:8 Along with the others slain by them, they killed the Midianite kings-- Evi, Rekem, Zur, Hur, and Reba, the five kings of Midian. They also killed Balaam son of Beor with the sword.
04Nm 31:9 The Israelites took the Midianite women and their children captive, and they plundered all their cattle, flocks, and property.
04Nm 31:10 Then they burned all the cities where the Midianites lived, as well as all their encampments,
04Nm 31:11 and took away all the spoils of war and the captives, both human and animal.
04Nm 31:12 They brought the prisoners, animals, and spoils of war to Moses, Eleazar the priest, and the Israelite community at the camp on the plains of Moab by the Jordan [across from] Jericho.
04Nm 31:13 Moses, Eleazar the priest, and all the leaders of the community went to meet them outside the camp.
04Nm 31:14 But Moses became furious with the officers, the commanders of thousands and commanders of hundreds, who were returning from the military campaign.
04Nm 31:15 "Have you let every female live?" he asked them.
04Nm 31:16 "Yet they are the ones who, at Balaam's advice, incited the Israelites to unfaithfulness against the LORD in the Peor incident, so that the plague came against the LORD's community.
04Nm 31:17 So now, kill all the male children and kill every woman who has had sexual relations with a man,
04Nm 31:18 but keep alive for yourselves all the young females who have not had sexual relations.
04Nm 31:19 "You are to remain outside the camp for seven days. All of you and your prisoners who have killed a person or touched the dead are to purify yourselves on the third day and the seventh day.
04Nm 31:20 Also purify everything: garments, leather goods, things made of goat hair, and every article of wood."
04Nm 31:21 Then Eleazar the priest said to the soldiers who had gone to battle, "This is the legal statute the LORD commanded Moses:
04Nm 31:22 Only the gold, silver, bronze, iron, tin, and lead--
04Nm 31:23 everything that can withstand fire-- put through fire, and it will be clean. It must still be purified with the purification water. Anything that cannot withstand fire, put through the water.
04Nm 31:24 On the seventh day wash your clothes, and you will be clean. After that you may enter the camp."
04Nm 31:25 The LORD told Moses,
04Nm 31:26 "You, Eleazar the priest, and the family leaders of the community are to take a count of what was captured, human and animal.
04Nm 31:27 Then divide the captives between the troops who went out to war and the entire community.
04Nm 31:28 Set aside a tribute for the LORD from what belongs to the fighting men who went out to war: one out of [every] 500 humans, cattle, donkeys, sheep, and goats.
04Nm 31:29 Take [the tribute] from their half and give [it] to Eleazar the priest as a contribution to the LORD.
04Nm 31:30 From the Israelites' half, take one out of every 50 from the people, cattle, donkeys, sheep, and goats, all the livestock, and give them to the Levites who perform the duties of the LORD's tabernacle."
04Nm 31:31 So Moses and Eleazar the priest did as the LORD commanded Moses.
04Nm 31:32 The captives remaining from the plunder the army had taken totaled: 675,000 sheep and goats,
04Nm 31:33 72,000 cattle,
04Nm 31:34 61,000 donkeys,
04Nm 31:35 and 32,000 people, all the females who had not had sexual relations with a man.
04Nm 31:36 The half portion for those who went out to war numbered: 337,500 sheep and goats,
04Nm 31:37 and the tribute to the LORD was 675 from the sheep and goats;
04Nm 31:38 from the 36,000 cattle, the tribute to the LORD was 72;
04Nm 31:39 from the 30,500 donkeys, the tribute to the LORD was 61;
04Nm 31:40 and from the 16,000 people, the tribute to the LORD was 32 people.
04Nm 31:41 Moses gave the tribute to Eleazar the priest as a contribution for the LORD, as the LORD had commanded Moses.
04Nm 31:42 From the Israelites' half, which Moses separated from the men who fought,
04Nm 31:43 the community's half was: 337,500 sheep and goats,
04Nm 31:44 36,000 cattle,
04Nm 31:45 30,500 donkeys,
04Nm 31:46 and 16,000 people.
04Nm 31:47 Moses took one out of [every] 50, selected from the people and the livestock from the Israelites' half. He gave them to the Levites who perform the duties of the LORD's tabernacle, as the LORD had commanded him.
04Nm 31:48 The officers who were over the thousands of the army, the commanders of thousands and of hundreds, approached Moses
04Nm 31:49 and told him, "Your servants have taken a census of the fighting men under our command, and not one of us is missing.
04Nm 31:50 So we have presented to the LORD an offering of the gold articles each man found-- armlets, bracelets, rings, earrings, and necklaces-- to make atonement for ourselves before the LORD."
04Nm 31:51 Moses and Eleazar the priest received from them all the articles made out of gold.
04Nm 31:52 All the gold of the contribution they offered to the Lord, from the commanders of thousands and of hundreds, was 420 pounds.
04Nm 31:53 Each of the soldiers had taken plunder for himself.
04Nm 31:54 Moses and Eleazar the priest received the gold from the commanders of thousands and of hundreds and brought it into the tent of meeting as a memorial for the Israelites before the LORD.
04Nm 32:1 The Reubenites and Gadites had a very large number of livestock. When they surveyed the lands of Jazer and Gilead, they saw that the region was a [good] one for livestock.
04Nm 32:2 So the Gadites and Reubenites came to Moses, Eleazar the priest, and the leaders of the community and said:
04Nm 32:3 "[The territory of] Ataroth, Dibon, Jazer, Nimrah, Heshbon, Elealeh, Sebam, Nebo, and Beon,
04Nm 32:4 which the LORD struck down before the community of Israel, is [good] land for livestock, and your servants own livestock."
04Nm 32:5 They said, "If we have found favor in your sight, let this land be given to your servants as a possession. Don't make us cross the Jordan."
04Nm 32:6 But Moses asked the Gadites and Reubenites, "Should your brothers go to war while you stay here?
04Nm 32:7 Why are you discouraging the Israelites from crossing into the land the LORD has given them?
04Nm 32:8 That's what your fathers did when I sent them from Kadesh-barnea to see the land.
04Nm 32:9 After they went up as far as Eshcol Valley and saw the land, they discouraged the Israelites from entering the land the LORD had given them.
04Nm 32:10 So the Lord's anger burned that day, and He swore an oath:
04Nm 32:11 'Because they did not follow Me completely, none of the men 20 years old or more who came up from Egypt will see the land I swore [to give] Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob--
04Nm 32:12 none except Caleb son of Jephunneh the Kenizzite and Joshua son of Nun, because they did follow the LORD completely.'
04Nm 32:13 The Lord's anger burned against Israel, and He made them wander in the wilderness 40 years until the whole generation that had done what was evil in the LORD's sight was gone.
04Nm 32:14 And here you, a brood of sinners, stand in your fathers' place adding even more to the LORD's burning anger against Israel.
04Nm 32:15 If you turn back from following Him, He will once again leave this people in the wilderness, and you will destroy all of them."
04Nm 32:16 Then they approached him and said, "We want to build sheepfolds here for our livestock and cities for our dependents.
04Nm 32:17 But we will arm ourselves and be ready [to go] ahead of the Israelites until we have brought them into their place. Meanwhile, our dependents will remain in the fortified cities because of the inhabitants of the land.
04Nm 32:18 We will not return to our homes until each of the Israelites has taken possession of his inheritance.
04Nm 32:19 Yet we will not have an inheritance with them across the Jordan and beyond, because our inheritance will be across the Jordan to the east."
04Nm 32:20 Moses replied to them, "If you do this-- if you arm yourselves for battle before the Lord,
04Nm 32:21 and every one of your armed men crosses the Jordan before the LORD until He has driven His enemies from His presence,
04Nm 32:22 and the land is subdued before the LORD-- afterwards you may return and be free from obligation to the LORD and to Israel. And this land will belong to you as a possession before the LORD.
04Nm 32:23 But if you don't do this, you will certainly sin against the LORD; be sure your sin will catch up with you.
04Nm 32:24 Build cities for your dependents and folds for your flocks, but do what you have promised."
04Nm 32:25 The Gadites and Reubenites answered Moses, "Your servants will do just as my lord commands.
04Nm 32:26 Our little children, wives, livestock, and all our animals will remain here in the cities of Gilead,
04Nm 32:27 but your servants are equipped for war before the LORD and will go across to the battle as my lord orders."
04Nm 32:28 So Moses gave orders about them to Eleazar the priest, Joshua son of Nun, and the family leaders of the Israelite tribes.
04Nm 32:29 Moses told them, "If the Gadites and Reubenites cross the Jordan with you, every man in battle formation before the LORD, and the land is subdued before you, you are to give them the land of Gilead as a possession.
04Nm 32:30 But if they don't go across with you in battle formation, they must accept land in Canaan with you."
04Nm 32:31 The Gadites and Reubenites replied, "What the LORD has spoken to your servants is what we will do.
04Nm 32:32 We will cross over in battle formation before the LORD into the land of Canaan, but we will keep our hereditary possession across the Jordan."
04Nm 32:33 So Moses gave them-- the Gadites, Reubenites, and half the tribe of Manasseh son of Joseph-- the kingdom of Sihon king of the Amorites and the kingdom of Og king of Bashan, the land including its cities with the territories surrounding them.
04Nm 32:34 The Gadites rebuilt Dibon, Ataroth, Aroer,
04Nm 32:35 Atroth-shophan, Jazer, Jogbehah,
04Nm 32:36 Beth-nimrah, and Beth-haran as fortified cities, and [built] sheepfolds.
04Nm 32:37 The Reubenites rebuilt Heshbon, Elealeh, Kiriathaim,
04Nm 32:38 as well as Nebo and Baal-meon (whose names were changed), and Sibmah. They gave names to the cities they rebuilt.
04Nm 32:39 The descendants of Machir son of Manasseh went to Gilead, captured it, and drove out the Amorites who were there.
04Nm 32:40 So Moses gave Gilead to [the clan of] Machir son of Manasseh, and they settled in it.
04Nm 32:41 Jair, a descendant of Manasseh, went and captured their villages, which he renamed Jair's Villages.
04Nm 32:42 Nobah went and captured Kenath with its villages and called it Nobah after his own name.
04Nm 33:1 These were the stages of the Israelites' journey when they went out of the land of Egypt by their military divisions under the leadership of Moses and Aaron.
04Nm 33:2 At the LORD's command, Moses wrote down the starting points for the stages of their journey; these are the stages [listed] by their starting points:
04Nm 33:3 They departed from Rameses in the first month, on the fifteenth day of the month. On the day after the Passover the Israelites went out triumphantly in the sight of all the Egyptians.
04Nm 33:4 Meanwhile, the Egyptians were burying every firstborn male the LORD had struck down among them, for the LORD had executed judgment against their gods.
04Nm 33:5 The Israelites departed from Rameses and camped at Succoth.
04Nm 33:6 They departed from Succoth and camped at Etham, which is on the edge of the wilderness.
04Nm 33:7 They departed from Etham and turned back to Pi-hahiroth, which faces Baal-zephon, and they camped before Migdol.
04Nm 33:8 They departed from Pi-hahiroth and crossed through the middle of the sea into the wilderness. They took a three-day journey into the Wilderness of Etham and camped at Marah.
04Nm 33:9 They departed from Marah and came to Elim. There were 12 springs of water and 70 date palms at Elim, so they camped there.
04Nm 33:10 They departed from Elim and camped by the Red Sea.
04Nm 33:11 They departed from the Red Sea and camped in the Wilderness of Sin.
04Nm 33:12 They departed from the Wilderness of Sin and camped in Dophkah.
04Nm 33:13 They departed from Dophkah and camped at Alush.
04Nm 33:14 They departed from Alush and camped at Rephidim, where there was no water for the people to drink.
04Nm 33:15 They departed from Rephidim and camped in the Wilderness of Sinai.
04Nm 33:16 They departed from the Wilderness of Sinai and camped at Kibroth-hattaavah.
04Nm 33:17 They departed from Kibroth-hattaavah and camped at Hazeroth.
04Nm 33:18 They departed from Hazeroth and camped at Rithmah.
04Nm 33:19 They departed from Rithmah and camped at Rimmon-perez.
04Nm 33:20 They departed from Rimmon-perez and camped at Libnah.
04Nm 33:21 They departed from Libnah and camped at Rissah.
04Nm 33:22 They departed from Rissah and camped at Kehelathah.
04Nm 33:23 They departed from Kehelathah and camped at Mount Shepher.
04Nm 33:24 They departed from Mount Shepher and camped at Haradah.
04Nm 33:25 They departed from Haradah and camped at Makheloth.
04Nm 33:26 They departed from Makheloth and camped at Tahath.
04Nm 33:27 They departed from Tahath and camped at Terah.
04Nm 33:28 They departed from Terah and camped at Mithkah.
04Nm 33:29 They departed from Mithkah and camped at Hashmonah.
04Nm 33:30 They departed from Hashmonah and camped at Moseroth.
04Nm 33:31 They departed from Moseroth and camped at Bene-jaakan.
04Nm 33:32 They departed from Bene-jaakan and camped at Hor-haggidgad.
04Nm 33:33 They departed from Hor-haggidgad and camped at Jotbathah.
04Nm 33:34 They departed from Jotbathah and camped at Abronah.
04Nm 33:35 They departed from Abronah and camped at Ezion-geber.
04Nm 33:36 They departed from Ezion-geber and camped in the Wilderness of Zin (that is, Kadesh).
04Nm 33:37 They departed from Kadesh and camped at Mount Hor on the edge of the land of Edom.
04Nm 33:38 At the LORD's command, Aaron the priest climbed Mount Hor and died there on the first [day] of the fifth month in the fortieth year after the Israelites went out of the land of Egypt.
04Nm 33:39 Aaron was 123 years old when he died on Mount Hor.
04Nm 33:40 At that time the Canaanite king of Arad, who lived in the Negev in the land of Canaan, heard the Israelites were coming.
04Nm 33:41 They departed from Mount Hor and camped at Zalmonah.
04Nm 33:42 They departed from Zalmonah and camped at Punon.
04Nm 33:43 They departed from Punon and camped at Oboth.
04Nm 33:44 They departed from Oboth and camped at Iye-abarim on the border of Moab.
04Nm 33:45 They departed from Iyim and camped at Dibon-gad.
04Nm 33:46 They departed from Dibon-gad and camped at Almon-diblathaim.
04Nm 33:47 They departed from Almon-diblathaim and camped in the Abarim [range] facing Nebo.
04Nm 33:48 They departed from the Abarim [range] and camped on the plains of Moab by the Jordan [across from] Jericho.
04Nm 33:49 They camped by the Jordan from Beth-jeshimoth to Acacia Meadows on the plains of Moab.
04Nm 33:50 The LORD spoke to Moses in the plains of Moab by the Jordan [across from] Jericho,
04Nm 33:51 "Tell the Israelites: When you cross the Jordan into the land of Canaan,
04Nm 33:52 you must drive out all the inhabitants of the land before you, destroy all their stone images and cast images, and demolish all their high places.
04Nm 33:53 You are to take possession of the land and settle in it because I have given you the land to possess.
04Nm 33:54 You are to receive the land as an inheritance by lot according to your clans. Increase the inheritance for a large clan and decrease it for a small one. Whatever place the lot indicates for someone will be his. You will receive an inheritance according to your ancestral tribes.
04Nm 33:55 But if you don't drive out the inhabitants of the land before you, those you allow to remain will become thorns in your eyes and in your sides; they will harass you in the land where you will live.
04Nm 33:56 And what I had planned to do to them, I will do to you."
04Nm 34:1 The LORD spoke to Moses,
04Nm 34:2 "Command the Israelites and say to them: When you enter the land of Canaan, it will be allotted to you as an inheritance with these borders:
04Nm 34:3 Your southern side will be from the Wilderness of Zin along the boundary of Edom. Your southern border on the east will begin at the east end of the Dead Sea.
04Nm 34:4 Your border will turn south of the Ascent of Akrabbim, proceed to Zin, and end south of Kadesh-barnea. It will go to Hazar-addar and proceed to Azmon.
04Nm 34:5 The border will turn from Azmon to the Brook of Egypt, where it will end at the Mediterranean Sea.
04Nm 34:6 Your western border will be the coastline of the Mediterranean Sea; this will be your western border.
04Nm 34:7 This will be your northern border: From the Mediterranean Sea draw a line to Mount Hor;
04Nm 34:8 from Mount Hor draw a line to the entrance of Hamath, and the border will reach Zedad.
04Nm 34:9 Then the border will go to Ziphron and end at Hazar-enan. This will be your northern border.
04Nm 34:10 For your eastern border, draw a line from Hazar-enan to Shepham.
04Nm 34:11 The border will go down from Shepham to Riblah east of Ain. It will continue down and reach the eastern slope of the Sea of Chinnereth.
04Nm 34:12 Then the border will go down to the Jordan and end at the Dead Sea. This will be your land [defined] by its borders on all sides."
04Nm 34:13 So Moses commanded the Israelites, "This is the land you are to receive by lot as an inheritance, which the LORD commanded to be given to the nine and a half tribes.
04Nm 34:14 For the tribe of the Reubenites and the tribe of the Gadites have received [their inheritance] according to their ancestral houses, and half the tribe of Manasseh has received its inheritance.
04Nm 34:15 The two and a half tribes have received their inheritance across the Jordan from Jericho, eastward toward the sunrise."
04Nm 34:16 The LORD spoke to Moses,
04Nm 34:17 "These are the names of the men who are to distribute the land as an inheritance for you: Eleazar the priest and Joshua son of Nun.
04Nm 34:18 Take one leader from each tribe to distribute the land.
04Nm 34:19 These are the names of the men: Caleb son of Jephunneh from the tribe of Judah;
04Nm 34:20 Shemuel son of Ammihud from the tribe of Simeon;
04Nm 34:21 Elidad son of Chislon from the tribe of Benjamin;
04Nm 34:22 Bukki son of Jogli, a leader from the tribe of Dan;
04Nm 34:23 from the sons of Joseph: Hanniel son of Ephod, a leader from the tribe of Manasseh,
04Nm 34:24 Kemuel son of Shiphtan, a leader from the tribe of Ephraim;
04Nm 34:25 Eli-zaphan son of Parnach, a leader from the tribe of Zebulun;
04Nm 34:26 Paltiel son of Azzan, a leader from the tribe of Issachar;
04Nm 34:27 Ahihud son of Shelomi, a leader from the tribe of Asher;
04Nm 34:28 Pedahel son of Ammihud, a leader from the tribe of Naphtali."
04Nm 34:29 These are the ones the LORD commanded to distribute the inheritance to the Israelites in the land of Canaan.
04Nm 35:1 The LORD again spoke to Moses in the plains of Moab by the Jordan [across from] Jericho:
04Nm 35:2 "Command the Israelites to give cities out of their hereditary property for the Levites to live in and pastureland around the cities.
04Nm 35:3 The cities will be for them to live in, and their pasturelands will be for their herds, flocks, and all their [other] animals.
04Nm 35:4 The pasturelands of the cities you are to give the Levites [will extend] from the city wall 500 yards on every side.
04Nm 35:5 Measure 1,000 yards outside the city for the east side, 1,000 yards for the south side, 1,000 yards for the west side, and 1,000 yards for the north side, with the city in the center. This will belong to them as pasturelands for the cities.
04Nm 35:6 "The cities you give the Levites will include six cities of refuge, which you must provide so that the one who kills someone may flee there; in addition to these, give 42 [other] cities.
04Nm 35:7 The total number of cities you give the Levites will be 48, along with their pasturelands.
04Nm 35:8 Of the cities that you give from the Israelites' territory, you should take more from a larger [tribe] and less from a smaller one. Each [tribe] is to give some of its cities to the Levites in proportion to the inheritance it receives."
04Nm 35:9 The LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 35:10 "Speak to the Israelites and tell them: When you cross the Jordan into the land of Canaan,
04Nm 35:11 designate cities to serve as cities of refuge for you, so that a person who kills someone unintentionally may flee there.
04Nm 35:12 You will have the cities as a refuge from the avenger, so that the one who kills someone will not die until he stands trial before the assembly.
04Nm 35:13 The cities you select will be your six cities of refuge.
04Nm 35:14 Select three cities across the Jordan and three cities in the land of Canaan to be cities of refuge.
04Nm 35:15 These six cities will serve as a refuge for the Israelites and for the foreigner or temporary resident among them, so that anyone who kills a person unintentionally may flee there.
04Nm 35:16 "If anyone strikes a person with an iron object and death results, he is a murderer; the murderer must be put to death.
04Nm 35:17 If a man has in his hand a stone capable of causing death and strikes another man and he dies, the murderer must be put to death.
04Nm 35:18 If a man has in his hand a wooden object capable of causing death and he dies, the murderer must be put to death.
04Nm 35:19 The avenger of blood himself is to kill the murderer; when he finds him, he is to kill him.
04Nm 35:20 Likewise, if anyone in hatred pushes a person or throws [an object] at him with malicious intent and he dies,
04Nm 35:21 or if in hostility he strikes him with his hand and he dies, the one who struck him must be put to death; he is a murderer. The avenger of blood is to kill the murderer when he finds him.
04Nm 35:22 "But if anyone suddenly pushes a person without hostility or throws any object at him without malicious intent
04Nm 35:23 or drops a stone without looking that could kill a person and he dies, but he was not his enemy and wasn't trying to harm him,
04Nm 35:24 the assembly is to judge between the slayer and the avenger of blood according to these ordinances.
04Nm 35:25 The assembly is to protect the one who kills someone from the hand of the avenger of blood. Then the assembly will return him to the city of refuge he fled to, and he must live there until the death of the high priest who was anointed with the holy oil.
04Nm 35:26 "If the one who kills someone ever goes outside the border of the city of refuge he fled to,
04Nm 35:27 and the avenger of blood finds him outside the border of his city of refuge and kills him, the avenger will not be guilty of bloodshed,
04Nm 35:28 for the one who killed a person was supposed to live in his city of refuge until the death of the high priest. Only after the death of the high priest may the one who has killed a person return to the land he possesses.
04Nm 35:29 These [instructions] will be a statutory ordinance for you throughout your generations wherever you live.
04Nm 35:30 "If anyone kills a person, the murderer is to be put to death based on the word of witnesses. But no one is to be put to death based on the testimony of one witness.
04Nm 35:31 You are not to accept a ransom for the life of a murderer who is guilty of killing someone; he must be put to death.
04Nm 35:32 Neither should you accept a ransom for the person who flees to his city of refuge, allowing him to return and live in the land before the death of the [high] priest.
04Nm 35:33 "Do not defile the land where you are, for bloodshed defiles the land, and there can be no atonement for the land because of the blood that is shed on it, except by the blood of the person who shed it.
04Nm 35:34 Do not make the land unclean where you live and where I reside; for I, the Lord, reside among the Israelites."
04Nm 36:1 The family leaders from the clan of the descendants of Gilead-- the son of Machir, son of Manasseh-- one of the clans of the sons of Joseph approached and addressed Moses and the leaders who were over the Israelite families.
04Nm 36:2 They said, "The LORD commanded my lord to give the land as an inheritance by lot to the Israelites. My lord was further commanded by the LORD to give our brother Zelophehad's inheritance to his daughters.
04Nm 36:3 If they marry any of the men from the [other] Israelite tribes, their inheritance will be taken away from our fathers' inheritance and added to that of the tribe into which they marry. Therefore, part of our allotted inheritance would be taken away.
04Nm 36:4 When the Jubilee comes for the Israelites, their inheritance will be added to that of the tribe into which they marry, and their inheritance will be taken away from the inheritance of our ancestral tribe."
04Nm 36:5 So Moses commanded the Israelites at the word of the LORD, "What the tribe of Joseph's descendants says is right.
04Nm 36:6 This is what the LORD has commanded concerning Zelophehad's daughters: They may marry anyone they like provided they marry within a clan of their ancestral tribe.
04Nm 36:7 An inheritance belonging to the Israelites must not transfer from tribe to tribe, because each of the Israelites is to retain the inheritance of his ancestral tribe.
04Nm 36:8 Any daughter who possesses an inheritance from an Israelite tribe must marry someone from the clan of her ancestral tribe, so that each of the Israelites will possess the inheritance of his fathers.
04Nm 36:9 No inheritance is to transfer from one tribe to another, because each of the Israelite tribes is to retain its inheritance."
04Nm 36:10 The daughters of Zelophehad did as the LORD commanded Moses.
04Nm 36:11 Mahlah, Tirzah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Noah, the daughters of Zelophehad, married cousins on their father's side.
04Nm 36:12 They married [men] from the clans of the descendants of Manasseh son of Joseph, and their inheritance remained within the tribe of their father's clan.
04Nm 36:13 These are the commands and ordinances the LORD commanded the Israelites through Moses in the plains of Moab by the Jordan [across from] Jericho.
